title: italian chicken
directions: You will also need an oven cooking bag.

title: cool whip cookies
directions: Beat egg into Cool Whip.
Add cake mix and mix thoroughly. Chill overnight.
Roll into balls and then into confectioners sugar.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: cabbage burger bake
directions: Brown meat and onion together; drain off fat.
Add salt and pepper.
Put uncooked rice in bottom of casserole dish, then meat, cabbage and carrot.
Mix soup with milk and pour over top.
Cover with tinfoil.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and cook 15 minutes.

title: grilled sliced potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain and peel potatoes.
Cut lengthwise into 1/2-inch slices.
Brush with oil and sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
Cook over hot coals on grill.
Brown on both sides.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water to cover.
Drain, cool and peel.
Mash in large bowl with butter, milk and season to taste with salt and pepper; set aside.
Saute beef until browned, stirring to keep meat crumbly.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, parsley, tomato paste, Worcestershire and gravy.
Stir to mix.
Add peas and cook about 5 minutes.
Turn mixture into a casserole dish.
Spread potatoes evenly over meat.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes until top is crispy brown.

title: quick and easy rolls
directions: Pour water into a large mixing bowl. Add yeast. Let stand a minute. Stir to dissolved. Add half the flour, salt, shortening, and egg. Beat with mixer until smooth. Add rest of flour. Stir in by hand until smooth. Cover, let rise about 30 minutes. Roll out, cut and put into pans. Let rise again for 30 minutes. Bake in 425 degree oven about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: wilcox's apple nut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve on crisp lettuce leaves. Serves 6.

title: ooey gooey cake
directions: With your hands, mix first 4 ingredients.
Press in pan.
With mixer, combine next 3 ingredients.
Pour over first layer.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift the confectioners sugar.
Beat the shortening creamy. If you use the butter for the shortening, reduce the milk by 1 tablespoon.
Gradually beat in the sifted sugar.
Add one egg at a time and beat each in thoroughly. Add and beat in vanilla. Measure flour and mix with baking powder.
Blend flour into beaten mixture in small amounts with alternate additions of milk.
After all is added, beat the batter hard.
Pour into lightly buttered and flour dusted tube pan, filling no more than 3/4 full.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours until lightly browned and pulled slightly away from sides of pan.

title: snow biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add melted shortening. Dough will be soft.
Turn out on floured board and knead dough quickly and lightly until smooth and elastic.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in greased pan.
Let rise until doubled in bulk, about 1/2 hour.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for about 20 minutes.

title: diabetic-sweet and sour sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cook for 10 minutes, uncovered.
Discard garlic.
Use for fruit salad, with Chinese dishes, or for basting chicken or pork.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate at least 2 hours.
Cook over medium heat.
Serve as vegetable or over charcoaled steaks. Serves 6 to 8.

title: new potatoes au gratin
directions: Greens (mustard, turnips, collard, kale, poke, dandelion, etc.) are best when cooked with meat.
Salt pork, ham hock, bacon ends or pork back and neck bones makes the "pot likken" extra good.
Put the meat on to boil while cleaning greens.
Cut or pinch off thick stems.
Wash and drain greens several times to remove dirt and grit.
A strong salt water solution helps to take the grit to the bottom.
Add greens to pot with meat; be sure liquid is boiling.
A small piece of red pepper may be added, also a whole onion.
Season to taste with salt.
(Some cooks add a touch of sugar.)
Cook until tender.
This will take from 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Do not drain greens; herein lies most of the nutritious value of this food.
A pressure cooker may be used, if desired.
Serve with pepper sauce, pepper relish or spring onion along with cornbread and buttermilk.

title: pecan snowballs
directions: Beat butter with mixer until fluffy.
Add sugar, pecans, flour and vanilla and blend well.
Refrigerate one hour.
Make into one-inch balls.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place balls one-inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until slightly brown, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool a few minutes, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake on low heat in crock-pot for 14 hours.
Freeze or process in jars.

title: cream of chicken soup
directions: Combine chicken and water in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 20-25 minutes. Remove chicken and let cool, reserving 3 1/2 c. broth. Bone chicken and chop meat. Combine chicken, reserved broth, carrots, celery, salt and pepper in a Dutch oven. Bring to a boil; over, reduce heat, and simmer 1 hour. Combine milk and flour, stirring until smooth. Gradually add soup to mixture, stirring well. Simmer, uncovered, an additional 15 minutes or until thickened, stirring occasionally.
5 cups.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown beef and add tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix.
Beat eggs and add Ricotta cheese.
Layer:
noodles, meat, Ricotta and top with Cheddar, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese. (Makes 3 layers.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut and serve.
May be frozen.

title: russian salad
directions: Mix marshmallows, jello, water and cream cheese over medium heat, whipping to make smooth.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Pour into 2-quart mold and refrigerate to set.

title: herbed lamb loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare 9 x 5 x 3 loan pan; set aside. Beat eggs lightly with a fork in a mixing bowl.
Add meat and blend together lightly with a fork.
Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water and add along with all remaining ingredients.
Blend lightly with a fork.
Put into loaf pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk in a large bowl.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Put thin layer of pudding mixture into casserole dish.
Cover with a layer of vanilla wafers followed by a layer of sliced bananas.
Repeat layers of pudding, vanilla wafers and bananas.
End with layer of pudding.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Melt butter over low flame.
Add milk.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Chill mixture until it can be handled easily.
Roll into balls.
Place toothpicks in balls and place in freezer.
Melt chocolate and paraffin over low flame. Remove from heat and dip balls in chocolate.
Place on waxed paper.

title: old fashioned amber pie
directions: Cream sugar, flour and butter.
Add well beaten egg yolks and the other ingredients in the order given.
Cook slowly until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue made with the 4 egg whites and brown at 350°.

title: heath bars
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Line the foil with the 40 saltine crackers.
In saucepan, combine butter and sugar.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 minutes.
Pour over saltines.
Bake 5 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top and return to oven for 12 seconds.
Spread melted chips over saltines and refrigerate 2 hours.
Peel from foil and break into pieces.

title: coconut pie(alma's)
directions: Bake in unbaked crusts.
Makes 2 pies.

title: horseradish cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Form into ball and chill.
Roll in parsley flakes.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove bones. Place a layer of crumbs in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Add half of the chicken.
Cover with another layer of crumbs; pour chicken stock over this mixture.
Add remainder of chicken.
Pour undiluted mushroom soup over entire mixture.
Top with remaining crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Grease 9 x 3-inch spring-form pan.
Dust with graham cracker crumbs.
In large mixing bowl, mix cottage cheese and cream cheese.
Beat on high until smooth and creamy.
Beat in sugar, then eggs.
Beat on low the next 3 ingredients.
Beat in margarine and sour cream until smooth.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 325° for 70 minutes or until firm around edges.
Turn oven off.
Let stand in oven 2 hours.
Remove and chill.
Remove side of pan.
Top with strawberry glaze (optional).
Serves 12.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, dark syrup and water
in a 2 quart saucepan until crackle
stage.
Pour
syrup
slowly
into
beaten
egg whites, beating until nearly set.
Add vanilla and nuts.
When stiff enough to hold shape, drop
by
teaspoons onto wax paper or quickly pour into buttered pan.

title: orange chicken and rice skillet
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken.
Cook and stir 3 minutes; drain.
Reduce heat to medium.
Stir in combined dressing, orange juice and sugar.
Add rice and green pepper.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on box.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onion, cheese and broccoli.
Pour in casserole dish and top with crushed cheese crackers.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°, then 5 minutes at 450°.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Poke holes in cake when done. Boil sugar and pineapple with juice and pour over cake.
Mix pudding with milk.
Pour over sugar and pineapple.
Cool completely.
Frost with Cool Whip.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Blend together the graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted margarine.
Press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend the cream cheese and sugar. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon onto graham cracker crust and spread evenly. Chill at least 3 hours. Top with your favorite topping or fresh fruit.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Place rice in large baking pan.
Melt margarine and pour over rice.
Place pieces of chicken on top of rice.
Dilute soups with milk and water.
Mix together and pour over all.
Cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 250° or until done.
Can use pork chops.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix all ingredients together.
Top with sliced maraschino cherries and freeze.

title: corn, green bean casserole
directions: Mix all except crackers and butter.
Place in casserole dish. Top with crackers and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry squares
directions: Stir together the flour, brown sugar, walnuts and butter. Spread evenly in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: custard
directions: Too much salt will make eggs watery.

title: italian heritage casserole
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with vegetable oil.
Arrange potatoes and peppers in the bottom of the dish.

title: blue cheese pecan dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Keep chilled until ready to serve. Serve with potato chips or crackers.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla; combine dry ingredients and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Bake in a greased 10-inch tube pan at 325° for about one hour and 20 minutes.
Yields one 10-inch cake.

title: fruit dip 2
directions: Cream cheese.
Add marshmallow cream.
When well blended, add Cool Whip.
Serve with fresh fruits.

title: easy mushroom sauce
directions: Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Remove mushrooms only.
Add sliced garlic to drippings.
Saute for a few minutes, then remove and discard.

title: white potato custard pie
directions: Cream potatoes, melted butter, sugar and eggs; add milk.
Beat egg whites separately and fold in last.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook for 10 minutes or until brown. Reduce heat to 325° and cook about 20 minutes.
Don't overcook. Remove pie from oven when pie filling is completely set but wiggles some.
Makes 2 (8-inch) pies.

title: supper in a skillet
directions: Cook beef in oil until gray in color.
Add onion and celery; cook until onion is soft.
Add ketchup, water, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, mustard and oregano; mix well.
Stir in cooked macaroni.
Cover; simmer to cook meat and blend flavors, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Just before serving, fold in cheese and add parsley.

title: hot-sweet pickles
directions: Pour juice off pickles; keep jar.
Slice pickles in rings 1/4-inch thick.
Put pickles back in jar with sugar and Tabasco sauce.
Let soak for 3 weeks, shaking the jar once daily.
Jar up in hot, sterilized jars and lids.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over top.
Pour melted butter over mixture.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.
Good!!

title: southern style pecan fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, heat sugar, butter, cocoa, milk, vanilla and salt over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Stir in nuts. Spread mixture quickly in buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: english apple pie
directions: In a medium bowl, beat butter and brown sugar with mixer until pale and fluffy.
Stir in flour, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and water until smooth and thick.
Stir in pecans.
Mound apples in a 9-inch pie plate.
Mix granulated sugar with remaining 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples in dollops.

title: overnight sweet rolls
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan. Arrange dough balls evenly in pan. Sprinkle nuts, sugar, cinnamon and dry pudding mix on top. Cut butter in chunks. Put butter chunks on top of pudding mixture. Place in cold oven overnight and bake in the morning at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add mayonnaise to taste. Chill and eat.

title: arlean's baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients together except the bacon.
Place in baking dish.
Lay bacon on top.
Bake until bacon is done, uncovered, at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until well blended.
Roll level tablespoon of the mixture into balls the size of walnuts. Arrange them on a cookie sheet, close but not touching.
Freeze until hard.
Then pack in gallon size freezer bag.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Peel apples, remove cores and slice. Blend dry ingredients together. Toss apples with lemon juice and dry ingredients. Place flour-coated pie crust in bottom of a pie plate. Turn fruit mixture, including any juices, into the bottom crust. Place top crust on the pie, trim and flute edges. Place slits in the top of the crust to allow steam to escape. Brush beaten egg white over the top of crust and sprinkle with granulated sugar. Place pie on bottom rack of preheated oven. Bake 25 minutes, until crust is golden brown. Reduce oven temperature to 375° and continue to bake until juices bubble and crust is a deep golden brown, 30 to 35 minutes. The bottom crust should be golden and the juices bubbling. Remove pie from oven and place on wire rack. Let pie cool to almost room temperature, about 4 hours. Pie is best eaten when completely cooled, even the next day.

title: hershey cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and add to milk, eggs, oil and vanilla. Stir in boiling water.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes for a round pan and 35 to 40 minutes for rectangular pan.
Delicious!

title: chow mein
directions: Cook meat 10 minutes in Crisco. Add onions. Cook 10 more minutes. Add celery and cook 10 more minutes. Add 1 1/2 cups water. Simmer until celery is tender.
Drain bean sprouts and add to vegetables and bring to a boil.
Combine the 1/3 cup water, cornstarch, soy sauce and sugar.
Add cornstarch mixture and cook until clear.
Cook 1 cup rice.
Serve with rice and chow mein noodles.

title: squash casserole
directions: Soak bread crumbs in hot milk.
Cook onions with squash.
Mix other ingredients, except crackers and butter.
Crush crackers. Put on top with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8 people.

title: oven baked smothered rabbit
directions: Soak rabbit in salt water for about 20 minutes.
Batter with flour.
Melt 1 stick of butter in large casserole pan (heat oven to 350°).
Place rabbit pieces in pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Turn pieces.
Cook 15 more minutes.
In frying pan, melt 1/2 stick butter.
Add 4 tablespoons flour.
Mix well (until creamy). Slowly add chicken broth until smooth.
Add milk and soup until smooth.
Pour over rabbit.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: sangria
directions: Squeeze and slice oranges and lemons.
Mix all ingredients. Add ice cubes.
Enjoy!

title: hugh's blender hollandaise sauce
directions: Heat butter in saucepan until very hot, not brown.
Clarify butter (skim top off butter).
Put egg yolks, lemon juice and seasonings into blender.
Cover, then mix 2 minutes.
Turn on top speed.
Remove cover; slowly pour in all butter.
Meantime, have hot water on side.
If mixture gets too thick and slows blender, add 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon hot water to keep blending.
Serve over asparagus, Eggs Benedict or any vegetable.

title: chili sausage squares
directions: Combine biscuit mix, milk and 2 tablespoons mayonnaise.
Stir well. Spread mixture in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside. Cook sausage and onion until brown, stirring to crumble meat. Drain.
Layer sausage mixture over biscuit mixture.
Combine egg and cheese; spread over sausage. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: blueberry biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together with electric mixer until smooth, reserving blueberries.
You must fold in the blueberries by hand to avoid breaking them.
Spoon onto cookie sheets 1/2 cup size pancakes.
Leave plenty of space between, approx. 6 per pan. Bake 375 degrees 12-14 minutes.
They are done when the middle springs back when touched.

title: old fashioned pull candy
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until it will spin a thread or to soft crack stage (265°) when dropped in cool water.
Pour into well buttered plates.
Add peanuts, if desired.
When candy is cool enough to handle, with well buttered hands (with another person), pull until it begins to get firm and turns white.
Make a rope and cut or break into 3 to 4-inch pieces. Wrap each in wax paper.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: In chicken fat or margarine, saute onion and grated carrot. Add flour and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth.
Add cream-style corn, half and half or milk, black pepper and parsley for color.
Let simmer for 3 to 4 minutes, then add cut up chicken.
Let simmer for awhile.

title: yogurt cheese
directions: Line a colander with cheesecloth.
Spoon in yogurt and set colander in a bowl.
Let it drain in the refrigerator overnight.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, egg yolks, sugar and flour.
Cook until thick. Add coconut and vanilla.
Put in baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until thick.
Spread over pie.
Sprinkle with coconut, put in oven long enough to brown.

title: just right custard pie
directions: Beat egg whites.
Mix egg yolks, sugar, salt and flour together.
Heat milk; fold in egg whites and vanilla.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, then at 325° until nicely browned and set. Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: easy spoon rolls
directions: Put yeast in water.
Melt margarine and cream with sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Pour in with yeast.
Add flour and stir until well mixed.
Put dough in bowl that can be tightly closed.
Store in refrigerator to cook; drop by spoonfuls into greased muffin tins and bake at 350°.
Dough keeps several days in refrigerator in a tightly closed bowl.
Rolls can be baked as soon as dough is mixed.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix and let set before serving.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: quick and easy "tandy kakes"
directions: Bake cake mix as directed.
Cool.
Spread layer of peanut butter on cooled cake; refrigerate.
Melt Hershey bar and spread over refrigerated cake.
Cut into bite sized pieces and refrigerate again.
When chocolate top is hardened "Tandy Kakes" are ready to eat!

title: 7-minute frosting
directions: In a double boiler or in a large metal bowl with a hand-held electric mixer, beat together all frosting ingredients, except vanilla, until combined. Set mixture over a saucepan of boiling water and beat on high speed until it holds stiff, glossy peaks, about 7 minutes (depending on your mixer and the weather; this may take longer than 7 minutes, 10 minutes). Remove double boiler or bowl from heat and beat in vanilla. Beat frosting until cool and spreadable.

title: peg's reuben casserole
directions: Tear beef into bite size pieces and place into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Spread on dressing.
Drain sauerkraut and place on top of beef.
Add cheese.
Top with bread cubes, which have been tossed with butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350° or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: microwave white sauce
directions: Melt butter in quart size measuring cup on High for 30 seconds.
Add flour and seasonings; stir well.
Add a little of the milk and stir until smooth, then add the rest of the milk and stir well.
Microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Stir well and microwave for 2 minutes, until sauce thickens.

title: orange buttermilk salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. When mixture boils, immediately add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Cool slightly.
Stir in buttermilk. Chill until partially set.
Fold in whipped topping and nuts.

title: bakers aid
directions: Pour granulated sugar slowly into the blender at its highest speed.
The longer you blend the finer the sugar.

title: stuffed portabello mushrooms
directions: Remove stem and skin mushroom caps by grabbing edge with thumb and forefinger and pulling.
Put caps in small bowl and pour dressing over.
Marinate 2 hours in refrigerator.
Shake off excess dressing and put mushroom caps, round side down, in baking dish.
Divide remaining ingredients and layer half in each cap starting with basil, followed by Prosciutto ham and Monterey Jack and Cheddar cheeses.
Slice pimentos 1/2-inch thick and crisscross over top of stuffed caps.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: shake and make ice cream
directions: Mix ice cream mix and sugar with 1/2 cup warm milk to dissolve it. Add it to Eagle Brand condensed milk and 1/2 gallon milk in a half gallon container; mix well. In a gallon Ziploc bag, put 2 cups crushed ice and 3 tablespoons rock salt. In a sandwich Ziploc, put 1/2 cup ice cream mix.
Put sandwich bag into gallon bag. Wrap in a towel and shake for 5 to 10 minutes or until ice cream is firm.

title: pineapple ginger chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper; brown in margarine. Drain off excess fat.
Gradually add flour to barbecue sauce, mixing until well blended.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add juice, honey, ginger and pepper sauce to barbecue sauce mixture. Pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add pineapple. Simmer uncovered 10 minutes or until tender.
Arrange chicken and pineapple on rice.
Serve with sauce; sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into an ungreased pie pan. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: wednesday's chili
directions: In a medium skillet, heat oil and brown the beef in it over medium heat.
Crumble beef with fork until pink color disappears; set aside.
Puree onion soup in a blender and pour over beef, stirring over medium heat until it has the consistency of rice, breaking it up with fork as it heats.
Stir in spices; add drained beans, tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Stir until combined.
Heat over low heat at least 20 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef;
drain.
Add chili mix, tomato juice and beans; simmer about 30
minutes.
Add
flour
to water and add to chili.
Mix
well.	Add cooked spaghetti.
Simmer about 10 minutes more.
This is really better if made the day before you plan to serve it.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and wine or broth; stir well.
Spoon evenly over chicken; sprinkle with stuffing mix. Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Yields 8 servings.

title: clam fritters
directions: Drain clams, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, paprika and pepper.
Stir in clams and onion. Combine clam juice and egg.
Add to flour mixture and stir until well blended.
Heat Crisco to 365° in deep saucepan.
(Do not use basket.)
Drop level tablespoons of clam mixture into hot Crisco. Fry several at a time for 3 1/2 minutes.
Drain on paper towels. Serve with tartar sauce.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in a dry container.
Use about 3 teaspoons of mixture per one cup of hot water.

title: black beauty salad(this is a pretty salad.)
directions: Drain cherry juice and save.
Dissolve jello in hot water. Add the drained cherry juice and lemon juice.
Cool until mixture begins to thicken, then add cherries, celery and nuts.
Put in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
When firm, cut into squares and set each square on a lettuce leaf.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk; add meat, eggs, onion and seasonings.
Mix well.
Form in individual loaves; place in greased pan.
Cover with Piquant Sauce.

title: date-nut krispies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients stirring until thickened.
Remove from stove and stir in Rice Krispies and nuts.
Sprinkle powdered sugar in bottom of cookie sheet.
Spread mixture and sift more powdered sugar on top.
Cut into 1 1/2 inch squares and store in closed container.
Will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: hamburger stuffing casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet. Make stuffing as directed on box. Heat soup and half a can of milk in saucepan. Layer ingredients in casserole dish, hamburger, then stuffing, then the soup on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Peel and cut eggplant into cubes.
Cook in salted water until tender.
Add margarine, cheese, onion, crackers, salt, eggs and milk.
Put in greased baking dish and bake at 350° until brown.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Blend well.
Add bananas and nuts.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to banana mixture.
Add sour cream to mixture.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: In a mixer, cream shortening and sugar.
Add hot water.
Add yeast that has been dissolved in the cold water; add egg and flour.
Grease top of dough.
Store in refrigerator overnight. Make into Parker House or cloverleaf rolls.
Allow to double in size before baking.
Bake in a 375° or 400° oven for 15 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Boil Coke
and mix with jello.
Add juice of pineapples and cherries;
add
fruit.
Put in refrigerator until jelled. Good with all types of meat.

title: party pink fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir and serve over ice.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and butter and pat into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.
Cool and refrigerate for 20 minutes (before you put the filling on top).
Mix together cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons milk and spread on rust. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Spread Cool Whip over layer and last a can of blueberry filling.
Swirl on top and refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry icebox pie
directions: Stir gelatin until dissolved with water; add strawberries and 1/2 cup whipping cream; mix thoroughly. Pour into pie shell; chill until firm.
Whip remaining cream; spread whipped cream evenly over pie.
Yields 6 servings.

title: deep sea mold
directions: Sprinkle gelatine over water in saucepan.
Place over low heat; stir constantly until gelatine dissolves (3 to 5 minutes).
Remove from heat; cool.
Combine sour cream and salad dressing; stir in dill, salt, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, onion and Tabasco. Blend in cooled gelatine mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Turn into 12-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Serves 12.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix together crackers and melted butter.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place 2/3 of crackers in bottom.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
Layer chicken, broccoli (uncooked), soup mixture and cheese.
Top with rest of crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly and brown.

title: day before lasagna
directions: Pour small amount spaghetti sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with uncooked lasagna noodles.
Combine all of the following: cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes, oregano, eggs, salt and pepper.
Put half of cottage cheese mixture on top of noodles.
Combine browned meat with spaghetti sauce and pour half over cottage cheese mixture.
Repeat layers:
noodles, cottage cheese, spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella.
(Top layer of Mozzarella goes on about 15 minutes before done.)
Make day ahead and refrigerate.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Do not use mixer.
Mix together eggs, nuts, sugar, flour, baking soda and crushed pineapple, including juice.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until cake tests done.
Cool in pan.
Cover with topping.

title: oatmeal sticks
directions: Go to Aldi's and buy a great big box of popsicles.
Take to Mamaw's house for her to keep in the freezer.
Freeze overnight. Run to Mamaw & ask for a TA TA TOO.
(If she is too busy, run to Papaw because you know you can get him to do anything.)
Have either one cut top open & enjoy.

title: confetti rice
directions: Bring 3 cups water and salt to a boil in a medium saucepan; add rice.
Cover; reduce heat to medium and let simmer for 25 minutes or until all water is absorbed.
Place in separate bowl and set aside.
In same saucepan, combine carrots, peas, corn and 1 cup water.
Steam for 8 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are crisp but tender.
Drain.
Add reserved rice, almonds, chickpeas, cranberries, oil and salad dressing mix.
Heat through for 1 minute.
Spoon into a serving bowl and serve.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: shake and bake biscuits
directions: Place in a large plastic bowl with lid the flour and Crisco. Shake until it looks like cornmeal.
Add buttermilk; shake until mixture is mixed well.
Place mixture on floured pastry sheet. Roll out and cut into biscuits.
Place on ungreased pan.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Heat margarine in an 8-inch skillet over low heat until melted.
Cook and stir onion in margarine until onion is brown. Discard onion.
Stir flour into margarine.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until flour is deep brown; remove from heat. Stir in broth and mushrooms.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in salt and pepper and if desired, a few drops of Worcestershire sauce.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Pour into crust.
Chill until firm.

title: mary jane squires' mexican creme
directions: Make candy on a sunny day.

title: blueberry gelatin salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in blueberries.
Pour into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish; chill until set. In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add vanilla and sour cream; mix well.
Spread over the gelatin layer. Sprinkle with pecans.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: grandma ruth's gingerbread
directions: Blend sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in molasses.
Add flour, ginger, salt, baking soda and cinnamon, alternating with buttermilk.
Beat well.
Spread in a greased, floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: three minute pie
directions: Combine melted butter or margarine, sugar, coconut, eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine cottage cheese, sugar onion, 1 tablespoon butter, dill seed, salt and soda.
Add egg and part of flour and yeast.
Add rest of flour.
Beat well.
Place in greased bread pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Beat flour, sugar and eggs with spoon.
Add pineapple with juice.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Stir melted butter into bread cubes until bread is soaked with butter.
Sprinkle bread cubes on top of casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8. Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients.
Cook rice separately and add to chicken mixture.
Bake, covered, for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cajun shrimp squash casserole
directions: In large black cast-iron skillet, saute onion in margarine until clear.
Add squash, sugar and spices.
Cover skillet and simmer on low fire until squash begins to wilt.
Add raw shrimp. Cover and simmer until shrimp turn red and curl.
Do not overcook. Serve as is or if you a real Cajun, serve over steamed rice.

title: snow peas oriental(low calorie)
directions: Coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Add oil and place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add snow peas and carrots.
Saute 2 minutes.
Add water chestnuts and broth.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Combine soy sauce and cornstarch, stirring until cornstarch dissolves.
Add to vegetable mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
4 servings (about 51 calories per 1/2 cup serving).

title: broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches. Rinse broccoli under running cold water to thaw; drain thoroughly. Mix broccoli, 2 cups of the cheese and the onion in plate.
Beat eggs, milk, baking mix, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean (about 35 to 40 minutes).
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake just until cheese melts (1 to 2 minutes).
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Let stand until dissolved.
Stir well into large bowl with cover.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Cover and let stand for 3 days at room temperature.
Stir daily.

title: coney's
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix together hamburger, chili sauce, beans, onion and cooked noodles.
Season with chili powder and pepper.
Cook hot dogs while mixture heats.

title: curry dip
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients until smooth and creamy. Use as a dressing or dip for fresh vegetables; as a sauce for fish or chicken; as a salad dressing; or as a sandwich spread.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large bowl.
Add all ingredients. Mix thoroughly.
Add egg and vanilla.
Pour in greased square cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve topped with applesauce.

title: eleanor's apple nut squares
directions: Break eggs into mixing bowl and beat until foamy.
Add sugar and beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add vanilla.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon and blend in mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares and serve with whipped topping, whipped cream or ice cream.
Top with maraschino cherry.

title: sugar-free baked vanilla custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, thoroughly blend the eggs, Splenda and salt. Then gradually add the cream and vanilla extract. In a baking dish, at least 2-inches deep, place 6 custard cups. Pour the custard mixture evenly among the custard cups and fill the baking dish with hot water, about 1-inch high. Bake for 1 hour. Chill in refrigerator for at least 2 hours before serving. Serves 6.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350° degrees. Place a layer of tomatoes in bottom of pie crust. In a bowl, combine sugar, salt, lemon zest, cinnamon, lemon juice, and butter; blend. Pour 1/3 of the mixture over the tomatoes in the pie shell. Make another layer of tomatoes and repeat. Roll out the second pie crust and place over the filling. Pinch edges together and make several slits in the top. Bake for 45 minutes, or until it is bubbling and golden brown.

title: chow-chow
directions: Chop cabbage, red and green pepper and onions separately. Drain off all water.
Mix together. Add vinegar, sugar and salt. Boil for 15 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: easy glazed carrots
directions: Steam carrots for 10 to 15 minutes over boiling water.
In a mixing bowl, combine drained carrots with butter, marmalade and pecans. Serve while hot. Yield: 4 servings.

title: crustless spinach pie
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Spoon into a greased pie plate or quiche dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Note:
Can add onions, celery, or water chestnuts, if desired.

title: coconut and sour cream dream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box, making 2 layers.
Split both layers horizontally after baked.
Blend together the sugar, sour cream and coconut, then chill.
Spread all but 1 cup of sour cream mixture between the 4 layers.
Blend remaining mixture of whipped cream and spread on top and side of cake.
Seal in airtight container; refrigerate 3 days before serving.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 servings.

title: quick and easy dressing
directions: Mix
all
ingredients thoroughly.
Stuff 12 to 14 pound turkey.
Bake in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together all but last two ingredients.
Crumble crackers on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread coffee cake
directions: Cut rolls into 3 pieces each while frozen.
Melt oleo; add sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over rolls and mix.
Pour into ungreased Bundt pan.
Let rise 1 or 1 1/2 hours.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry banana pie
directions: Bake and cool crust.
Slice a layer of bananas in bottom of pie crust.
Spread 1/2 can blueberry pie filling over bananas. Repeat layers.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
It is done!

title: farina dumplings
directions: Bring milk, salt and farina to a slow boil and stir until thick.
Cool.
Add butter, egg and nutmeg.
Drop in small amounts from a wet spoon into boiling soup.
Simmer for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: strawberry melon slaw
directions: Toss main ingredients and fruit in large bowl.
Mix salad dressing, honey and poppy seed together.
Mix dressing with main ingredients.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion.
Blend together.
Simmer until a good consistency.
Can be refrigerated for later use.

title: flank steak with herb stuffing
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in butter in medium heat until golden.
In bowl combine parsley, crumbs, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper and egg then mix in onions and mushrooms.

With sharp knife score surface of meat on both sides in diamond pattern. Place mushroom mixture lengthwise down center of steak, then bring both ends together on top; fasten with string at 1 in. intervals or use skewers.
Add 2 tbsp shortening to skillet, brown steak well on all sides on medium heat.
Place in roasting pan and add bouillon; cover and bake at 350 for 1/2 hours or until meat is fork tender. Remove meat to heated platter.
Remove string or skewers then cut into pieces.
Thicken pan juices, if desired.
Serve with meat.

title: chinese pork roast tenderloin
directions: Stir together all ingredients, except meat.
Pour over meat and marinate, turning occasionally, for at least 4 hours (preferably overnight).
Lift meat from marinade and place on a rack in a roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer into the thickest portion of one of the pieces.
Roast, uncovered, in a 425° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until the temperature reaches 170° on the meat thermometer.
Slice thinly across tenderloin.
Serve with hot mustard, ketchup and toasted sesame seed.

title: chicken broccoli spears
directions: Cut up frozen broccoli or fresh broccoli into small bite size pieces.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Cut up cooked chicken and place over broccoli in casserole.
Mix cream of chicken and mayonnaise - spread over chicken and broccoli. Sprinkle with cheese then breadcrumbs.
Bake at 375° for about 3/4
hour until done.
6 servings.

title: baked chicken
directions: Butter a 9 x 13 baking dish. Sprinkle dried beef on bottom of pan. Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of bacon. If necessary, hold together with a toothpick.
Place on top of dried beef.

title: orange pie
directions: Let orange juice thaw, then mix in Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix this real good, then pour mixture into graham cracker crust.
Put in refrigerator and let set for 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: scalloped broccoli
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli and noodles according to directions.
Drain.
In a
greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, blend soup and milk together until smooth.
Stir in broccoli, noodles, pepper and mushrooms. Combine crumbs with melted butter. Sprinkle over broccoli mixture. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Melt oleo in pan; remove from heat.
Blend in sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder.
Stir well. Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: eckrich sausage and mostaccioli
directions: Cut sausage into 3/4-inch pieces.
In medium saucepan (3-quart), saute sausage, onion and green pepper about 3 minutes or until sausage is lightly browned.
Drain well.
Stir in spaghetti sauce. Bring to boiling and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Top hot cooked pasta with sauce and Parmesan cheese.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix food coloring and cocoa and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and coloring paste mix and beat 10 minutes. Add buttermilk, then slowly add flour, salt and vanilla.
Mix in by hand soda and vinegar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in greased and floured pans.

title: microwave beef jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a large bowl.
Add meat strips; let set overnight.
Drain and put on paper towels.
Lay on microwave bacon tray.
Cook on High 3 to 4 minutes.
Turn and cook 3 to 4 minutes.

title: italian fried chicken
directions: In paper or plastic bag, combine all ingredients, except chicken.
Add chicken, a few pieces at a time and shake to coat evenly.
Heat oil in 12-inch skillet.
Place meaty pieces toward center and remaining pieces around the edges.
Cook, uncovered, over medium-low heat for 50 to 55 minutes or until chicken is tender, turning occasionally.
Drain on paper towels.

title: chinese dumplings
directions: Heat, in 1 inch boiling water, heat cabbage to boiling.
Cook cabbage 1 minute; drain.
Immediately run cold water over cabbage to cool.
With hands, squeeze as much water out of cabbage as possible.
Finely chop cabbage.

title: turkey vegetable soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add onions and saute until translucent, about 10 minutes.
Add broth, potatoes, carrots, celery, parsley and sage and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to simmer; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add turkey, half and half and spinach.
Cover and continue simmering until heated through, about 7 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: banana peanut butter sandwich
directions: Spread peanut butter on 2 slices of bread. Arrange banana slices over peanut butter. Top with remaining slice of raisin bread. Enjoy!

title: easy chicken and biscuits
directions: Cook together chicken, soup and peas.
Bake up biscuits. Serve chicken mix over biscuits.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Cut up (dice) onions.
Add all ingredients to 2 cups of water. Cook on medium for 45 to 60 minutes.
Ready to eat.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle brand milk together.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well. Chill well before serving.

title: carrot bread
directions: Sift
dry
ingredients	together except sugar.	Combine eggs, sugar
and	oil
and mix well.
Add carrots, raisins and flour mixture and blend lightly.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and cut into chunks, saving broth.
Cook vermicelli and drain.
Cook onion, celery and green pepper in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and slowly add milk and broth; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add soups, pimento, olives (cut in half) and boned chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix with pasta and place in 3-qt. flat casserole. Top with cheese and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
This is enough for 2 casseroles.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and onion. Drain grease. Add rest of ingredients. Simmer 20-30 minutes.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into mixing bowl; add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin and spices; mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Garnish.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Cook shredded cabbage in some boiling salted water for 7 minutes.
Drain, cover and set aside.
Fry bacon in pan until crisp.
Remove bacon.
Add brown sugar and flour to bacon drippings and blend well.
Add water, vinegar, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook until thick.
Add cooked bacon.
Mix all with cabbage and heat through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Follow directions on pudding box for making pudding.
Fold in the Eagle Brand milk and 8 ounces Cool Whip; blend thoroughly.
In a 13 x 9-inch (or larger) pan, put a layer of vanilla wafers and put 2 1/2 sliced bananas on top of wafers.
Pour half of the pudding mixture over the bananas.
Repeat for second layer and top with remaining 8 ounces of Cool Whip.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour, baking powder and salt with pastry blender until mixture resembles fine crumbs. Stir in just enough milk so dough leaves side of bowl and rounds up into a ball.
(Too much milk makes a sticky dough; not enough makes the biscuits dry.)
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface. Knead lightly 10 times.
Roll 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut with a floured biscuit cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet about 1 inch apart for crusty sides, touching sides will be soft.
Tops can be brushed with melted butter.
Bake until golden brown, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet.
A two-inch cutter makes about one dozen biscuits.
The larger your cutter, the bigger the biscuit and the fewer also.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in medium size casserole dish. Mix together egg, cornbread mix, 1 can whole corn (partially drained), creamed corn and cheese. Pour into dish with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pie meringue
directions: Beat eggs, salt and vanilla until stiff.
Add sugar slowly, while still beating.

title: cabbage and shrimp omelet
directions: Cut up cabbage and add to onion, bell pepper and chili peppers wilting in buttered skillet, about 10 minutes.
Make an omelet with eggs and cream.
Season with salt and drop into buttered skillet.
Shake around until cooked.
Slightly scramble across top with fork until it begins to harden.
Pour cabbage and shrimp over omelet.
Fold and serve.

title: six-week bran muffins mix
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, flour, baking soda, sugar, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl with airtight cover. Blend eggs, oil and buttermilk and mix well. Add this to large bowl and mix well. Fold in fruit cocktail. Do not use batter until it has been refrigerated for 24 hours.

title: make ahead potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets in boiling water.
Cook, peel and dice.
Add salt, celery, pickles, eggs and onion.
Add mustard and salad dressing; mix just enough to blend.
Pickle juice may be added if desired.
Salad is better if allowed to stand overnight for flavors to blend.
Garnish with olives at serving time.

title: apple pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle chopped pecans on bottom of pie shell.
Combine apples, flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Turn into pie shell; spread with topping.

title: meat sauce(spaghetti sauce)
directions: This recipe is excellent doubled and tripled and frozen in meal-size or recipe size containers (such as: lasagna or any pasta, bean or rice recipe).

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix together as directed on box.
Pour half of batter into cake pan and put in the oven.
Let bake about 15 minutes. While that's baking, melt caramels with 1/3 cup Pet milk.
Take cake out of oven; pour caramels over the top of cake.
Put pecans over top of caramels, then pour rest of cake batter on top of pecans.
Put back in oven about 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and seasoning mix well; cool and toss with remaining ingredients.
Wait until ready to serve before adding Doritos so they will not be soggy.

title: christmas party punch
directions: In a large bowl, combine the strawberries, sugar and 1 bottle of the cranberry juice. Cover and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour. Strain the mixture through a fine sieve into a punch bowl, pushing the fruit through with the back of a wooden spoon. Stir in the lemonade concentrate. Add the remaining bottle of cranberry juice and the sparkling water. Before serving, add ice.

title: rabbit salmi
directions: Place rabbit in baking pan and add onion, celery and bay leaves.
Brush with oil and roast in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Remove meat from pan, add fat and flour and stir until sauce becomes a rich brown.
Add hot water, stir well.
When smooth, add salt, Worcestershire sauce, capers and olives.
Replace meat, cover tightly and roast in 350° oven for an additional 80 minutes or until tender.

title: fool's toffee
directions: In small saucepan, over medium high heat, blend butter and brown sugar.
Heat to boiling and boil for 4 minutes.
Cover 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan with foil and butter lightly.
Place single layer of saltine crackers on foil close together.
Pour butter mixture over crackers spreading evenly.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Immediately sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Allow to soften.
Spread evenly over cooked crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate until cool.
Break into pieces and store in tin container in refrigerator.
Can be kept in refrigerator for 1 to 2 weeks.

title: moussaka(easy greek casserole)
directions: Dip eggplant in slightly beaten egg and then in bread crumbs. Brown in olive oil.
Set aside.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake 30 minutes.

title: sausage dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and keep warm in a crock-pot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix in large bowl sugar and salt with 3 cups very warm water. Melt shortening.
Put into water mixture.
Let cool, then take mixer and blend in about 3 cups of flour, then put in eggs and yeast.
Blend good, then put in rest of the flour.
Take hands to blend.
Put about 1 cup flour on table and work in.
Put in greased bowl; let sit until double.
Punch down.
Put 1/4 cup oil and put in pans to rise again until top of pans.
Bake at 400° until brown (don't preheat oven).

title: glamorous cabbage casserole
directions: Microwave cabbage (grated) 10 minutes in 1/4 cup water. Combine soup and cream cheese (softened) in a small bowl.
Mix well and stir into cabbage.
Microwave 5 minutes, then sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Cheese will melt from heat of casserole.

title: chewy fudge squares
directions: Grease
x
13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together
cake mix, eggs and butter in bowl until well blended (mixture
will
be
stiff).
Stir in marshmallows and walnuts. Spread mixture
in pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until set in center.
Cool and cut in squares.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: vegetable chili
directions: Heat oil in a heavy bottom pot; saute onions, pepper and garlic with oregano, cumin, thyme, coriander and chili powder.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, celery, carrots and corn.
Simmer, covered, for 40 minutes; then add beans and cook for 15 minutes.
Add salt, hot pepper, liquid and vinegar to taste.
Before serving, you may combine some cabbage and cilantro to serve as a garnish.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add egg to make crumbs.
Put apples in buttered casserole dish.
Spread crumbs over apples.
Pour butter over and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: roast("crock-pot")
directions: Put all in crock-pot and cook on low all day or night.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; cut in shortening until well mixed and add buttermilk or milk, stirring quickly until a very soft dough.

title: fresh vegetable soup(lo-cal)
directions: Chop vegetables as fine as desired.
(A blender may be used to chop vegetables, adding enough water to chop well.)
Place chopped vegetables in a 4-quart kettle and add enough water to make 6 cups.
Add bouillon cubes, butter and chives.
Bring to boil. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 cups, 50 calories per cup.

title: plum pudding
directions: Mix ingredients well, not too stiff.
Steam for 4 hours. Grease cans with butter.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add unbeaten eggs 1 at a time and beat thoroughly.
Add flour, salt, mace and vanilla.
Mix carefully.
Bake in tube pan 50 to 60 minutes at 325°.
Grease bottom of pan.

title: layered pie
directions: Mix and flatten first 3 ingredient in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and one cup Cool Whip.
Put over crust.
Mix chocolate pudding with 2 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Mix vanilla pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over chocolate layer.
Top with additional Cool Whip.
Shaved chocolate can be added over Cool Whip topping.
Refrigerate.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine crumbs, 2 tablespoons Parmesan, oregano, garlic and pepper; roll chicken in mixture.
Arrange in 2-quart shallow 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn chicken; bake 20 minutes more.
Meanwhile, blend soup and milk; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika and remaining Parmesan. Bake 20 minutes more or until done.
Arrange chicken on platter. Stir sauce; pour over chicken.
Makes 4 servings.
Yummy!

title: spicy rice
directions: In a large skillet, cook celery and onions in butter until tender-crisp.
Stir in seasonings, rice and raisins.
Heat thoroughly.
Stir in apple; remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Makes 6 servings.

title: philadelphia cream cheese pie
directions: Mix with a spoon or electric whipper the cream cheese, Cool Whip, powdered sugar and water.
Mix until creamy.
Pour the filling into the graham crust.
Put either cherry or blueberry filling spread on top.
Refrigerate.

title: squash dressing
directions: Crumble the bread.
(Can use some corn bread and some other kind.)
You can change to 3 cups breads and 3 cups squash.
Cook, mash and drain the squash.
Melt the margarine.
Add everything together.
Put in a Pam sprayed dish.
Cook as you would chicken dressing.
I cook mine about 30 minutes at 400°.

title: cream jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add ice cream.
Stir until no lumps remain.
Chill and serve.
For added elegance, put Jell-O in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill.
Make 2 more layers of different colors, chilling between each layer.

title: quick dinner rolls("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Dissolve yeast, sugar and salt in water.
Beat well.
Add egg, flour and shortening.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Stir down raised dough.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin tins.
Let rise again. Bake 15 to 20 more minutes in 400° oven.
(Raisins may be added, plus 2 more tablespoons sugar.)

title: fudge chip cream cake
directions: In a mixer bowl, whip cream cheese with sugar until light and fluffy; blend in vanilla. Fold in whipped cream. Arrange cookies around sides and bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan or cake pan with removable bottom. Spread half of filling in pan. Arrange fruit on filling. Top with remaining filling; chill until set. If desired, garnish with whole strawberries.

title: apple butter
directions: Heat to boiling and pour in small jars and seal.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat cream cheese and butter.
Mix in 1/2 cake mix, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in rest of cake mix and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hellmann's chocolate sensation
directions: Grease and flour 9-inch layer cake pans.
In a large bowl with mixer at low speed, blend all ingredients for 30 seconds.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes or until cake springs back at a light touch.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and place on a wire rack to cool.
Frost, if desired.

title: salsa halibut
directions: Cube halibut into bite size chunks. Pour salsa over halibut and mix well. Marinate for 10 minutes. Make a foil boat and place the halibut into boat. Grill until halibut is cooked evenly, carefully stirring occasionally.

title: sprouts and carrots with orange
directions: Trim the bottom of the Brussels sprouts and pull off any withered leaves.
Cook them in boiling, salted water until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Slice carrots and cook in boiling, salted water until tender, 8 to 10 minutes.
Grate 1 teaspoon of the colored zest from orange.
Squeeze 3 tablespoons juice.
In a large frying pan, heat butter and orange juice over medium heat until foamy.
Add carrots, sprouts, zest, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper and stir to mix well.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are hot and well coated, about 2 minutes.

title: turkey stir-fry
directions: In a large skillet, stir-fry turkey in oil over medium-high heat until no longer pink (5 to 6 minutes).
Remove turkey and keep warm.
Stir-fry onion, carrots, green pepper and mushrooms until crisp and tender (5 minutes).
In a small bowl, combine broth, cornstarch, soy sauce and ginger.
Add to skillet.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Return turkey to skillet with pea pods. Cook and stir until heated through.
If desired, serve over rice and top with cashews.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil, vanilla, zucchini and pineapple and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: dirty rice
directions: Heat beef broth and water.
Put all ingredients in a casserole with a tight fitting lid.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave nacho dip
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Place beef, beans and relish into microwave dish and heat thoroughly.
Add cubed Velveeta cheese. Heat until cheese melts.
Stir.
Top with Mozzarella.
Heat just until Mozzarella melts.
Serve with chips.

title: becky's mock key lime pie
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together and pour into crust.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Garnish and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dill crackers
directions: Place crackers in roasting pan. Mix oil, dressing mix and dill weed. Pour over crackers.
Bake 5 minutes at 325°, stir. Bake 5 minutes more.

title: maple nut cake
directions: Combine shortening, salt, vanilla and maple extract.
Blend. Add sugar gradually and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Sift flour and baking powder together 3 times.
Add small amount of flour to creamed mixture, alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Pour into two 8-inch greased cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes (about).

title: sweet potato fritters
directions: In a large deep skillet, heat 1-inch of oil to 350° on deep-fat thermometer.
Diagonally slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick. In medium-sized bowl, mix together flour, cornmeal, water, green onions, 2 teaspoons salt, mace and pepper until smooth.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil in wok or skillet.
Stir in onion and cook 2 minutes. Add peas.
Stir in rice.
Coat with oil and peas.
Stir 2 to 3 minutes. Pour beaten eggs over rice.
Cook, stirring often, until eggs are set.
Mix soy sauce and sugar.
Add and stir.
Season to taste.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: After cutting the bacon into small pieces, fry crisp and drain on paper towel.
Cut lettuce into pieces; add the onions and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add the vinegar to the bacon fat and bring to a boil.
Pour the hot vinegar over lettuce, tossing thoroughly.
Sprinkle bacon on top and serve.

title: double lemon salad
directions: Mix jello with water.
Add pie filling.
Stir in pineapple. Pour into 9 x 13 dish.
Mix sour cream and powdered sugar.	Put on top of jello mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: salmon mouse
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Place over hot water, stirring until dissolved (double boiler).

title: easy cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch casserole, melt butter in oven.
Combine flour, sugar and milk.
Pour mixture over melted butter; do not stir.
Cover mixture with fruit, do not stir.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until browned.
Serve warm with milk.

title: linguine with spicy eggplant sauce
directions: Remove sausage meat from casings.
In a 4-quart saucepan over medium-high heat in hot olive oil, cook sausage meat until browned, stirring frequently to break up sausage with slotted spoon.
Remove sausage to bowl.

title: creamy taco
directions: Serve over taco chips with lettuce and tomato
on top.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo and shortening; add brown sugar, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Sift and add the flour, baking powder and baking soda. Add oatmeal, chocolate chips, pecans, Rice Krispies and coconut. Use 1/4 measured cup per cookie or ice cream scoop.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet, 6 to a sheet.
Cook 15 minutes at 350°. Let cool 5 minutes before removing from sheet.
Makes 30 to 40 cookies.

title: micro pralines
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in 8 cup measuring cup.
Cook in microwave on High for 13 minutes, then add last 2 ingredients. Beat candy mixture until creamy.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper or buttered lightly aluminum foil.

title: pork chops, mushroom sauce
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet. Add sliced mushrooms and soup. Simmer 30 minutes. To thicken sauce, add 1 tablespoon flour.

title: easter bread
directions: Cream butter and add liquids.
Add sugar.
Add yeast.
Combine dry ingredients and fold into liquid.
Put in large oiled pan.
Let rise about 8 hours, until triples in size, in warm place.

title: chicken jerusalem
directions: Flour chicken with 1/2 cup flour, salt, pepper and paprika. Brown chicken in butter; remove.

title: sweet and sour stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix meat with onion, egg, rice, salt and pepper.
Place in 13 x
9-inch baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce, currants and brown sugar
over
this
(mix
these 3 ingredients together). Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chunk o'cheese bread
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine water, cornmeal and salt. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in molasses and butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl. Blend in cornmeal mixture.
Gradually add flour to form stiff dough.
Knead until smooth and satiny.
Place in greased bowl. Let rise until doubled.
Grease two squares of foil and line two 8 or 9-inch round pans.
Place dough on surface sprinkled with cornmeal.
Work cheese into dough 1/4 at a time, until cubes are evenly distributed.
Divide; shape into loaves, covering cheese cubes.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: nancy's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix everything, except flour and chips first, then flour and finally stir in chips.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen small or about 3 dozen large cookies.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook onion, garlic and oregano in oil.
Stir in spinach; cook until tender and liquid evaporates.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup, cottage cheese and egg; set aside.
Arrange 3 lasagna noodles over sauce; spread with 1/2 of spinach filling.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of Mozzarella cheese.
Arrange 3 more noodles over cheese; spread remaining filling.
Sprinkle with another 1/3 of the Mozzarella cheese.
Top with remaining 3 noodles and remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle rest of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: peach salad mold
directions: Simmer cloves and cinnamon in water 1/2 hour.
Remove whole cloves.
Dissolve gelatin in the spiced water; allow to cool.
Add vinegar after mixture has cooled.
Slice one peach half into each of six individual molds.
Pour gelatin mixture into molds; allow to set.
Unmold on lettuce leaf; garnish with a sprig of parsley. Yield:
6 servings.
Carbohydrate 6 g, protein 0 g, fat 0 g, calories 24.
One serving = 1/2 fruit exchange.

title: chinese ting-a-ling
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and add nuts and noodles.
Spoon on buttered wax paper.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Boil green beans for 20 minutes with garlic.
Remove garlic and drain.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Slowly stir in flour to make paste, then gradually add milk to make a cream sauce.
Next, add other ingredients, cooking and stirring until cheese melts.
Mix with green beans and spoon into lightly greased casserole.
Bread crumbs may be sprinkled on top.
Bake in moderate oven (300°) about 30 minutes.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Chop onion and celery and cook until tender.
Cook sausage until done.
Drain off grease.
Mix rice, cream of mushroom soup and cream of chicken soup together, then add to sausage mixture. Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar, molasses and egg.
Mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and cloves and add to molasses mixture, stirring until smooth.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and dip one side into sugar.
Place 2 inches apart, sugar side up on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
(Tops will crack.)
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in heated orange juice.
Add buttermilk; mix well.
Add mandarin oranges and let congeal.

title: fish parmesan
directions: Wash and dry fish.
Arrange fish in a 12 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Dot with butter.
Cover with waxed paper; microwave at High 2 minutes.
Blend Parmesan cheese, mayonnaise and onions.
Spread cheese mixture over fish.
Cover with waxed paper; microwave at High 2 to 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti following directions on package; drain. Add other ingredients. Stir well. Chill 24 hours before serving.

title: egg custard
directions: Makes its own crust.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk.
Add cheese, green pepper, pimento, pepper and 1/2 cup of the crumbs.
Pour into a shallow casserole; top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: ma's pecan pie
directions: Cook until thick as instant pudding, all ingredients except pecans.
Have pecans finely chopped.
Then layer mixture with pecans.
When pie crust is filled, bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.

title: scrambled omelet
directions: Stir soup until smooth.
Blend in eggs and pepper.
In skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet and crumble into bowl.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Cook green pepper and onion in drippings until tender.
Pour in egg mixture and scramble.
Sprinkle bacon on eggs when done.
You can also add shredded cheese to hot scrambled eggs, if you like.

title: gala fruit punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine concentrates, juices and water. Stir well. Stir in strawberries, ginger ale and club soda. Serve immediately. Yields 25 (1 cup) servings.

title: mom's peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, and salt.
Cream crisco, sugar and peanut butter.
Add flour mixture.
Moisten with water and vanilla.
Drip by spoonfulls on ungreased pan.
Press flat with a fork dipped in water.
Bake at 350° degrees until brown about 15 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Melt oil and butter in 9 x 13-inch dish at 400°.
Remove and coat chicken with melted oil and butter and place skin side up. Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove chicken from oven and drain off juice.
Place broccoli over the chicken; season with salt.
Then mix and pour over chicken and broccoli the soup, mushrooms, water, Worcestershire and thyme.
Place back in oven and cook 30 to 45 minutes more or until done.
Serve with white rice.

title: lye soap
directions: Dissolve the lye in the hot water; let cool, then pour lye solution in a slow, easy stream into melted fat, stirring constantly.
Continue stirring until cool.
Pour into boxes that have been dipped in cold water.
Cut into desired size of squares when cold and set.
You can add perfumed bath oil, if so desired.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Add salad dressing and beat well.
Add pimentos.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cranberry refresher
directions: Pour all ingredients (except sherbet) into chilled bowl. Stir.
Pour into tall glasses.
Top with a scoop of sherbet. Serves 10.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove bones and cut into bite-sized pieces. Cook spaghetti in the broth.
Do not drain.
Saute onion, garlic, celery and pepper in the butter.
Remove from heat.
Add soups and pimento.
Combine spaghetti, chicken and soup mixture along with the cheese. Place in a greased 2 or 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until cheese is melted and casserole is bubbling hot.
Serves 18 to 20 and freezes well.

title: taco salad
directions: Chop lettuce, tomatoes, onions and olives; keep separate.
Mix mayonnaise and salsa.
Crumble taco chips.
Put each ingredient in separate bowl.
To serve, top salad ingredients with salsa mix and crumbled chips.

title: mexicorn cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 13 x 9 pan.
Stir baking mix, cornmeal, sugar, salt, milk, oil and eggs in medium bowl until moistened.
Stir in cheese, corn and peppers.
Pour into pan. Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 16 servings.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemon juice.
Add cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Blend in pineapple.
Pour into pie crusts and chill.
Slice bananas over top before serving.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 400° until brown on top.

title: bread sticks
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Let stand a few minutes. Blend remaining ingredients. (Add 1/2 cup more flour if dough is too sticky.) Let rise 1 hour, covered, in warm place. Roll dough on floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut into strips 1/2-inch wide and 5-inches long. Melt 4 tablespoons margarine. Dip strips in margarine. Put on cookie sheet and twist. Let rise 20 minutes. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: spinach pesto
directions: Puree first 10 ingredients in blender or processor until smooth.
Set aside.
Bring water to boil in large pot.
Add oil and salt.
Add pasta and cook over medium heat until al dente. Strain through colander, reserving 1/3 cup of liquid.
Blend hot liquid into puree and toss with pasta.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Bring to hard boil.
Turn off heat; stir in 1/2 cup peanut butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir in 3 cups oatmeal.
Put in greased pan and cool.

title: sour cream potato pancakes
directions: Peel potatoes, grate and drain.
Beat eggs well and mix with the rest of the ingredients.
Brown on both sides.
Serve hot. Serves 4.

title: picadillo
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Add tomatoes, vinegar, cinnamon, chili powder, salt, raisins and optional ingredients. Simmer with cover for 45 to 60 minutes.
Stir in slivered almonds. Serve with tortilla chips or wrap in flour tortillas.
Can also serve with shredded cheese and lettuce.

title: dixie's breakfast
directions: Saute sausage and drain. Beat eggs with milk and salt.
Layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour eggs on top. Refrigerate overnight. Bake in
a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: sundae cake
directions: Bake cake by directions.
After cake is done, punch holes with fork all over while still hot.
Pour Eagle Brand milk all over. Pour chocolate syrup over cake and let cool.
After cake has cooled completely, spread Cool Whip all over.
Sprinkle with nuts and if you like, drizzle with remainder of chocolate syrup.
Keep in refrigerator until serving.
Bake in oblong pan.

title: rice soup with lemon
directions: Add broth and water to 5-quart pot; bring to a boil.
Add rice, onions, parsley and lemon rind.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes, until rice is done.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice.
Makes 4 servings.
Lo-cal and low-fat; about 185 calories.

title: layered salad
directions: Arrange in layers, broken lettuce, broken cauliflower, onion, bacon and half of mayonnaise.
Repeat for 2nd layer.
Chill. Before serving, cut through with a knife once or twice.
Can be made the day before.

title: apple spice cake
directions: In large bowl, blend ingredients. Spoon evenly into 12-cup Bundt pan.
Follow package directions for baking.
Let stand 10 minutes, turn onto plate.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix meal, flour and cheese.
In separate bowl, mix eggs, corn, onion, oil and peppers.
Combine all ingredients and add buttermilk.
Bake at 450°.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: coleslaw souffle
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Blend in mayonnaise, vinegar and salt.
Chill until practically set.
Beat until fluffy; add vegetables.
Pour into a 1-quart mold.
Chill until firmly set.
Unmold and garnish with sliced radishes and/or cherry tomatoes.

title: judy's butterscotch cheese cake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Microwave margarine and butterscotch morsels until melted.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs and chopped nuts with fork until mixture forms small crumbs.
Reserves 2 cups of mixture for top.
Press remaining mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Using electric mixer, cream butter and sugar.
Add 1 cup flour, then 1 egg.
Continue to alternate a cup of flour with an egg until all flour and all eggs are used.
Add baking powder, flavoring and milk.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated 300° oven 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until cake tests done.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients together.
Grease a long cookie sheet and pour cake mixture in.

title: bacon and tomato shells
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on box.
Add bacon bits and chopped tomato along with cheese sauce.
Stir until well blended. Makes 4 servings.

title: peas, carrots, asparagus casserole
directions: Arrange half the asparagus in a buttered 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine peas, soup, mushrooms, carrots and cheese, blending well.
Spoon half the mixture over asparagus.
Repeat layers. Combine breadcrumbs and oleo and sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until crumbs brown.
Make white sauce of 2 tablespoons oleo, 2 tablespoons flour and 2 cups milk.
When cooked, add 1 cup shredded cheese.

title: big batch raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine Raisin Bran, raisins, flour, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and soda.
Cream oil and sugar; add eggs and buttermilk and mix with dry ingredients until moist.
Mixture will keep stored in refrigerator for 5 weeks.
When ready to bake, spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread(fat-free)
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat 5 minutes.
Pour into two bread pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: In a large sauce pan, combine sugar, butter and milk; bring to a boil for five minutes, stirring occasionally.	Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased 13 by 9 by 2 pan.	Cool to room temperature.
Preparation time 20 minutes.	Great Fudge!

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain.
Crush
soda crackers.
Heat oleo in skillet; add cracker
crumbs and stir.
Add seasoning.
Mix with noodles and bake in casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop beef and green onions.
Combine all ingredients.
Roll in chopped nuts, if desired.
Roll in two balls.

title: beef italian soup
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain.
Brown meat, crumbled; drain off fat.
Saute celery, onion and garlic powder in margarine; drain.
Mix all ingredients together; heat and serve.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Blend together and put in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: russian friendship tea
directions: Mix well.
Use approximately 3 teaspoons of mixture to each cup of boiling water.

title: granny perryman's old timey tea cakes
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar and egg.
Next, add milk, mixing in well.
In a separate bowl, mix baking powder and flour.
Add this combination to the first.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Roll out dough and cut with cookie cutters to form different shapes or roll into small balls and flatten on cookie pan with a fork.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add soup, onion, eggs and mayonnaise. Cover with cheese.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on cheese; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jo's cookies
directions: Cream
sugars,
butter,
eggs
and
vanilla.
Add
dry ingredients, mixing
with
spoon.
Form into long rolls, about 2-inches
in
diameter
and
place
