in refrigerator overnight. Rolls should be formed on wax paper.
If you want to keep them longer in the fridge, use plastic bag to keep them from drying out.
Slice
and
place
on
cookie sheets when ready to bake. Bake at 375° until light brown on low rack.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cut up in cubes, save broth to cook veggies in.
After veggies are cooked until tender add cut up chicken, mushroom and celery soup, salt and pepper to taste.
Add a sprinkle of poultry seasoning.
This freezes well for later use.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Cook first four ingredients (in a large pan) until it comes to a rolling boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add a few drops of green food coloring and a bottle of Certo.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars.

title: country vegetable soup
directions: Melt butter in a deep heavy pot.
Add all the sliced vegetables.
Cover tightly and stew over low heat for 20 minutes. Chop cooked vegetables; add water.
Bring to a boil and simmer 20 minutes.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in a loaf-shaped baking pan, or form by hand into a loaf and place in 2-quart casserole.
Cook on MEDIUM for 12 to 14 minutes.
Let sit 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Let cool.
Crumble 1 layer of cake in a punch bowl.
Add 1/2 pie filling, pineapple, pudding mix, Cool Whip and 1 package of coconut.
Repeat the steps.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix together and let stand at room temperature for 1 1/2 hours.
Pack in freezer-safe containers and freeze.
Thaw before serving.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic about five minutes or until onion is tender in 2 Tbsp. oil in a large saucepan.
Add tomatoes, chilies, chicken broth, pepper, worcestershire sauce, chili powder, cumin and hot sauce and let simmer for 20 minutes.
Combine 4 Tbsp. flour with 1/2 cup water and whisk into soup. Bring back to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add boiled chicken, cut into small cubes.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/3 cup nonfat sour cream, salt & pepper to taste.

title: coconut macaroon pie
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and salt until mixture is lemon-colored.
Add melted butter and flour.
Blend well.
Add milk and fold in 1 cup coconut.
Pour into pie shell, top with remaining coconut.
Bake in slow oven (325°) about 60 minutes.

title: blintzes
directions: In a bowl with a whisk beat milk, flour and oil until smooth. Add eggs one at a time while beating; add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well. heat a heavy 7-inch skillet until drop of water sizzles; brush with oil.
Using large spoon, ladle into pan and tilt around to cover.
Cook until lightly brown; loosen edges and flip over. Cook slightly then flip out onto a rack or wax paper.
Always oil pan before each crepe.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; slice lengthwise.
Put butter in skillet; let melt.
Add potatoes; let cook until almost done with top on skillet.
Then add sugar, nutmeg and flavoring.
Stir once in a while and let cook until well done and candied; cook down low.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions and bake.
When done, immediately poke holes all over top of cake.
Pour pineapple over cake.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Then add pudding that has been mixed with milk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over top of pineapple, then cover with whipped topping.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts over top.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: caramel cluster bars(microwave)
directions: Butter 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
In 2-quart glass bowl, place unwrapped caramels and milk.
Microwave on High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes, stirring often after the first minute, until mixture is a smooth consistency.
Stir in Honey & Nut Tasteeos to coat.
Press into pan with fingers moistened with water.
In small glass measuring cup, microwave chocolate on High for 60 to 80 seconds or until melted.
Drizzle over top of candy.
Refrigerate 30 minutes or until chocolate is set.
Cut into bars.
Store in refrigerator. Makes 24 bars.

title: fiesta dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine beans, salsa, and chilies; mix well. Spread into a 2 quart shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle evenly with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Garnish with green onions and black olives.
Serve with chips. (Approx. 6 servings.)

title: opal's mexican chicken soup
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients. Simmer for 20 minutes, then add chicken. Simmer for 5 more minutes. Combine flour and water. Whisk into soup. Stir in sour cream. Garnish with flour tortilla strips that have been baked.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Brown beef.
Add tomato paste and water to make sauce.
Add garlic.
Cook noodles and drain.
Add sour cream and onion.

title: hot potatoes and franks
directions: Brown frankfurters in butter in skillet.
Remove from skillet; stir soup mix, flour, sugar and pepper into pan drippings plus 1/2 cup water and vinegar.
Stir well.
Add frankfurters.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Cover; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add potatoes and sour cream.
Heat just to boiling point.

title: tender crust rolls
directions: Add butter, sugar and salt to scalded milk.
Stir to mix well. Let cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast to cooled milk mixture; stir until dissolved.
Add 1 cup flour; beat with rotary beater until well blended.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Mix in remaining flour until thoroughly blended.
Cover and let rest for 5 minutes.
Knead for 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl. Let rise in warm place until double in bulk.

title: deviled oysters
directions: You will need an oak plank, one-inch thick and as long and as wide as a large platter that is a satisfactory device for broiling fish.
For planking or broiling, it is best to use thin, flat fish such as mackerel or fish steaks.

title: my favorite chili
directions: Saute onion, green pepper, chopped garlic and ground beef in a heavy Dutch oven.
Stir in chili powder, cilantro and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, about 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and green chilies.

title: ding dong cake
directions: Bake a German chocolate cake according to package directions using a 9 x 12 inch pan.
Invert on a cookie sheet and place in freezer to stiffen, so you can cut it in half.
Make filling while cake is freezing.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together everything but chicken.
Set aside 2 cups of mixture.
Add chicken to remaining mixture.
Place about 3 tablespoons of chicken mixture in each tortilla.
Roll up.
Place side by side in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan and 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread mixture that was set aside over top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinning ham
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until onions are done. Remove casing from ham; score and roast 15 to 20 minutes per pound at 350°, basting often with sauce, or cook on rotisserie again basting often.
If you want sauce to serve with ham, make a double portion.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread rice, layer chicken, then broccoli.
Mix soup with 1 can water.
Pour over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: roux in the microwave
directions: In a 4-cup Pyrex measuring cup, put oil and flour.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Stir and microwave for 1 minute at a time, stirring after each minute, until as brown as you like.
Add onion, celery and bell pepper.
Microwave for 3 minutes.
If desired, add garlic, green onion and parsley.
Microwave for 2 minutes.
Pour into prepared gumbo stock, about 4 quarts.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Place fruit in a glass Pyrex 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Sweeten to taste.
One-quart is adequate for this size.
Cream sugar and oleo together in bowl.
Add milk and flour and beat until smooth. Mixture should be thin.
Pour over fruit.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Mix together flour, sugar and chili powder.
Mix into ground beef mixture.
Add 2 cans chili beans with 2 cans water.
Then 1 small can tomato paste.
Then add tomato soup, 1 can water, 1 can tomato sauce and 1 can of water.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Melt over low heat the butter and chocolate.
Remove from heat and add the other ingredients.
Pour into greased pie pan and cook for 25 minutes at 350°.
No longer!

title: lasagne and meat sauce
directions: Cook lasagne noodles per box directions.
In bowl, stir together cottage cheese, egg and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
In baking dish, layer 1/3 of lasagne noodles, 1 1/4 cups sauce, half of cheese mixture and 1/3 of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat once. Top with remaining noodles, sauce and Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Cover dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: banana oat bread
directions: In small bowl, combine first 4 ingredients. In a large bowl, combine next 4 dry ingredients.
Combine milk and bananas, then add to dry ingredients alternately with the contents of the small bowl.
Stir in nuts and oatmeal and put mixture into a greased loaf pan and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Then remove and cool 10 minutes before removing from its pan.

title: manhattan meatballs
directions: Mix apricot preserves and barbecue sauce in crock-pot and heat until bubbly.
Defrost frozen prepared meatballs (1/2 bag at a time).
Add 1/2 bag of thawed meatballs to bubbling sauce.
Heat on high setting for 1 hour and turn down heat setting to low; keep warm until ready to serve.
Transfer to chafing dish when needed.

title: biscuits
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until shortening is the size of peas.
Add buttermilk, stirring with fork, until dry ingredients are moistened.
(Dough will resemble cottage cheese and be sticky.)

title: grilled italian chicken
directions: Marinate chicken breast overnight, then grill until done. Serve with rice.

title: barbecue ham sandwiches
directions: Saute the onions in oleo until tender.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; put in a crock-pot, or cook on low for several hours.
Stir in finely chipped ham; heat until meat is warm.
Place on buns and serve.

title: fruit casserole
directions: Pour together juice from all fruits. Mix together cornstarch, margarine, brown sugar and 1/4 cup juices from fruit. Place fruit in baking dish; pour juice mixture over it. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Best served warm.

title: chicken curry
directions: Put chicken in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish, then broccoli on top of chicken.
Mix together soups, mayonnaise, spices and lemon juice.
Pour on top. Sprinkle cheese on soup mixture, then bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: no sugar cranberry salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Put milk in freezer for one hour, then beat adding juice of 2 lemons.
Grate rind of one lemon and add to milk.
While beating add sugar.
Combine jello with water and let chill until thick. Add to milk mixture mixing well.
Pour into crusts and chill until set.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients and pour into hot greased black iron skillet.
Bake for 30 minutes or until done.

title: lobster and corn chowder
directions: Fill a large pot with 2-inches water.
Set over high heat and bring to a boil; add lobsters.
Cover and cook until lobsters are red, about 7 minutes.
Transfer lobsters to a large ice bath to cool.
Remove meat from claws, knuckles and tails.
Reserve shells and bodies and refrigerate meat until ready to use.

title: dietetic cake
directions: Cream oleo well.
Add Sucaryl and eggs; beat well.
Add applesauce and dates.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and bake in a loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: yams
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until tender.

title: tex-mex cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking pan. Combine all ingredients in order listed; blend well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 9 servings.

title: burnt-sugar cake
directions: In a small heavy skillet, heat 3/4 cup sugar, stirring until a brown syrup forms and mixture begins to smoke. VERY GRADUALLY (because of spattering), stir in boiling water and remove from heat. Cool thoroughly.

title: french dressing
directions: You will need a 1-quart bottle.

title: pork chops with vegetables
directions: Brown pork chops in frying pan.
Add onion, carrots, potatoes, salt and pepper.
(I add a little garlic powder, too.)
Cover; cook until vegetables are tender.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate walnut yummies(ella davis' recipe)
directions: Combine mixes and sugar.
Beat egg, margarine, milk and vanilla.
Combine with mixes and sugar and stir in coconut. Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 13 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet immediately.
Ice with chocolate icing and top with walnut half.

title: buttermilk baked chicken
directions: Melt butter and crushed garlic clove in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dip chicken pieces in milk, then in cereal.
Place in pan.
Sprinkle seasoning over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn chicken.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes.

title: cajun fettuccine
directions: Using a 12-quart roaster, melt butter over medium heat.
Saute onions, bell peppers, garlic and jalapeno peppers for 15 minutes. Add cayenne; salt to taste.
Add flour slowly and stir.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Add parsley and allow to soften in mixture while stirring.
Add half and half, lemon juice and cheese.
Stir until cheese is blended well.
Boil shrimp for 3 minutes in 5-quart pot. Strain.
Add shrimp and crab meat.
Cook 15 minutes.
Stir in noodles; serve in 4-quart casserole dish.
Garnish with fresh parsley, lemon and cheese.
Yields 8 servings.

title: turkey apple salad
directions: In medium bowl stir first 4 ingredients.
In cup stir dressing and brown sugar, pour over and gently toss to coat.
Serve on lettuce if you like.
Yields 2 or 3 servings.

title: quick lemon pineapple pie
directions: Put pineapple (juice and all), pie filling, water and butter in pan.
Cook until very thick, stirring constantly.
Cool; stir a couple of times during cooling.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill in refrigerator.
For a less tart taste make pie the day before it's served.

title: 1-2-3 chicken pie
directions: Baking Temperature: 450°.
Baking Time: 15 minutes, divided.

title: fat-free fantasy fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add milk and corn syrup.
Boil mixture about 15 minutes, until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
(Drop small amount into cup of cold water.
Use fingers to form soft ball.)
Take off heat and beat with electric hand mixer for about 1 minute.
Do not overbeat.
Stir
in vanilla and cereal.
Spray 9-inch glass baking dish with nonfat cooking spray. Pour fudge into dish and let harden.
Cut into squares when set. Makes about 30 pieces.

title: crisp slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients and toss with shredded cabbage.
Will keep very well in refrigerator for several days.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box except use margarine or butter instead of oil.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Layer sauce, noodles, cheese and sauce in a 9 x 13-inch pan. When all is layered in pan, cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour, then bake 15 minutes, uncovered.
Allow to rest 10 minutes. Serves 12.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer in a larger pie plate: bean dip, sour cream (mixed well with taco seasoning), green chilies, tomatoes, cheese and black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lemon dill chicken saute
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a shallow dish.
Dip chicken in egg and then crumb mixture.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook 5 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lemon-nut bread
directions: Combine butter and sugar, creaming until light and fluffy. Add eggs, beating well. Combine dry ingredients. Add buttermilk and dry ingredients alternately to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with buttermilk.
Stir just until all ingredients are moistened. Stir in lemon rind and pecans.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool 15 minutes and remove from pan.

title: boiled no-baked cookies
directions: Measure peanut butter, oats and nuts.
Set aside. Measure sugar and cocoa.
Mix in large saucepan. Add milk and margarine. Stir.
Bring to a boil.
Boil together 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Add the set aside ingredients and vanilla.
Mix well together. Drop by spoon onto wax paper.

title: sweet-n-spicy meat balls
directions: Mix beef, breadcrumbs, onions, milk, parsley, salt, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and egg; stir well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Cook in melted shortening in large skillet until browned.
Remove from skillet; drain fat.
Heat chili sauce and jelly in skillet, stirring until jelly is melted.
Add meat balls; stir until coated.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Serve hot. (Makes about 5 dozen.)

title: coconut custard
directions: Grease pan heavily with butter, then flour.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: toll house marble squares
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and water.
Beat in the egg.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Add walnuts; spread mixture in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels over top.
Bake at 375° for 1 minute.
Run knife blade through to marbleize.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes longer.
Makes 24 squares.

title: meringue for 1 pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and 2 tablespoons sugar with water; cook until clear.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Add salt to 3 egg whites; whip until foamy or stands in peaks.
Add cornstarch mixture gradually to egg whites; continue beating until creamy.
Add remaining sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Pile on top of pie filling.
Be sure to spread all the way to edges.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix and place in freezer for 20 minutes.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Dip in almond bark or butterscotch chips.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In casserole dish, mix beans and vegetables.
Toss lightly with fork.
Mix soup with bean liquid until smooth.
Pour over beans.
Sprinkle with cheese and almonds.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and lightly browned.
Garnish with bacon. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: frito pie
directions: Brown ground
beef
in
skillet.
Prepare
Chili-O
mix according to package directions.
Combine with onion, beef and beans.
Layer Fritos,
chili
and cheese in large baking dish. Repeat layers.
Bake in a 325° oven until cheese has melted.

title: cornbread surprise(microwave recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a 2-quart microwave casserole dish. Bake on Medium-High for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops and set aside.
Add cup of rice to drippings. Add beef broth and water.
Place chops back into mixture.
On top of each chop, put 1 slice of onion, tomato and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy orange sherbet
directions: Pour Eagle Brand
into ice cream freezer. Add orange soda to fill line. Freeze! Enjoy!

title: lemon butter with strawberries
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients well, folding cream lightly into cooled lemon butter.
Decorate with strawberries or other fruit.

title: tomato salsa
directions: Peel and dice tomatoes. Toast peppers in oven until skin bubbles, then place in plastic bag until cool. Peel skin from peppers; cut out seeds and pith. Chop very fine. Combine all ingredients in a bowl; mix well.

title: ground beef stir
directions: Brown meat in pieces, then drain off fat.
Add other ingredients and simmer until tender.
Thicken with 2 tablespoons flour with cold water.

title: spaghetti hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix in eggs and milk.
Break spaghetti in thirds and cook until two-thirds done.
Mix in with hamburger mixture.
Top with grated cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and dried onion in skillet; drain grease. Cook spaghetti in salt water until tender; drain.
Combine beef, onion and spaghetti with sauce in bowl.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: luca's rice
directions: Combine in a 7 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour. (This is a simple side dish that a child can "help" make.)
Serves 6.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Melt the margarine.
Add the flour, salt, pepper, ham base and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in the ham broth, then stir in the milk.
Cook your potatoes, ham and onions until tender, then mix with the other ingredients.

title: salad of gold
directions: Put gelatin in hot water in blender.
Cover and stir until dissolved all juice, vinegar and milk.
Use liquify on blender and add cream cheese.
When mixture is smooth, add carrots and pineapple.
Chill.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Combine flour, pie spice, soda and salt in a large bowl.
Make a well in center.
Pour pumpkin mixture into well; stir just until dry ingredients are moist.
Stir in cranberries.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 8 x 3 3/4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick in center comes out clean. Makes 2 loaves.

title: junk over rice
directions: Start cooking rice.
While it's cooking, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain grease; season with garlic powder, salt and pepper. Add tomato sauce and tomatoes.
Bring to boil; lower heat and add vegetables.
Cover and simmer until rice is done cooking.
Serve Junk over mounds of rice.
Any vegetable of your choice can be used.

title: better than milk and cookies cake
directions: Bake German chocolate cake mix as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan. Remove from oven and while still warm, poke holes about 2-inches apart all over the cake with the end of a wooden spoon handle. Pour can of sweetened condensed milk into holes all over cake. Pour jar of butterscotch-caramel topping all over cake into holes. It doesn't matter if these drip all over cake as well as into holes. Cool completely (important as Cool Whip will melt and look curdled). Cover cake with Cool Whip, then sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter, add sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Place in baking dish.
Place fruit in center of batter and bake at 350° until brown.
This is a quick and easy way to make cobbler.

title: five minute microwave croutons
directions: Microwave butter in a 2-quart shallow baking dish at High (100% power) for 55 seconds, or until melted.
Stir in salad seasoning.
Add bread cubes. Stir to gently coat.
Microwave on High (100% power) for 4 1/2 to 5 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times. Cool.
Croutons will crisp as they cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: holiday ribbon gelatin
directions: In a bowl dissolve jello (lime) in 2 cups water (boiling) and 2 cups cold water. Pour into 9x13 inch dish. Refrigerate until set. (1 hour).

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Brown onion, beef and bacon.
Add all other ingredients, draining some of the liquid off the beans before adding.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: In mixing bowl, combine salmon with broth, eggs, corn meal and flour.
Mix thoroughly and add additional flour and meal if too moist.
Add onions; stir thoroughly and heat oil in skillet.
Pat salmon out into desired size patties and place in skillet.
Cook on medium-high heat for about 3 minutes; turn over and cook other side for 3 minutes.
Continue cooking and turning patties until golden brown.
Place paper towels on plate.
Place patties on plate and serve.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Mix all together except peas.
Add the peas 15 minutes before serving.
Bake in a covered casserole for 5 hours at 250°.
If it looks too dry, add a little water.

title: candied yams
directions: In a saucepan melt first 3 ingredients.
Pour over yams. (I use 3 very large yams which have been wrapped in aluminum foil and baked until soft.
Peel and slice about 1 1/2 inches thick.
Set on end in baking dish and pour candied sauce over yams.)
Bake in 350° oven until sauce boils and yams are heated through.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a shallow baking dish.
Combine apples, 1/4 cup sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and lemon juice in baking dish.
In medium size bowl cut margarine into flour until crumbly. Stir in remaining 1 cup sugar.
Sprinkle this flour mixture evenly over the apples in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until brown and bubbly and apples tender.

title: split seconds
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and sugar.
Blend in the shortening, egg and vanilla.
Place on lightly floured board. Divide into 4 parts; shape each into roll, 13 x 3/4-inch wide. Place on ungreased cookie sheet 4-inches apart.
Make depression down center of each roll.
Fill depression with jelly, jam or marmalade of your choice.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until light golden brown.
While warm, cut diagonally bars; cool on wire rack.
Transfer to wire rack to cool.

title: school day rolls
directions: Add 1/2 of flour to yeast; mix well.
Heat other 4 ingredients over low heat until it becomes 110°.
Pour liquid into flour and yeast, then slowly add the rest of flour.
Add more if needed. Knead well; let rise 2 hours, then form into rolls.
Let rise for 2 more hours.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or make into loaves and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corned beef and cabbage(microwave)
directions: Cut cabbage into 1/4-inch slices, then cut crosswise into 1-inch strips.
Place cabbage, onion, water and 1/4 teaspoon salt in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, on full power for 6 to 9 minutes or until cabbage is crisp-tender.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Drain and set aside.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil and peel potatoes and dice.
Add chopped onion and celery.
Add pickles and eggs. Add remaining ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: guacamole
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend until well combined. Makes about 2 cups.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice and beat well.
Add peanut butter.
Beat some more.
Add Cool Whip.
Beat until it stands. Pour in graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, drain and set aside.
Beat eggs, onions and cheese.
Add broccoli and soup.
Cover with bread crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1/2 hour or until brown.

title: spiced shrimp
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low 3 to 5 hours.

title: old fashioned rugulach
directions: In a large bowl, with mixer set at medium speed, cream butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar for 2 to 3 minutes, until light and fluffy.
Using a wooden spoon, stir in flour, just until blended.
Divide dough into four pieces and wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours until chilled and firm.

title: honey bars
directions: Mix all ingredients well and spread into 9 x 13-inch glass baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool; cut into 2 x 2-inch bars.

title: deep fried turkey
directions: Note: This is to be prepared on an outdoor cooker.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix well and serve.
Do not beat, just fold in.

title: pina colada mold(low calorie)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Stir in pineapple.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Whip until foamy.
Stir in yogurt and coconut.
Pour into a 4-cup mold.
Chill several hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Press
Oreo
crumbs
in 13 x 9-inch pan; drizzle butter over crumbs.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Blend Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar.	Spread over crumb crust.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Pour
prepared
chocolate
pudding	over
cream
cheese mixture. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together the sugar and eggs; add instant pudding, mixing well.
Add vanilla and condensed milk.
Put in ice cream freezer and fill to within 2-inches of the top of freezer can with whole milk.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: hasty fruit cobbler
directions: Dot a 13 x 10-inch baking dish with margarine.
Mix the flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour mixture into dish.
Pour juicy fruit on top of batter.
Fruit can be canned or fresh stewed fruit.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: instant rhubarb
directions: Cover rhubarb with sugar.
Let it stand overnight.
Add strawberries.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Add butter to 2 cups graham crackers to form crust.
Combine cream cheese, vanilla, Dream Whip, sugar and milk.
Whip with mixer until thick.
Put half of mixture on top of crust; add pie filling, then layer with the other half of mixture.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening over warm water.
Cool slightly. Mix together eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Blend in chocolate mixture.
Mix in flour.
Fold in walnuts.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 325° for about 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Cut into bars.

title: pearl of a pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening well.
Add sugar gradually, then eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add baking powder to flour and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Bake at 320° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let cool in pan.

title: amish bread
directions: Combine Herman, oil, eggs, vanilla and sugar, stirring well after each addition.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients. Stir into Herman mixture.
Pour into 2 greased and sugared loaf or cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans to cool on racks.
Nuts, raisins, candied fruit, etc., can be added to mixture.

title: baked spinach-stuffed onions
directions: Boil whole onions in outer skins for 20 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Peel skin and lift out center core.
Be sure to slice at least 1-inch from stem end of onion so inner core pops out easily. Chop remaining small inner cores of the onions and saute these in olive oil until tender.
Add spinach and cook over medium heat until all liquid has evaporated.
Stir in remaining ingredients except chicken broth.
Add salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Place onion cups in shallow baking pan; fill with spinach mixture.
Pour chicken broth over onions.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Garnish with parsley and peeled tomato skins rolled into rose shapes.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Line baking pan with aluminum foil.
Put pork chops in pan; top each with green pepper and onion rings.
Sprinkle each chop with 1 teaspoon lemon juice and 2 tablespoons brown sugar.
Cover chops, onions and green pepper with catsup.
Cover pan with aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, then bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp spread dip
directions: Soften cream cheese, then add mayonnaise.
Mix until well blended.
Add parsley, chopped egg, onion, pepper and shrimp; chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: lanette's grape salad
directions: Wash and dry grapes, if grapes are large, slice; set aside. Mix sour cream, cream cheese, and sugar.
Add 1/2 mixture to grapes and spread the remainder over top.
Toast pecans and mix with brown sugar and sprinkle on top of mixture.
Chill.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter with Crisco.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Add vanilla.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Put cake in cold oven.
Turn to 325 for 1 hour, then turn to 350 for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and turn out to cool.

title: fresh fruit sundae
directions: Arrange fruit in individual dessert dishes.
Top each serving with 1/2 cup cottage cheese.
Serve with dressing; sprinkle with nuts.

title: gingerbread
directions: Blend brown sugar, shortening and molasses.
Add baking soda and boiling water.
Mix well.
Add flour, ginger, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg, cloves and salt.
Mix well.
Add eggs and mix again.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: marinated broccoli chunks
directions: Combine vinegar, olive oil, dill weed and garlic in a medium bowl, stirring well with a wire whisk.
Set aside.
Trim large leaves from broccoli.
Remove flowerets and reserve for another use.
Remove tough ends of lower stalks and discard.
Wash remaining stalks and cut diagonally into 1/2-inch slices.
Add 2 cups broccoli slices to vinegar mixture.
Toss gently to coat. Reserve any remaining slices for another use.
Cover coated broccoli slices and chill 3 hours.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes.
Blend all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: banana coffee cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Combine egg and milk and add to flour mixture, stirring until well blended. Turn into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Peel bananas and cut in 1/4 inch slices.
Arrange bananas on cake top.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cover leaves with water; boil 15 minutes or until limp.
Mix ground beef, salt, pepper, rice, onion, egg and poultry seasoning together.
Place equal portions of meat on each leaf.
Fold sides of leaf over meat, roll up and fasten with toothpick or string. Brown in hot oil in large skillet.
Combine sugar, water and lemon juice and stir into tomato sauce.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour, basting occasionally.

title: mom's cake and frosting
directions: Bake cake as directed.
If baked in a 13 x 9-inch pan, cool and cut lengthwise, using dental floss and a sawing motion.

title: sweet potato sonker
directions: Using first five ingredients make pastry. Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender.
Beat egg, pour into cup and add 1 teaspoon vinegar and 1/2 cup cold water.
Mix well.
Roll out dough to 1/4 inch.
Line 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle pastry with 2 teaspoons of the sugar.
Place potatoes in dish, layering with brown and white sugar, dot with margarine.
Sprinkle on cinnamon and nutmeg. Pour 1 1/2 cups reserved liquid over ingredients.
Top with thin crust.
Bake approximately 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Bake until slightly brown, remove and brush top with melted butter or margarine and return to oven to continue browning.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake mix following box directions.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix coconut and nuts.
Place in bottom of pan.
Pour cake mix over nut mixture.
Melt cream cheese mixture.
Pour evenly over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve warm and enjoy!!!

title: easy pickled beets
directions: In a large saucepan, combine vinegar, sugar, cinnamon and salt. Add spices. Bring to a boil. Drain the beets, reserving 3/4 cup juice. Stir beets and reserved juice into saucepan. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove spices. Yield: 18 to 20 servings.

title: crisco double pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and Crisco until like crumbs.
Add water.
Mix well and roll out to fit pie plate.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix cubed chicken with sour cream and soup.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with crushed crackers mixed with melted margarine.
Sprinkle poppy seed over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt; gradually add milk with egg yolks mixed in, to the dry mixture.
Cook over medium heat until thick, about 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool; add butter and
vanilla.
Pour
into cooled baked shell and spread with meringue or Cool Whip.
If using meringue, bake in a 325° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: stuffed bread(ham, pickle, egg, tomato)
directions: Mix together cream cheese, green onions and grated cucumbers and salt well.
Consistency should be that of easily spreadable cream cheese.
Set aside.

title: slow cooker barbecue beef
directions: Place beef in a 5-quart slow cooker. Add celery, onion and green pepper. In a bowl, combine the ketchup, tomato paste, brown sugar, vinegar, chili powder, lemon juice, molasses, salt, Worcestershire sauce and mustard. Pour over beef mixture. Cover and cook 8 to 9 hours or until meat is tender. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate mint(serves 1)
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender on medium speed until smooth.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix squash and egg together.
Mix dry ingredients together. Add dry ingredients to squash mixture and mix together.
Add sugar and stir until sugar dissolves.
Drop by teaspoon into frying pan of grease.
Brown on both sides.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl with a spoon.
Pour batter into a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan 1 hour before removing from pan.
Allow to cool completely and ice if desired with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Mix sugars, butter or margarine, oil, egg and vanilla together with mixer.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar and add to the mixture.
Then add coconut, Rice Krispies, oatmeal and pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased pan; flatten with a fork. Bake about 12 minutes to a golden brown, leave some space between. Cool on a rack.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat egg yolks. Add sugar and flour.
Gradually add milk. Cook until thick.
Add vanilla and peanut butter. Stir until peanut butter melts.
Pour in baked pie crust. Top with egg whites that have been beaten and sweetened.
Brown lightly in oven.

title: crab dip
directions: Melt butter or margarine and mix with ketchup and hot sauce (or just use the butter and hot sauce).

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Cook on medium heat; bring to boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Add vanilla, oatmeal and peanut butter; stir until starts to thicken.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: amigo pie
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Add tomatoes, chili powder, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
In bowl combine cornmeal, flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and baking powder.
Add hot water and melted butter.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in 1 cup Cheddar cheese. Pour into greased pie pan.
Spoon in meat mixture into center of cornmeal mixture and press down gently.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Top with 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Serve with taco sauce.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in a slow cooker all day or simmer on the stovetop on low until flavors combine.
Serve over angel hair spaghetti with salad and garlic bread.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Mix biscuit mix and ground sausage very well, then add cheese. Mix well again.
Roll into balls the size of large marbles. These can be made in advance, covered and refrigerated.
Bake at 350° until brown; serve very hot.
Leftovers can be frozen, thawed, heated and served again.

title: cranberry nut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter a 9-inch pie plate and layer berries on bottom.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
In a bowl beat egg until thick.
Gradually add sugar, beating until thoroughly blended.
Stir in flour and melted butter.
Blend well. Pour over berries, sugar and nuts.
Bake 45 minutes.
Cut in wedges.
Serve with ice cream.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain and rinse pinto beans. In a large bowl, mix all ingredients with 1/2 bottle of Catalina salad dressing.
Add to your personal preference.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole.
Bake in 300° oven for about 3 hours or use electric pot to cook about 2 to 3 hours, until rice is done.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten whole eggs and add vanilla, vinegar and salt.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Start cooking at 300°; raise heat in 10 minutes to 350°.
Cook for 45 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, bell pepper, pineapple, seasoned salt, onion and dried beef.
Place wax paper on table.
Sprinkle paprika and pecans and roll cheese ball all over until covered.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: DRAIN ALL FRUITS.
Crumble macaroon in a shallow pan..
Bake at 400° for 3 to 4 minutes or until lightly toasted, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Sprinkle 1/2 of macaroons in a 2 1/2 quart casserole.
Layer remaining ingredients in order given.
Sprinkle on remaining macaroons.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.
Remove from refrigerator; let stand for 30 minutes. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly. Serves 8 to 10.

title: unleavened bread for communion
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add alternately eggs and flour. Add salt and vanilla.
If mixture seems too thick to spread, mix a small amount of milk into dough.
Spread into greased cookie sheet. Perforate into squares and put fork hole in center of each.
Bake at 375° until firm.
Does not take long.
Keep watch.

title: yogurt oat bran muffins(makes 1 dozen)
directions: In medium bowl, combine oat bran, flour, brown sugar and baking powder; stir in yogurt, margarine and egg whites just until blended.
(Batter will be slightly lumpy.) Spoon batter into 12 paper-lined or greased 2 1/2-inch muffin-pan cups.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes or until done.
Serve warm.

title: venison marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate venison in liquid for 3 to 5 hours at room temperature.
Drain.
Grill venison to medium-rare doneness; do not overcook.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: lemon and garlic chicken
directions: Slice chicken thin.
Put in frying pan with oil over low heat. Brown both sides with garlic.
Add juice of 1 lemon and cover. Lower heat and cook until done.
Garnish with other lemon slices and parsley.
Serve with rice.

title: festive turkey with peppers
directions: In large bowl, combine brown sugar, soy sauce and cornstarch. Add turkey and turn to coat.
In large skillet, heat oil and cook garlic and turkey mixture over high heat, stirring constantly, 3 minutes.
Stir in peppers and onions. Cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.

title: marinated steak
directions: Mix together and pour over meat and cover.
Let stand overnight, turning meat often and broil to desired doneness.
If you are in a hurry, heat the sauce, pour over meat and let stand as long as possible (over meat).

title: baked custard
directions: Beat the egg slightly; stir in milk, salt and vanilla.
If you wish, add artificial sweetener to flavor.
Pour into custard cup and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Set in pan of hot water and bake in 350° oven 45 minutes.
Other flavors such as almond, lemon, orange or maple may be used in place of vanilla.
One serving equals 1/2 cup milk and 1 meat exchange.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix and blend in blender.
Shake well before using.

title: bean pot
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir and simmer in crock-pot until bubbly.

title: caramel pudding
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, eggs, flour, milk, salt, vanilla, baking powder and shortening into a batter.
Pour into baking pan.
Mix together the brown sugar, butter and cinnamon; sprinkle over the top of the batter.
Pour water over the top.
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: old dutch pickled cabbage
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, vinegar and water; boil for 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Dissolve 2 teaspoons salt in quart of water. Stir in ice cubes (about 1 tray full).
When water is cold, pour it over cabbage and pepper mixture, ice and all.
Stir lightly to mix; let set about 30 minutes, until crisp.
Add 1 shredded carrot and 1 stalk celery (diced).
Squeeze and drain cabbage and pepper well. Mix in carrot and celery.
Place in airtight container.
Pour vinegar mixture over cabbage mixture; stir well.
Cabbage will settle to bottom.
Refrigerate at least overnight, as it improves with time.
Stir mixture once in a while, until cabbage settles to bottom.

title: buttermilk biscuits 6
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. In a large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients. Using a fork or pastry blender, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal. Blend in buttermilk until a soft dough is formed. Turn onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly 7 or 8 times. Roll to 1/2-inch thickness and cut out with a floured biscuit cutter. Re-roll scraps and cut until all dough is used. Place biscuits on an ungreased cookie sheet about 1-inch apart and bake until golden, approximately 15 minutes. Makes about a dozen to a dozen and a half biscuits, depending on the size of the cutter.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add corn a little at a time. You want this mixture to be thick enough to drop from a spoon. Sometimes I don't use the entire can of corn.
After mixing the corn, add onion; onion is optional.
I use ice cream scoop and drop a small amount, maybe a tablespoonful, into hot oil and let them brown lightly.
Do not have the oil too hot or they will be raw in the center.
This recipe makes enough to serve from 4 to 6 people.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in
a
4 quart saucepan.
On medium heat stir until it boils.
Boil
for 1 minute. Remove.
Add vanilla, oats and peanut butter.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by rounded teaspoons on wax paper.
Cool.

title: two-part icing
directions: Mix milk and cornstarch.
Cook until thickened; cool.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add cooled mixture and cream.

title: stromboli
directions: Spray frozen dough with cooking spray; place on greased aluminum foil (Release preferred) on greased cookie sheet. Place dough in cold oven overnight.

title: steak marinade
directions: Pour over steak before grilling and baste with brush while cooking.

title: coconut pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Combine in a large bowl all ingredients; stir until moistened.
Roll into balls about the size of walnut.
Place on cookie sheets about 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until light golden brown.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: bread pudding with apples
directions: Combine in a saucepan brown sugar, spices and 4 cups water. Bring to a boil, then simmer while stirring 20 minutes.
Discard spices.
Combine in a large bowl apples, raisins, almonds and cheese.
Butter a 3-quart baking dish and layer half of the bread crumbs.
Spoon half the apples over them, then layer rest of bread crumbs and apple mixture.
Pour the syrup with butter over mixture and bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: barbecued beef brisket
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and garlic powder.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Pour liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce over meat and cover with foil.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight, turning once.
Bake, covered, with foil at 300° for 4 to 4 1/2 hours or until tender.
Pour over barbecue sauce and bake additional 30 minutes.
Slice diagonally; electric knife works best.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate at least 24 hours in refrigerator.
May be made 2 or 3 days in advance.

title: butterscotch thins
directions: Melt oleo; add sugars.
Mix well.
Add egg; beat until light colored. Sift flour and soda.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Shape into roll about 1 1/2 inches in diameter. Roll in foil or plastic wrap.
Chill or freeze.
Slice thin and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for about 10 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: jello
directions: Put fruit cocktail, juice and all, in a pot to boil.
Pour over Jell-O and stir until Jell-O is dissolved.
Don't set completely, when almost set, fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, pineapple, green pepper, 1/2 cup of pecans, onion and salt.
Form into a ball.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Remove from refrigerator and roll in the remaining nuts.

title: gusisada
directions: Saute onion and garlic until brown.
Add tomato and saute lightly.
Add meat; cook until gray, stirring often.
Add salt and cover with water.
Cook 5 minutes; add potatoes, beans and pepper. Cook until vegetables are tender; do not overcook.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: In bowl combine first 4 ingredients, add salad dressing, water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 inch by 13 inch cake pan.
Bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Put in pan in order given.
Cover and bake 5
hours at 250°.

title: quick tortoni cups *
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Spoon into 10 individual paper bake cups in muffin pans.
Freeze until firm.
Top each with cherry.
Makes 10 servings.

title: kahlua
directions: Dissolve coffee and sugar in boiling water.
Add liquor and vanilla bean.
Pour into large bottle, let stand for 30 days. Remove vanilla bean and drink (tie a thread around the bean for easy removal).

title: spanish omelet rounds
directions: Use enough
margarine
to
grease a 12-inch Dutch oven. Heat oven just
hot
enough
to sizzle a drop of water.	Break eggs into
oven.
Top
with
bacon
and cheese.	Cook over low heat until
edges
turn	white.	Add
a small amount of water. Cover with
lid to hold steam.
While eggs are cooking, spread salsa on muffin.
Add fried egg on top of muffin when done.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, salt and spices until everything is well dissolved.
Do not heat.
Slice the onion into a glass or plastic quart jar.
Fill the jar with sliced, unpeeled cucumbers.
Pour solution over cucumbers.
Put on lid, but it is not necessary to seal.
Keep in refrigerator.
They are crisp and keep for up to a year.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; set aside.
Cream butter and sugars; add eggs and beat.
Mix in vanilla, dry ingredients and oats.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: denver pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with Season-All.
Coat both sides of pork chops with sour cream. Then dip into cornflake crumbs.
Cover both sides.
Place on cookie sheet sprayed lightly with Pam. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done. Great flavor, easy and the meat stays moist!

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix the ingredients well.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Chill 24 hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: no sugar cookies
directions: Cook raisins, dates, apples, and water for 3 minutes on low heat.
Add margarine and cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix sugar, pumpkin and eggs.
Add oil and beat lightly.
Add dry ingredients.
Do not overmix.
Spoon into greased muffin tins and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: glass candy
directions: Mix the sugar, water and corn syrup in a saucepan on medium heat; cook to 300° or hard crack.
Remove from heat after boiling stops.
Add food coloring and flavoring.
Spread powdered sugar into bottom of cookie sheet.
Pour candy over the top.
Cool; break into pieces.

title: carrot crunch
directions: Cut carrots lengthwise in slivers.
Cook in large covered pan, using salt and small amount of water.
When carrots are just barely tender, remove from pan and set aside.
Drain water.
In the pan, stir together butter, brown sugar, orange peel and almonds.
When well mixed, return carrots to pan.
Let simmer for 5 minutes, turning carrots to coat with almond mixture.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery; drain.
Mix in soups.
Put in a baking dish, 11 x 14-inch.
Put Tater Tots over top, bake uncovered 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Yields 8 servings.

title: reduced calorie pound cake
directions: Gradually beat sugar into margarine until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time beating after each addition. Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in lemon rind, vanilla and yogurt.
Pour batter into 10-inch Bundt pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes; remove from pan.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 24 (1-inch) slices; 156 calories per slice.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts into bite size pieces and marinate in water and 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Dip chicken in eggs and the flour/cornstarch mixture.
Fry until golden brown. While frying make the sauce, chop cashews and green onions.
Cook rice and put in 9 x 12 pan and keep warm until chicken is done.
Put chicken pieces on rice, pour sauce on and sprinkle cashews and green onions on top and serve.

title: *kool-aid pie
directions: Chill milk thoroughly, then beat until stiff peaks.
Fold in slowly the sugar and Kool-Aid.
Pour in graham cracker crust and freeze.
Top with Dream Whip.
Keep in freezer.
Remove from freezer 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: turkey and broccoli
directions: In a large saucepan over medium-high heat, heat water and butter until butter melts.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: Cut cheese into cubes.
Place in a saucepan with 1/2 cup of butter.
Heat over low heat until melted, stirring often.
Place vegetables in 1-quart casserole dish.
Pour cheese over and mix well.

title: garlic ranch chicken
directions: Combine dressing, garlic and basil in a heavy-duty zip-top plastic bag. Add chicken, turning to coat. Squeeze out air and seal bag. Place in the refrigerator to marinate for at least 30 minutes; the longer, the better. Grill chicken breasts on medium heat for 6 to 8 minutes on each side.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in eggs.
Mix thoroughly. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Chop vegetables; add to pasta.
Pour dressing over.
Refrigerate 24 hours for best flavor.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add water.
Add cubes to dissolve.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Combine soy sauce and lime juice; pour over chicken in large plastic bag.
Press air out of bag and tie securely.
Marinate 1 hour, turning bag over occasionally.
Reserving marinade, broil chicken 5-inches from heat for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender. Turn over and brush occasionally with reserved marinade.
Or grill chicken 4 to 5-inches from hot coals 8 to 10 minutes on each side, or until tender.
Keep warm while preparing the pepper and onions. Slice chicken into thin strips.
To serve, spread tortillas with butter.
Wrap around desired amount of chicken and vegetables.

title: aunt betty's cookies
directions: Cook sugar and Karo to a good boil.
Add peanut butter and Special K. Mix well with syrup mixture.
Over hot water, melt butterscotch chips and chocolate chips.
Press first mixture in a buttered 9 x 11-inch pan and pour chocolate and butterscotch mixture over it.
Cool.

title: pecan roast
directions: Cook celery, onion and peppers in 2/3 cup water for 10 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl. Bake in well-oiled loaf pan at 375° until nicely browned (about 1 hour).
Serves 8 to 10.

title: frankfurters in a loaf
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Split frankfurters lengthwise, not cutting completely through.
Fill each with a strip of cheese, about 1 teaspoon relish and/or catsup.
Mix remaining ingredients with a fork; beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Spread in pan.
Arrange frankfurters crosswise in pan, pressing into dough slightly.
Bake until dough is light brown (about 20 minutes).

title: parmesan turkey patties
directions: Combine all ingredients except margarine.
Shape into 4 patties.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Fry until done.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Layer apples and onion in casserole. Combine the sugar, Worcestershire sauce, catsup, vinegar, salt and pepper.

Combine the catsup/vinegar mixture and pour half over the apples and onion. Trim all excess fat from the chops and layer them over the apples and onion. Pour the rest of the catsup mixture over the chops and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
This can be made ahead and refrigerated before baking.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and mix well.
Add melted butter.
Add syrup and vanilla.
Mix well and add nuts.
Bake for about 10 minutes at 400°, then about 30 minutes at about 350°.
Times vary with ovens.

title: raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl; set aside.
Stir baking mix, water, raisins and butter.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: stupid pie
directions: Beat egg whites, add sugar gradually until stiff. Stir in vanilla, add nuts and Ritz crackers. Pour into a greased pie tin and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Cool before serving and top with whipped cream.

title: peach stone sour
directions: Blend together and serve.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Sprinkle gelatin in cold water.
Combine egg yolks, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add to hot milk.
Cook in a double boiler until mixture coats a spoon.
Add gelatin to hot mixture.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill until syrupy.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and 1 cup whipped cream.
Pour into crust-lined pan and chill. Top pie with remainder of whipped cream and sprinkle with coconut.

title: polish reuben casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, onion and mustard in medium bowl; blend well.
Spread sauerkraut in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with uncooked noodles.
Spoon soup mixture evenly over top.
Top with sausage, then cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter in small bowl; sprinkle over top.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until noodles are tender.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: peach porcupine cake
directions: Beat margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla together by mixer or by hand until creamy.
Add flour.
Form ball and place in 8-inch greased pie plate.
Leaving it in the ball shape, push peach slices into it, as many as you can, all over it (it will look like a porcupine).

title: cocktail sauce for seafood
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and blend thoroughly.
Chill before serving.
Makes about 3/4 cup.

title: green beans
directions: Boil
bacon
drippings, vinegar and sugar to mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef, green pepper, celery and onions.
Add remainder of ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 375° for one hour.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal, flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Stir.
Combine egg, buttermilk and oil.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients.
Stir until moistened. Spoon batter into greased miniature muffin pans.
Fill 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: fruit (apple) dip
directions: Stir Marshmallow Fluff with cream cheese until smooth.
Slice apples in quarters.
Dip!

title: apple salad
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat until sauce is thick. Let cool. Chop apples and pour sauce over them. Mix well. Top with chopped nuts and maraschino cherries. Store in the refrigerator.

title: syrup tea cakes
directions: Mix
together all ingredients except flour and shortening. Beat
well.
Add
shortening
in flour as in making biscuits. Knead
until dough is slightly firm.
Roll out and cut in circles and bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk, without stirring, to 234° or until mixture forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and salt.
Beat until it just loses its gloss.
Spread into buttered pan.
Cut into squares.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds of fudge.

title: salmon burgers
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Form into 4 patties.
Panfry in small amount of oil.
Brown on both sides.
Serve on toasted hamburger buns.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potatoes, and heat until cheese is melted.
Slice potatoes and cook until almost done.
Layer potatoes in large baking pan.
Salt and pepper.
Pour cheese mixture over potatoes and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Top with French fried onions and bake another 5 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes with onions
directions: Mix soup and milk in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer potatoes, onions and cheese.
Repeat layers and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Bake an additional 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Combine in 2 1/2-quart casserole the rice, water and butter. Add celery, onion and soup.
Add broccoli and cheese.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: raisin sauce(yield: 20 tablespoons; pan size: 2-cup)
directions: Combine all ingredients in glass dish.
Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes or until thickened, stirring once.
Serve with pork roast.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; cover with sugar and set aside.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add orange juice, pineapple, and rest of ingredients with cranberries to the jello.
Pour in mold and chill overnight.

title: yellow cornbread
directions: Sift together cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in egg, milk and oil.
Pour batter into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine the ingredients and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into small cubes.
Dice onion.
Bring to boil in water and add beef bouillon cubes and margarine.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add milk and thicken with flour.
Cook until flour dissolves on low heat.

title: rita may's brownies
directions: Melt together the chocolate squares and butter.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Mix and pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: john ben getty
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Pour off excess fat.
Cook noodles in slightly salted water.
Do not overcook.
Drain noodles.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese, in large casserole dish.
Bake in moderate oven about 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top for last 15 minutes of baking.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together in order.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: peach chiffon pie
directions: Combine gelatin, sugar, salt and flour in saucepan.
Drain peaches.
Add water to syrup if necessary to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add syrup to gelatin mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice and rind. Chill until mixture is consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Beat with electric beater until fluffy.
Whip evaporated milk.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Fold in peaches.
Reserve a few slices. Pour custard into pie shell.
Place slices on top.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together except tomatoes.
Wait 2 hours before serving and add tomatoes.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, vinegar and celery seed and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine sugar, water, cinnamon and nutmeg. Cook 5 minutes or until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat; add butter.

Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Mix with dry ingredients the shortening, then add milk. Roll out dough until 1/4 inch thick; cut into 6 squares. Place sliced apples in square. Sprinkle with additional sugar, spices and a little flour; dot with butter. Bring corners of pastry and pinch edges together firmly. Place in well greased pan and pour sauce over all. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, basting often.

title: eggplant patties
directions: Cook eggplant until tender; drain and mash.
Stir in crumbs, cheese, eggs, parsley, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Shape into 8 patties.
Cook in hot oil about 3 to 5 minutes each side, until brown.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Peel cabbage leaves off.
Put in pan and steam until starts to get tender.
Saute ground beef, onion, green pepper, oregano and rice until tender.
Take cabbage leaves out.
Fill leaf and roll up and anchor with toothpick.
Put in pan.
Pour tomato sauce over.
Cook over medium heat about 20 minutes or bake in oven at 350°
for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two loaf pans.
Set aside.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients as listed.
Pour into pans about 3/4 full.
Bake 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: garden deviled eggs(makes 48 appetizers)
directions: Cut each egg crosswise in slices.
Scoop yolks out into small bowl; mash well.
Set egg whites aside.
Stir cheese spread, mayonnaise, scallions, pimientos and mustard into yolks until smooth and well blended.
Top each Wheat 'n Bran Triscuits wafter with an egg white slice.
Spoon or pipe yolk mixture onto egg whites.
Garnish with parsley and tomato, if desired.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until set.

title: dottie martin's shortbread
directions: All flour should be sifted twice to prevent heaviness.
Set oven at 375°.

(When baking in quantity, I bake in an approximately 12 x 18-inch cookie tin with a lip and cut into pieces about 2 1/2 to 3-inch square and 1/4-inch thick, 24 pieces, or make fingers by cutting into 48 pieces.)

title: date whip pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients except whipping cream.
Spread in greased 9 x 9 pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Mixture will raise and fall.
Cool.
Crumble with fork into bowl (taste some here, but try not to eat it all yet!).
Whip cream and stir into crumbled mixture.
Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Serve.

title: chewy candy crunch bars
directions: 1. In large bowl combine cereal, peanuts, candies.
Set aside. 2. In a 2 qt. saucepan melt butter (2-4 minutes).
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup, and flour.
Cook over medium heat stirring occasionally until mixture comes to a full boil (2-4 minutes). Boil one minute. 3. Pour caramel mixture over cereal mixture; toss to coat well.
Press on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool completely and cut into bars.

title: peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large pan, melt butter.
Add flour, sugar and milk mixture.
Pour in peaches and bake about 30 minutes or until done.

title: chicken diablo
directions: Season chicken; remove skin first, if desired.
Brown in oil. Remove chicken.
Stir in flour (you can remove most of the fat first).
Add water or broth.
Cook until thick.
Add remaining 4 ingredients and mix until smooth.
Add chicken to sauce.
Cover and simmer until tender (45 minutes to 1 hour).
Serves 4.

title: home-brewed vanilla extract
directions: Combine vodka and vanilla beans in a jar with a tight fitting lid. Cover the jar and let it stand 6 to 8 weeks, shaking 3 times a week. (The vodka mixture will turn amber colored after a day or two.)
After half the vanilla extract is used, add more vodka to cover the beans. The flavor in the beans is gone when the vodka no longer turns to a dark color.
Yields 2 cups.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sift flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt into large bowl. Add apples, nuts, butter and eggs.
Beat until just mixed.
Batter will be thick.
Bake for 1 hour.
Cool slightly.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: main dish - three bean medley
directions: Combine beef, onions and salt.
Brown over medium heat; drain. Combine beef mixture and remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour mixture into lightly greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: no bake persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour into a baking pan; cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: glazed pork chops
directions: In skillet, in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook half of the chops 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.

Remove; repeat with remaining chops. In skillet, combine soup and sugar. Heat to boiling. Return chops to skillet; cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes or until chops are no longer pink. Stir occasionally. Remove chops; keep warm.
Stir cornstarch mixture into skillet. Cook until mixture boils and thickens. Stir constantly.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook fryer and cut off bones. Cook your peppers and onions in 2 tablespoons butter.
Cook your spaghetti in chicken broth. Add chicken, onions, peppers, pimentos, chicken soup and cheese. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave on High 2 minutes more.
Add baking soda and vanilla.
Stir well and pour over the popped corn which has been placed in a very large bowl.
Stir to coat evenly.
Microwave on High for 45 seconds; stir.
Microwave on High for 45 more seconds.
Turn out onto cookie sheet to cool.
Break into pieces and store in airtight container (if there's any left).

title: skippy oatmeal cookies
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and oats and mix together.
In mixer bowl at medium speed, beat the margarine and peanut butter until smooth.
Beat in the sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add the flour mixture by hand and mix well. Drop on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 17 minutes.
Store in tightly covered container.
Yields about 50 cookies.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix above ingredients and pour in greased baking dish.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Slice or quarter cucumbers and pack in 10 hot quart jars.
Add 1 clove of garlic and 1 teaspoon dill weed to each jar.

title: chocolate yum yum cake
directions: Butter 9 X 13 inch pan on bottom and 1/2 inch up the sides. For bottom layer, bake cake 15 minutes at 350 degrees.
Let cool.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and condensed milk well.
Slowly add lime juice and blend until thick.
May bake this at 325° for 30 minutes. Cool thoroughly and top with whipped cream.

title: peach torte
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar and sugar gradually.
Beat until stiff.
Add Ritz crackers, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour into buttered pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°. Cool.
After cooling, pour pie filling over baked layer.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar in a large bowl.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add to oil and sugar and mix well.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and carrots.
Fold in nuts or raisins.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased cake pan for 45 minutes, or until center springs back to the touch.
This cake is very moist and keeps well.

title: macaroni, peas and tuna
directions: Boil macaroni until tender.
Drain and wash.
Add peas, tuna, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Serve hot.

title: e-z cobbler
directions: Spread sweetened fruit in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Drizzle with a mixture of flour, salad oil and milk.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: marie's chicken noodle casserole(excellent)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a buttered casserole.
Grate 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and put on top.
Put buttered bread crumbs on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat powdered sugar and oleo together.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add Vanilla.
Beat again to mix.
Spread evenly over crumbs in dish.
Slice 3 bananas and place on top of pudding layer.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over all evenly and sprinkle ground nuts on top and dot with maraschino cherries over top.
No Baking - Refrigerate over night.

title: spanish green beans
directions: Fry bacon and onion until crisp; add 1 tablespoon flour.
Stir and add 2 cups tomatoes and drained green beans.
Chopped celery or water chestnuts may be added.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fritos mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain.
Add chopped onions and salt.
Add chili and tomato soup; simmer while stirring.
Mixture should be consistency of gravy.
Add small amount of water, if dry. Line large casserole with 1/2 of Fritos.
Pour in meat mixture. Put remaining Fritos on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 400° oven until cheese is melted.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add soups, milk and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Heat.
Pour over crushed Doritos in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cornbread tamale pie(lo-fat)
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with vegetable spray.

Over medium heat, brown turkey. Add onion, green pepper, jalapenos and garlic. Cook until tender. Stir in tomato sauce and the next 6 ingredients. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes; add Cheddar cheese, stirring constantly. Cook until the cheese melts.
Spoon into an 8-inch square pan coated with oil spray. Combine cornbread, salt and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat and cook, stirring constantly (about 3 minutes).
Stir in oleo and spoon over the meat mixture to within 1-inch of the edge.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until topping is golden. Serves 6.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients and spread over sliced apples in unbaked pie crust.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lo-fat shrimp dip
directions: Drain and rinse shrimp pieces.
Add all together, mixing well. Refrigerate.
Serve with fresh vegetables or Snack Well fat-free crackers.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon undrained pineapple into pan.
Spread evenly.
Add pie filling in even layer.
Sprinkle dry cake onto cherry layer and spread evenly.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix and place butter over top. Bake at 350° for 48 to 53 minutes.
Serve warm or cooled.

title: goulash with green peppers and noodles
directions: Cut beef into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Dice the bacon and put into heavy Dutch oven.
Saute over medium heat until fat is rendered out.
Add beef cubes.
Brown slowly until browned on all sides. Add onion; cook until onion is softened.
Add soup, paprika, salt and green pepper, blending well.
Cook slowly, covered, without allowing to boil, for about 2 hours, or until meat is very tender. Spoon over hot buttered noodles.
Serves about 4.

title: glazed sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water to cover 20 to 25 minutes or until fork-tender.
Let cool to touch; peel and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange slices in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add baking powder and beat.
Add vanilla.
Beat with mixer until creamy and to desired consistency for spreading on cake.

title: sourdough bread
directions: To Make Starter Batter:
Dissolve 1 package active dry yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Stir in 2 cups lukewarm water, 2 cups sifted all-purpose flour and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Cover with cheesecloth.
Let stand at room temperature 5 to 10 days, stirring 2 or 3 times a day.
(Starter will have a "yeasty" not sour smell.)
Cover and refrigerate the starter until ready to make bread.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars together with butter and eggs until smooth.
Add oil, flour, soda and tartar (mix well).
Drop on cookie sheet. Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate spiders
directions: Place morsels in 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Heat in microwave for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Allow to set until firm.
Yields 3 1/2 to 4 dozen.

title: fruit and yogurt creme pie
directions: Arrange fruit in crust.
In food processor or blender, process cottage cheese and yogurt on high speed until smooth.
Mix gelatin and cold water.
Add to mixture, blending well.
Pour over fruit in crust.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Garnish with dollops of yogurt and fruit just before serving.

title: make your own eagle brand milk
directions: Blend well until smooth and creamy.
Use about 1 cup to equal the one can of Eagle Brand milk.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter, salt and cream over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves. Boil for 5 minutes on medium heat. Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream and stir.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; stir well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan and cool.

title: chicken taco casserole
directions: Crush doritos; place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup, salsa and chicken.
Put on top of Doritos.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes (until toothpick comes out clean).

title: mary's mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Brown ground beef, drain. Add taco seasoning and water required on package. Mix cornbread mix by package directions. Add corn, meat and one half of cheese. Bake for 25 minutes, sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: border buttermilk
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve over ice.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, onions and peppers into a jar or other container with a lid.
Sprinkle with salt and stir.
Let stand in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Drain all liquid.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir and refrigerate.
Will keep up to 2 months. Ready to eat the next day.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Put butter and vanilla in bowl.
Attach bowl and flat beater. Turn to speed 6 and cream until smooth, 2 minutes.
Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar for 30 seconds; continue beating for 1 minute.
Add eggs and beat 30 seconds.
Scrape bowl.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Do stir speed and gradually add dry ingredients until mixed, 1 minute.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter. Cook onion until clear. Stir in broccoli and soup.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in cheese and rice. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and vanilla, then dry ingredients, nuts, chips and oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: aunt dora's squash souffle
directions: Saute onions and green pepper until soft and light brown. Wash and slice squash.
Cook in boiling water until soft.
Drain and put through food processor, blender or chopper.
Add onion, green pepper, butter, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Pour into well-buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute the onion in oil until tender.
Mix all ingredients; put in 9 x 13-inch greased pan and refrigerate for 1 hour or more. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: anita's artic salad slices
