directions: Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar; add nuts and fruit. Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into square pan.
Freeze until firm, about 6 hours or overnight.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Dip tortilla in chicken broth and line bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole pan.
Place chicken on top; pour soup mix over chicken.
Grate Longhorn cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: hot cheddar bean dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Spoon into small ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Beat in eggs, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased sheet.
Flatten with a wet fork, crisscross.
Bake at 325° for about 10 minutes.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix together Bisquick, brown sugar, oil and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: sausage and egg breakfast casserole
directions: Layer the first 4 ingredients in casserole dish.
Mix the eggs, 2 1/2 cups milk and mustard together; pour over layers and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, mix soup and 1/2 cup milk. Spread over top of casserole.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: aunt jemima easy spoon bread
directions: Scald 1 1/2 cups of milk.
Combine corn meal mix and remaining 1 cup milk.
Slowly add to scalded milk; cook until just thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in butter. Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Slowly add corn meal mixture to beaten egg yolks, beating constantly.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole. Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake another 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift the flour, baking powder and sea salt.
Stir in the parsley.

title: orange waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apple with lemon juice.
In a large salad bowl, combine all ingredients and toss lightly.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Mix well; roll out onto a floured surface.
Roll up and cut with knife into thin noodles or 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.

title: somemores
directions: Make a sandwich of piece of chocolate and two crackers.
Toast a marshmallow golden brown and well puffed.
Pop it into the sandwich and press gently together.
Eat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer in buttered dish with tomato wedges on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.
The chips/onion rings provide the salt.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add alternately the flour, baking powder and salt (mix together in small bowl).
Fold in grated rind of lemon and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: In a large, heavy saucepan, combine sausage, beef, mushrooms, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook about 15 minutes or until onion is translucent and meat is crumbly and no longer pink; drain off liquid.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, olives and bay leaf. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove and discard bay leaf.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Line bottom of cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Spread biscuit dough over pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese and dressing in bowl.
Spread over crust.
Spread chopped vegetables over mixture.
Sprinkle with both cheeses on top. Serve cold.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients, except hash browns, cornflakes and 1/4 cup margarine.
Then add hash browns.
Put into casserole dish. Mix melted margarine and cornflakes.
Sprinkle on top of hash brown mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add orange juice, pineapple and orange slices.
Place in 8	x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Congeal in refrigerator.
Prepare pudding
by package directions using 1 cup cold milk; fold in	whipped
topping.
Spread
over congealed salad and top with	nuts.
Place
in refrigerator until completely firm.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce.

title: meal-in-one casserole
directions: Arrange in layers.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 400°.

title: beef hash
directions: Combine broth, potato, onion, beef and seasoning.
Melt butter in heavy ovenproof skillet. Add meat mixture. Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until potato and onion are tender and hash is lightly browned on bottom.
Uncover and place in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. To serve, fold hash in half like an omelet and slide onto a platter.
Serves 6.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes with broth; set aside.
Grease a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Layer the following: 1/2 chicken, 1/2 tortillas (in bite size pieces), 1/2 onion, 1/2 sauce (soups and broth) and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: aeblekage - apple cake
directions: The crumbs may be from dried French bread, cake, zwieback or from a combination of two of these.
Brown crumbs well in a skillet with butter and sugar.

title: microwave cheese and bean dip
directions: Mix
soup
and cheese in 1 quart measuring cup.
Microwave for 3 minutes on Medium (50% power), stirring occasionally.
Blend sour cream, onion and hot pepper.
Heat 1 additional
minute. (May
take
longer, depending on your microwave.) Serve with crackers or chips.

title: dean's peanut butter fudge
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and milk over medium heat.
Stir to full boil (soft ball) 230°.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Stir.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage until brown, then drain.
Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low heat until all is melted.
Serve over chips.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix well and refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: blue ribbon white cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add baking powder and salt to sifted flour.
Add flour and milk alternately to creamed mixture. Add vanilla.
Fold in egg whites by hand.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes (two 9-inch layers).

title: dietetic pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk together. Add pumpkin and spice to taste. Pour into baked crust and chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: beef parmesan
directions: Trim fat from round steak.
Cut into 5 or 6 pieces.
Beat eggs in medium bowl.
In shallow dish, combine bread crumbs and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Roll meat in beaten egg; roll in bread crumbs to coat.
Brown meat in hot oil.
Transfer to oblong baking dish. Saute onion and garlic until tender.
Stir in tomato paste, Italian seasoning, salt, sugar and 2 cups hot water.
Bring mixture to a boil; boil gently for 5 minutes.
Pour 1/2 sauce mixture over meat.
Place Mozzarella cheese over meat.
Pour remaining sauce over Mozzarella cheese.
Top with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cover and cook 45 minutes at 350°, uncover and cook 10 more minutes.

title: pasta and ceci (chickpeas)
directions: Brown
garlic in oil in a 3 quart saucepan.
Add tomato sauce and simmer for about 15 minutes.
Drain and add ceci to sauce
and cook on low heat for about 15 minutes.
Add cooked pasta
and cook
for
another 15 to 20 minutes.
Add a little water, if needed.
Serves 4.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix well. Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook until warm or 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 325°
for 1 hour. Makes 2 large loaves.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Add baking powder to salmon juice and let foam.
Mix flour into salmon with egg; add juice and mix again.
Drop by teaspoons into hot oil to cook.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Scald sweet milk; add shortening or butter.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast cake dissolved in warm water.
Add 3 tablespoons of sugar, 2 tablespoons of salt and 3 cups of plain flour; beat thoroughly.
Let rise to double in bulk.
Add flour to make dough.
Make out rolls.
Let rise, then bake at 350° to 375° until golden brown.

title: french apple cobbler
directions: Combine apples, 3/4 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt, cinnamon, vanilla and 1/4 cup water in bowl, mixing well.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Combine 1/2 cup flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, 1/4 teaspoon salt, 2 tablespoons butter and egg in bowl, beating well. Drop by 9 large spoonfuls over apples.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: meringue
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Then add water, stirring well. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until transparent. Cool.
Beat egg whites and salt until foamy.
Continue beating while adding cooked mixture into egg whites.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Put on top of pie, being sure to seal to crust. Brown in 350° oven.

title: mexican beef bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Brown hamburger and drain off fat.
Stir in chili powder; cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in taco sauce, chiles and salt.
In small bowl, combine corn and 1/2 onions.
In casserole, layer half the corn mixture, half the beef mixture, half the olives and half the cheese.
Repeat layering. Bake, covered, for 20 minutes until heated and cheese is melted. Garnish with tortilla chips, sour cream, tomato and remaining onions to serve.

title: rib-eye steaks with roquefort glaze
directions: Combine
first
6 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed of an electric
mixer until smooth.
Spread a thin layer over top of each
steak.
Place
on
lightly
greased rack of a broiler pan. Broil 4
inches from heat for 4 to 6 minutes on each side or to desired degree of doneness.

title: beef stew
directions: Heat corn oil in a large pan.
Cut meat in 1-inch cubes and chop onion.
Brown onion and meat in hot oil.
After all water has cooked out, brown flour in the hot oil.
Cut carrots and potatoes into small pieces.
Add with enough water to cover well.
Simmer until well done.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Melt butter in 11 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread graham crackers to make bottom layer.
Add next layer of chips, coconut and nuts. Pour can of Eagle Brand milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: great and easy stew
directions: Put cut up meat in a very large roasting casserole with carrots, onions, tomato sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake, covered, at 250° for 5 hours.
After 3 hours, add sweet potato and regular potatoes.
Cook until tender.
At very end, thicken with potato starch, dissolved in wine or water.
Mushrooms and pearl onions are an optional addition.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Add yeast to warm water. Add other ingredients and let dough rise. Work into biscuits and drop into hot fat.

title: quick, easy, delicious italian meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except puree.
Shape into balls. Place in large oblong baking pan.
Pour puree over all.
Sprinkle with more cheese and seasonings, if desired.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 1 hour.
Serve as main dish with spaghetti or as small sandwiches on Parker House rolls.
You can keep them hot in crock-pot.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar well.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add eggs last, beating one at a time.
Add vanilla. Makes 2 layers.

title: sam's cabbage
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; set aside.
In a large frying pan put cabbage, onion, water and bacon drippings.
Cover and cook 30 minutes or until as done as you like it, but cook until mushy. Then add the sugar, salt, pepper and red pepper.
Cook a little longer, 5 or 6 minutes.
Don't forget to add the crumbled bacon to cabbage for added flavor.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Brown beef.
Pour all ingredients on top of beef.
Use roasting pan with tight lid.
Place in oven for 3 hours at 350°. Serve with wild rice.

title: chocolate midgets
directions: Combine
sugar, 1 cup flour and baking powder; mix well and set aside.
Combine butter and chocolate syrup in a heavy saucepan;
bring
to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat
and
cool.
Gradually
stir into flour mixture.
Stir in eggs
and
vanilla.
Dredge pecans in remaining 1/2 cup flour; stir
into
batter.
Pour
batter
into
a greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until wooden
pick
inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes; cut into squares to serve.

title: old time fudge
directions: In an iron skillet, add butter, cocoa, sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down heat so it won't boil over.
Cook until it makes a hard ball in cool water.
Remove from heat and add nuts. Pour out on buttered plate.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in 1 cup of water for 20 minutes.
Stir in sugar and cook 5 minutes longer.
Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water; add to hot cranberries and stir until dissolved; set aside to cool.
When mixture begins to thicken, add chopped celery, nuts and salt.
Turn into mold that has been rinsed with cold water. Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Unmold on serving plate. Garnish with salad greens, if desired.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well and bake in buttered casserole at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cedric's casserole
directions: Spread half of cabbage in 3-quart dish; cover with meat, then remaining cabbage.
Spread 1 can tomato soup over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake potatoes alongside for a complete meal.

title: smoky brisket
directions: Combine seasonings and pour over brisket; marinate overnight. Place brisket in roasting pan.
Cover with aluminum foil and place lid on roaster.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Do not remove lid during baking.
Let stand 15 minutes before slicing.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: vegetables in sour cream
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Chill until nearly set; add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: In large skillet, cook potatoes until tender. Next, add onion, peppers and mushrooms. Cook until tender. Whisk eggs together in small bowl. Add to skillet along with cheese cubes. Stir constantly. Cook to desired doneness. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: corn pudding casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour in an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Drain juice off beans.
Brown bacon and drain.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Combine all meat and beans.
Add ketchup, brown sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sawdust salad
directions: First Layer:
Dissolve gelatins in boiling water; stir in cold water.
Add crushed pineapple.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan; chill until set.
Top with sliced bananas and miniature marshmallows.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Place dinner rolls in a 9 x 13 pan. Mix together pudding, brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over rolls. Melt margarine and pour over rolls. Sprinkle nuts on top. Cover with plastic wrap. Let rise in warm place until rolls double in size. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry sausage and hamburger until lightly browned.
Add onions, pepper and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add tomato sauce and tomatoes; simmer 1 hour or longer.
Ten minutes before finished, add cheese.
Mix well.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: honolulu chicken
directions: Boil chicken, debone and cut up. Brown flour

and oil. Add salt, pepper, preserves, barbecue sauce and soy sauce. Add enough broth and chicken for consistency desired to serve over rice. Cook until tender. Add green pepper and water chestnuts (cut in bite size pieces). Serve over rice.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Trip off large and tough ends of broccoli.
Wash and cut into bite pieces.
Put in large bowl.
Add bacon and onions.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; add dressing to broccoli mixture and toss gently.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: quick fudge
directions: Heat in microwave until melted.
Pour in buttered dish.
Let cool, then cut.

title: nut cake(from 1975 edition)
directions: Grease tube or Bundt pan and dust with flour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter to cream it; beat in sugar (gradually).
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat until thick and light.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to butter mixture alternately with milk; blend well.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until light, not dry.
Fold in; do not beat again.
Bake about 1 hour.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into 9-inch pastry.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in very hot oven, 450°, for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° and bake 30 to 40 minutes longer or until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill in refrigerator.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: nori hamburger
directions: Mix hamburger, Teri burger mix, onion and egg.
Mix well. Place about two to three tablespoons of mixture to center of sheet of nori.
Spread evenly in middle.
Fold ends of nori.
Place in pan with folds downward so nori will stick together.
Place in refrigerator for about three to four hours.
Coat with flour and fry in oil.
Slice in several pieces.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Combine warm potatoes (mashed) with beaten egg, salt and pepper.
Add a little milk if mixture is too dry.
Form ball around marshmallow.
Roll in corn flakes.
Place in oiled baking dish.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: walnut dainties
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Add flour and salt. Blend thoroughly.
Mix 2 tablespoons of flour with coconut and nuts and sprinkle over the top after batter is poured into a greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buckeyes candy
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar and margarine together well. Form into walnut-size balls and refrigerate.
Melt chocolate chips, paraffin and vanilla in a double boiler.
Dip the balls into the chocolate mixture, leaving the very top without chocolate on it.
Place on waxed paper and let dry.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and lard.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk in separate bowl.
Pour mixture over melted margarine; do not stir. Lay blueberries around in mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
Tastes good with vanilla ice cream on top.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and pour in greased casserole dish.

title: rum cake
directions: Use conventional method of mixing butter cakes.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour at 350°.
While cake is cooling in pan pour the following hot glaze over it when cool.
Remove from pan and pour remaining mixture over it.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients except the nuts.
Shape into a ball and roll in nuts.
When ball is evenly coated with nuts, chill about 1 hour.
Serve with your choice of crackers.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Do not grease or flour your pans.

title: tamale dressing
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, mixing well. Pour mixture into a greased 3 qt. pan or casserole dish.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Remove unpopped kernels.
Melt margarine over low heat.
Add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Pour over popcorn.
Grease hands with margarine and form popcorn into balls.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix and cook over low heat.
Good on hot biscuits.

title: butter squash and apples
directions: Cut each squash in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds.
Cut squash into half-inch slices and peel.
Layer squash in a lightly greased 12-inch round glass dish.
Top with apple slices.
Mix all remaining ingredients and spoon over squash and apples.
Seal with foil.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until squash is tender.
Remove foil during last 5 minutes of cooking time. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: cherry delights
directions: Combine ingredients.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.	Roll in 1-inch balls;
press
a
cherry in the center.
Dip in beaten egg whites; roll in coconut.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 325° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: el chili de antonio(winning entry of "7th annual chili cookoff"-spanish iii)
directions: Chop your onion finely and simmer in oil or water for 10 minutes over a medium flame.
Add hamburger meat, salt, pepper and chili seasoning mix; let simmer until meat is cooked, about 10 minutes.
Add salsa, tomato sauce and beans.
Simmer for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in 1 1/2 C. hot water.
Add remaining water. Chill until partly set.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to the Jello, mixing only slightly.

title: e-z hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Coat frying pan with Pam.
Brown both sides over medium heat.
Cover and simmer until done, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: white house fudge
directions: Boil sugar, butter, salt and milk for 6 minutes, stirring often. Combine chocolate morsels, German's chocolate, marshmallow cream and nuts. Pour boiling syrup over chocolate mixture. Stir until all is melted, working fast. Pour into 10 x 15-inch pan. Let stand a few hours before cutting into squares.

title: rhubarb sauce
directions: Heat sugar and water to boiling, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat.
Add rhubarb.
Simmer, uncovered, until rhubarb is tender and slightly transparent, about 10 minutes.
If desired, add a few drops of red food coloring.
Serves 5.

title: rich butter wafers(cookies)
directions: Cream butter until soft; add sugar gradually, until light. Beat in egg.
Add vanilla and flour and mix well.
Roll dough into small balls, about 3/4-inch, and place on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Press down to flatten with the bottom of a glass dipped into sugar (dip into sugar before each cookie).
Bake at 375° for 10 to 11 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: hot appetizers
directions: Cook hamburger and sausage; drain.
Melt cheese and mix together.
Spread on cocktail rye or pumpernickel bread.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Blend until smooth. Roll into balls.
Roll balls in graham cracker crumbs.

title: ham loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine bread crumbs with onions.
Stir in eggs and milk.
Add ham, pepper, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pat into 8 or 9-inch loaf pan.
Put brown sugar on top.

title: baked nacho dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Hollow out the loaf of bread, reserving the cubes for dipping.
In a two-quart saucepan, blend and heat the first 4 ingredients.
Pour this mixture into the bread shell and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Heat oven
to
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Beat cheese, butter
and milk with electric mixer until well blended. Gradually
add
flour
mixture.
Shape teaspoons of dough into 1/2 inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten
with
a
fork to 1/2 inch thickness.
Bake 12 minutes until
bottom
is brown.
Cool on cookie sheet or wire rack 1 minute, then remove to rack to cool completely.
Store in tightly covered container.
Can keep up to two weeks.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Drain off water.
Cook rice in 2 1/2 cups water.
Saute onion in butter until tender, not brown.
Mix together broccoli, rice, onion, Cheez Whiz, mushroom soup and 1/3 cup water.
Put in 2 quart casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas caviar
directions: Soak peas overnight.
Drain and/or add more water and simmer 40 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Serve hot or cold.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Roll the dough out lengthwise until it looks like a flat loaf of Italian bread, but twice as wide.
Down the center of dough spread a little margarine and sprinkle with salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Place a row of salami down the center, longways, then place a row of Swiss cheese on top of salami.
Fold the dough in half, pressing the sides together tightly.
Now you can become creative. Shape the dough into a ring, leave it long, like a loaf of bread or just give it a little twist, so it will look like a loaf of Italian bread.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Brush on egg and bake for a few minutes more.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix contents gently until smooth.
Pour into a 9-inch prepared oil-pastry crust and bake approximately 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: different dip for fruit
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan over low heat.
Add brown sugar, cook until sugar melts, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Serve dip with an assortment of fresh fruit.
Yield:
1 1/3 cups.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Place in sieve and with back of spoon, press out excess water.
Mix spinach with rest of ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 24 hours.
May be prepared in advance, up to 3 days.
(Makes 3 cups.)

title: jumbo cookies
directions: At medium speed, in a large bowl, beat the margarine or butter with brown sugar.
Add granulated sugar and beat until creamy. Blend in vanilla and egg.
At low speed, blend in flour, salt and soda.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips, chopped nuts, M&M's, coconut or any combination you desire.
Set aside an additional 1/2 cup of the same ingredient for sprinkling on top later.
Chill dough in refrigerator for 1 1/2 hours or in the freezer about 45 minutes. Grease a 12 x 1/2-inch deep round foil baking pan or 12-inch round pizza pan.
Place dough in pan and press it evenly within 1 1/2-inches of the edge.
Sprinkle reserved topping on dough.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Cool on rack, then remove from pan.

title: mom's easy lemon cake
directions: Put first five ingredients together in a bowl and mix well. Put in greased oblong pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: khrusty(angel wings)
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth.
Roll out on floured surface, very thin.
Cut 2 1/2-inch strips vertically and then cut on a diagonal to make diamond shapes.
Make a 1/2-inch slit vertically in center of each diamond shape.
Pull one end through slit.
Fry in electric skillet or on the stove in deep hot oil or Crisco, until very lightly browned, turning once.
Do not overcrowd skillet.
Drain on paper towels; cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
After the dressing is mixed, add the first five ingredients and serve. If making the night before, add sunflower nuts right before serving.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: If using angel food cake, slice it into three layers, starting with cake, layer each ingredient in a punch bowl.
Repeat layers. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 25 servings.

title: cathy's cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and lite brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in sifted together flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add oatmeal.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and pecans.
Roll into golf ball size and place on a cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 370° for 5 minutes.
Press down from a ball to a pancake.
Cook 7 more minutes.
The dough is great kept in the refrigerator for a few days.

title: meat croquettes(leftover meat)
directions: Mix together.
Chill.
Shape into pyramids or cylinders.
Roll in fine dry bread crumbs.
Set aside 2 to 3 hours in refrigerator. Dip in mixture of 1 egg (slightly beaten) and 2 tablespoons water. Again, roll in fine dry bread crumbs.
Let dry again 1 1/2 hours (refrigerate).
Fry in deep fat (400°) until delicately browned (1 1/2 to 2 minutes).
Drain on absorbent paper in warm place.
Keep hot in oven until time to serve.
Serve hot with hot mushroom or tomato sauce or any desired sauce.
Yield:
8 pyramid croquettes, 3 inches high.

title: mrs. nell's company beans
directions: Drain beans, peas and lima beans.
Mix ingredients together. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until well heated.

title: broccoli pizza
directions: Rub Boboli with a little olive oil.
Take fresh broccoli and saute in olive oil with fresh garlic, salt, pepper and oregano for about 7 minutes.
Layer Muenster cheese on Boboli, then layer fresh broccoli, then add Mozzarella cheese and finish with American cheese on top.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Place directly on oven rack.

title: ritz cracker cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter between 2 crackers.
Melt chocolate or almond bark; dip crackers in coating.
Let dry.

title: "easy" au gratin potatoes
directions: Combine butter, flour and milk in saucepan and heat until thickened (be sure and stir).
Add Cheddar soup.
Spread hash browns into 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 pie plates (greased).
Pour mixture over hash browns and mix well.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Cover bottom of pan with peaches.
Cover peaches with mixture of flour, sugar, milk and baking powder. Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 11-inch pan.

title: our favorite meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into small balls.
Place into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Place in a 375° oven for about 30 minutes or until meatballs are brown.
Take out of the pan and drop them into the Meatball Sauce.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together; cut in shortening.
Mix with buttermilk; turn out on floured board.
Knead lightly.
Roll the dough to 1/2-inch and cut with biscuit cutter dipped in flour. Drizzle with liquid margarine.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breasts, remove meat from bone and shred.
Mix with other ingredients.
Serve with fruit and crackers (pineapple halves).

title: flaky biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk to mixture.
Stir together.
Put on lightly floured board or pastry sheet.
Knead for 1/2 minute or so.
Press to 1/2 inch thick for fluffy biscuits.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: milk shake in a blender
directions: Put the milk and ice cream into the container.
Cover.
Press the shake button for 10 seconds.
Yields 1 serving.

title: snicker bar cookies
directions: Preheat oven using cookie dough directions.
Press cookie dough in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake by cookie directions. Arrange candy over baked layer.
Bake until candy is softened. Spread evenly over surface.
Cool.

title: sirloin tips in wine sauce
directions: Brown sirloin tips in oil and place in a baking dish.
Saute onions, peppers and mushrooms for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add to meat and mix.
Add cooking wine.
Mix together beef bouillon cube, water and flour; add to meat.
(One package of brown gravy mix and 1 cup water may be used instead of bouillon.)
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours, stirring often.
Serve over noodles, rice or potatoes.

title: steamed asparagus with red-pepper sauce
directions: Remove and discard woody ends of asparagus stalks.
With vegetable peeler, peel lower part of each stalk.
Arrange in single layer in shallow 10-inch microwave-safe dish.
Add water. Cover with plastic wrap and microwave 3 to 4 minutes.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Mix dip and let sit 4 to 5 hours.
"Light" versions of mayonnaise and sour cream may be used.
To cut down on saltiness, boil dried beef for a minute and drain well before adding it to mixture.
Cut off top(s) of rye bread, scoop out center and cut into cubes for dipping later (fresh vegetables may be used also). Fill the center of bread with dip.
You can eat the whole thing.

title: frozen berry fluff
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and butter.
Press into bottom of a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Beat egg whites and vanilla slightly in large bowl.
Gradually beat in sugar and berries.
Beat at high speed 12 to 15 minutes.
Mixture is fluffy and has large volume.
Fold in whipped cream; spread over crumb crust.
Freeze overnight.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Saut chicken breasts in butter or margarine. Season with salt and chicken seasoning. Dissolve 2 cubes chicken bouillon; add to chicken breasts. Put in casserole and add rice with broccoli; top with grated cheese. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese stuffed pickles
directions: Cut off ends of pickles and remove centers with apple corer or potato peeler.
Soften the cream cheese and add enough cream to moisten.
Add the Worcestershire sauce and bacon bits and mix well.
Stuff the pickles with cheese mixture and chill for 2 to 4 hours.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: easy sweet and sour chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, mix together the dressing, preserves and onion soup.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake for 25 minutes, covered.
Uncover; bake for an additional 20 minutes, or until chicken is fork-tender.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken and mushroom dijon
directions: In skillet in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown on both sides.
Remove.
In remaining 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook broccoli and mushrooms until tender and liquid is evaporated, stirring often.
Stir in soup, milk and mustard.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover; cook over low heat 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring occasionally.
Serve with noodles.
Serves 4.

title: summer corn relish
directions: Remove husks and silks from corn.
Place ears in boiling water to cover.
Return water to a boil; cook 5 minutes.
Drain and immediately cover ears with ice water.
Let stand until cool; drain.
Cut corn from cob, measuring 8 cups of kernels.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Slice and peel apples.
In separate bowl, mix cinnamon and 5 tablespoons sugar.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients. Mixture will be thick and smooth.
Grease and flour large tube pan.
Pour in part of batter, then layer of apples, then sugar and cinnamon.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, cut Twinkies longway in 1/2 with filling up.
Mix instant pudding and milk together.
Slice bananas; layer bananas and pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cut the ends off the eggplant and slice the rest into 1/2-inch thicknesses.
Slice the onion and tomato in 1/4-inch thicknesses (or as you prefer).
Using the margarine, grease a large, flat baking dish well.
Salt and pepper both sides of the eggplant slices and arrange them in the bottom of the baking dish.
Cover each slice with
a slice (slices) of onion and lightly salt.
Cover the onions with slices of tomato; salt again.
Top each stack with a small pat of margarine and cover the baking dish with foil. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Remove the foil and sprinkle each stack generously with Parmesan cheese.
Return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: ice cream cupcakes
directions: Follow the directions on the cake mix box.
Instead of pouring in cupcake liners, pour batter into ice cream cones.
Bake according to the directions for cupcakes.
Frost and decorate.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel and halve eggs. Remove yolks. Mash yolks, add salt & pepper, sugar, mayo. Melt butter in small pot, add shrimp & steam for 5 minutes or until opaque. Drain. Chop shrimp til fine; add to egg yolk mixture. Stir well. Spoon into egg whites. Sprinkle with paprika on top.

title: pumpkin soup - ii
directions: Mix everything together and cook slowly.

title: texas hot sauce
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients, add water, rest of spices and bread.
Warm hot dog buns, put mustard on hot dogs.
Add onions and then Texas Hot Sauce.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll dough into walnut size balls. Roll the balls in a mixture of two tablespoons of sugar and two teaspoons of cinnamon.
Bake at 350°.

title: indian rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in melted margarine until tender.

Stir in water, uncooked rice, parsley, bouillon, curry powder, allspice, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Bring to boiling and reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Stir in raisins and peanuts.

title: zesty onion meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, 1/3 cup of soup, 2/3 cup French fried onions and remaining ingredients. Shape into 8 x 4-inch loaf and place in loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour until meat loaf is done. Pour off fat. Spoon remaining soup over meat loaf. Top with 2/3 cup onions. Bake 5 minutes more until onions are golden.

title: honey-whole wheat bread(follow receipt exactly)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Stir in honey, shortening, salt and 1 3/4 cup water and whole wheat flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough all-purpose flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn greased side up.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double, about 1 hour.
Punch down.
Divide into halves.
Flatten each half with hands or rolling pin to 18 x 9-inches.
Fold crosswise into thirds, overlapping the 2 sides.
Roll up tightly, beginning at one of the open ends.
Press with thumbs to seal.
Press each end with sides of hand to seal.
Fold ends under loaf.
Place loaves, seam side down in in 2 greased baking pans.
Brush with margarine.
Let rise until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fricasseed raccoon
directions: Remove fat from lean meat.
Combine flour, salt and pepper in a bag.
Add meat and shake bag to coat.
Fry in hot fat until brown.
Add water, cover and simmer 2 hours or until tender.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll out bread dough until it forms a 9 x 12-inch rectangle. Place spinach, meat and cheese on dough, leaving a 1-inch border. Roll up jelly roll fashion and seal seams.
Place seam side down on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash beans. Add boiling water. Cover and let stand 1 hour or longer. Cook in same water until tender (about 1 hour). Add more water as necessary. Add all ingredients to the beans. Blend. Pour beans into deep baking pan. Bake.

title: christmas snowballs
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix biscuit mix, butter, nuts and flavoring.
Add water; stir with fork until dough forms a ball and cleans the bowl.
Shape into 24 small balls; bake for 10 to 12 minutes on an ungreased baking sheet.
While warm, roll each ball in confectioners sugar.
Decorating gel may be used on top. Squeeze 3 small red dots in the center, then squeeze 3 green leaves for the Christmas flower.

title: old time potato salad dressing
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients and cook until thick, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add the mayonnaise or salad dressing and mustard.
Mix and add to cooked potatoes.

title: pecan cake
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, 2 cups sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 2 teaspoons baking soda.
Boil 2 sticks butter and 1 cup water and pour over dry mix.
Add 2 eggs and 1/2 cup buttermilk and mix. Pour onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or slightly longer.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Mix strawberry D-Zerta according to package and leave to cool. Take graham crackers and crush.
Add 1/4 cup melted butter plus 2 tablespoons powdered sugar to make crust.
Put in a cake pan. Mix cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla in separate small bowl.

title: energy bars
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and marshmallows in a microwave until smooth. Add remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan lined with foil or sprayed with cooking spray. Flatten. When set, cut into squares.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix and add 1 stick of melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
This recipe is a delightful surprise to family and guests.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to mixture.
Add water and pumpkin.
Beat well. Pour into 2 greased 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.

title: german soft pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix in salt and flour.
Knead dough until smooth.
Let rise 15 minutes. While dough is rising, mix baking soda and cold water together. Roll dough out to 1/2-inch thickness and cut into strips.
Shape into pretzels.
Brush with baking soda solution and sprinkle with coarse salt.
Place pretzels in a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with cheese sauce, hot mustard or plain.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt margarine; mix all together.
Sprinkle with cinnamon before baking.
Bake 1 hour or until firm at 375°.
Makes 4 pies.

title: pork chops(electric frypan)
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides at 360°.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook at 220° for 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: rose freedman's sponge cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and beat for 20 minutes on low speed.
Sift potato starch and cake meal.
Beat yolks until light and creamy.
Add lemon juice.
Add yolk mixture to egg whites.
Fold dry ingredients into egg mixture.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pear pie
directions: Mix together sour cream and vanilla, almond and lemon extracts.
Coat pears with 2/3 cup sugar and 1/3 cup flour and stir into sour cream mixture.
Place in 9-inch pie shell which has been cooked at 325° for 10 minutes.
Mix together 1/4 cup brown sugar, flour and butter until crumbly.
Top pie with this crumbly mixture and bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and add next 4 ingredients.
Blend and cook for 5 minutes.
Add 4 cups of water; mix and boil for 10 minutes.
In a saucepan, add just enough butter or margarine to fry tortillas, about 3 seconds each.
Layer in Dutch oven tortillas, meat mixture, onions and cheese (3 or 4 layers).
Bake at 325°, uncovered, about 40 minutes.

title: sourdough pancakes
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Fry on a hot griddle.

title: french lemon pie
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Beat eggs; blend all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350°.

title: lime or lemon pie
directions: Beat ingredients, the first 3, into froth.
Place into pie crust and refrigerate.
(I put it in the freezer.)

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water.
Put into a colander and set aside to drain.
Cook and bone chicken.
Cut into large bite size pieces.
Spread broccoli in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Put chicken over broccoli.
Mix soup (undiluted), mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice.
Spread over chicken and broccoli.
Melt butter, toss bread crumbs in it, add cheese and top the casserole. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Cream together Crisco, brown sugar, peanut butter, salt and egg.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten by pressing crisscross with tine of fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pineapple-pecan upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter.
Sprinkle evenly with brown sugar.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup pineapple juice.
Set juice aside. Arrange pineapple slices in single layer over brown sugar.
Place pecan half in center of each pineapple slice; set aside.

title: seven-layer cookies
directions: Pour melted butter into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Layer graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and condensed milk in prepared pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
May use more pecans, if desired.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: angel crisps
directions: Cream sugars, shortening and egg.
Add vanilla; blend well. Add sifted flour and other dry ingredients.
Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip top half into water, then into some granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press down into the center of each with a finger.
Decorate center with a walnut half or a candied cherry, if desired.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Combine dressing and cheese. Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly and chill.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Steam broccoli until tender or according to package directions.
Drain well.
Place in bottom of a baking dish sprayed with Pam.

title: the "ugly but scrumptious" cake
directions: Mix together sugar, brown sugar and cocoa and sprinkle over batter.
Pour 1 1/2 cups water slowly over all and bake 45 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Delicious served warm from the oven or well chilled after refrigeration!

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Keep covered in refrigerator.
Will keep up to 10 days.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add wafer crumbs, milk, coconut and nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 80 minutes.

title: no cook strawberry jam
directions: Completely crush strawberries.
Thoroughly mix sugar with fruit; let it stand 10 minutes.
Mix the water and Sure-Jell in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Stir in fruit.
Continue stirring 3 minutes.
A few sugar crystals will remain.
Ladle quickly into jars (scald jars first).
Cover at once.
Set at room temperature for 24 hours.
Store in freezer.
If used in 3 weeks, store in refrigerator.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, nutmeg and butter.
Add eggs; beat smooth. Pour over rhubarb in unbaked shell.
Top with crust or lattice top. Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes, then at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Using microwave:
Combine sugar and orange juice in a 1 1/2-quart container.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes in microwave on High. Stir to dissolve sugar.
Boil mixture 5 minutes, or until syrup is candy consistency.
Add cranberries and cook 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, or until most cranberries have popped.
Stir well and cover to stand for several minutes.
Add liqueur and stir.
May be served warm, chilled or prepared in advance.

title: festive bean salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients in salad bowl.
Mix second four ingredients and pour over bean/olive mixture.
Chill well.
Serves four.

title: chicken pastries
directions: Mix melted butter with cream cheese.
Add to chicken and onions.
Pinch 2 rolls together at seam, making a square.
Place 1/8 of chicken mixture in center and fold sides up.
Pinch all edges together.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, bananas, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 min.
Until wooden toothpick comes out clean.

title: krispy mallow balls
directions: Melt first 3 items over water.
Dip marshmallows in mixture. Dip and roll in Rice Krispies.

title: turban fillets
directions: Sprinkle fillets with salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Mix shrimp, crabmeat, scallions and cheese and spread on fillets.
Roll fillets into a turban and secure with wooden picks.
Place turbans on end in a well-greased baking dish.
Brush generously with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Remove from oven and drain off all liquid.
Top the seafood with your favorite Hollandaise Sauce and sprinkle with paprika.
(Individual dishes work best for this recipe.)
Serves 4.

title: michelle's sparkling berry punch
directions: Combine concentrated lemonade and water.
Add raspberries, 7-Up and champagne.
Serve in punch cups.
Garnish with sherbet or fresh mint, if desired.
Makes 3 quarts or 24 servings.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: murkon(rolled-up beef steak filipino style)
directions: Boil meat until tender.
Place on platter; slice rolled up beef and pour remaining sauce on top.
Afluent Filipinos prepare this menu because of the economic stability in the Philippines.
We have lower class, middle lower class, middle class and upper class.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Simmer onions in butter until limp.
Blend in flour and water. Add
Cheez
Whiz.	Add
frozen
broccoli that has been cooked and well drained.
Add 3 well beaten eggs.
Turn into a 1
1/2	quart casserole.	Cover
with
buttered bread crumbs. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pecan icebox cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add yolk and beat well. Add milk and vanilla. Sift flour, salt and baking powder. Add pecans to dry ingredients. Combine with creamed mixture and blend well. Chill at least 1 hour after rolling dough into balls.
Wrap in waxed paper. Slice 1/8-inch thick and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: hanky pankies
directions: Brown beef and pork together.
Melt Velveeta in double boiler, then mix with meat mixture.
Put on party rye (can freeze at this point).
When serving, heat 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: oven fried mustard chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix bread crumbs, flour and paprika.
Mix mustard, 3/4 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and 2 tablespoons water.
Melt butter.
Dip the chicken breast in mustard mixture, then coat with bread crumb mixture.
Place in pan.
Bake until browned (10 to 15 minutes).

title: onion patties
directions: Mix together first six ingredients.
Stir in enough cold water for thick batter.
Mix in onions and drop by teaspoon into deep fat.
Flatten patties slightly as you turn them.
Fry until golden brown.

title: simple fruit cake
directions: Boil water, sugar, shortening, raisins, currants, salt and spices until the fruit is soft and the shortening melted.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add flour, lemon and soda; mix thoroughly.
Bake in a well-greased and floured loaf pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown rice slowly in butter or margarine.
Put in 2-quart casserole and add other ingredients.
Mix.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine frozen vegetables with cream of celery soup until well mixed.
Cover vegetables with cheese slices.
Spread Ritz cracker crumbs and melted butter on top of the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: huntington chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly (about 25 minutes).
Top with remaining cheese and melt.

title: apricot snack bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add flour, salt and soda and mix
well.
Add
oatmeal,
apricots, raisins and nuts and mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: In a medium bowl, mix together cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and corned beef spread.
Add green onions and tomatoes and mix well.
Shape into a ball; roll in mixture of pecans and parsley. Chill; serve cold with crackers.
Makes 1 (4-inch) ball.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Fry hamburgers until fully cooked.
Drain all grease off. Leave in pan.
Dice onion and add to hamburgers.
Fix gravy in small pot, gradually adding 1 cup fo water.
Stir for 2 minutes. Add to hamburgers and onion and let it stand for 2 minutes.

title: garden batter bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine 2 cups of flour, yeast and salt.
Add water, molasses, oil and egg.
Beat at low speed on electric mixer for 1/2 minute.
Scrape sides of bowl constantly. Beat for 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand stir in the remaining flour, wheat germ, carrot and parsley.
Turn batter into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover; let rise in a warm place until the bread has nearly doubled in size (45 to 60 minutes).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cover loosely with foil after the first 20 minutes of baking.
Remove from casserole dish as soon as done. Brush top crust with melted butter or margarine if desired. Cool.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook meat until it changes color and add spices until done. Add raw onions.
Dip tortillas in hot oil and roll meat into tortilla.

title: 7 layer bars
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan, sprinkle cracker crumbs and sugar over margarine evenly.
Sprinkle coconut over crumbs, sprinkle bits over the coconut, pour condensed milk evenly over all.
Add nuts and press into pan a little.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into small squares.

title: four layer dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, butter and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Pat into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spread coconut and pecans in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour over coconut and pecans.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, milk and wafers.
Dust pecans with 1 tablespoon flour.
Add pecans and coconut.
Mix well and pour into lightly greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mother's lemon snow cake
directions: Sift the sugar, flour and cornstarch before measuring.
Then sift the measured cornstarch, flour, baking powder and salt together 4 times.
Cream the butter thoroughly and add the sugar a little at a time, creaming it in well.
Add the dry ingredients alternately with the milk.
Beat the egg whites into stiff peaks. Fold into the creamed mixture.
Pour into 3 greased and floured layer cake pans and bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool in pans for 15 minutes.
Remove from pans and finish cooling.
Put the layers together with filling.

title: spinach sauteed with mushrooms
directions: Wash spinach several times.
Boil enough water to cover spinach when added.
Add and cook 1 or 2 minutes.
Drain well and cool.
Squeeze excess water from spinach and chop well.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet and saute mushrooms, salt and pepper over high heat, stirring often until browned.
Add remaining butter and spinach.
Stir and cook for about 30 seconds.
Sprinkle with garlic and stir.

title: margie's chicken casserole
directions: Mix together chicken, celery, onion, lemon juice, pepper, salt and mayonnaise.
Add almonds.
Top with Cheddar cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be frozen.
When ready to use, thaw thoroughly and then heat through at 350°.
(Doubled easily for a big lunch or dinner.)

title: peanut butter and jelly cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
In large mixing bowl with electric mixer, beat butter, peanut butter, brown sugar and honey until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat 1 minute. Gradually stir in flour mixture until well combined.
Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet 2 inches apart.

title: korean style namasu
directions: Chop
cabbage;	soak
and rub in salt water.
Rinse and remove excess water.
Mix all ingredients together;
pour over cabbage. Soak for 2 to 3 hours.

title: ranch salad
directions: Wash and cut up broccoli and cauliflower.
Drain.
In bowl, add bacon bits, cheese and sour cream.
Stir and refrigerate.

title: meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix ingredients and form a loaf.
Place in shallow pan in oven at 350°.
While it is starting to bake, combine sauce ingredients.

title: my mother's fudge
directions: Beat until ready to pour into buttered pan.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, and sugar.
Mix eggs and melted butter and combine with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and pour into pie pan. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
(The center will be runny when the pie is hot but will firm up as it cools.)
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: jambalaya
directions: *(Shrimp or crab may be substituted for the sausage or chicken.)

title: pork chop supper
directions: Put 1 tablespoon olive oil and the margarine in a large skillet that has a lid
to
fit and cook the onions and garlic until soft.
Remove
from
skillet and reserve.
Add the potatoes and saute until
tender,
turning to brown on both sides. Remove and add to
the
onions
and
garlic.
Flour
the
pork chops. Add the rest of
the olive oil and brown chops on both sides. Return the
potatoes,
onions
and garlic.
Lower heat and add the chicken
broth, rosemary, pepper and salt.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, or until chops are tender.

title: russian salad
directions: Marinate each vegetable separately with 1/2 teaspoon Russian dressing.
Divide sections of large round platter using chopped parsley, chopped pimiento and chopped green peppers.
Place vegetables in triangle with point in center of plate.

Pile high. Garnish each section differently with small pieces of smoked salmon, finely chopped hard-cooked egg whites, hard-cooked egg yolks forced through a strainer and small pieces of chicken or ham.
Serve with Russian dressing.

title: smoked sausage bean soup
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven bring vegetables and water to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add sausage and bean soup.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pie dough
directions: Mix together flour, shortening, sugar and salt until forms small peas.
Mix together vinegar, egg, water and then add gradually to other ingredients.
Cool in refrigerator 15 minutes.

title: japanese chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Combine sour cream, lemon juice, garlic, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Stir chicken into sour cream mixture to coat.
Marinate, refrigerated, for several hours or overnight.
Chicken should be completely covered with mixture. When ready to cook, preheat oven to 350°.
Remove chicken from marinade, roll coated chicken in cornflake crumbs.
Arrange pieces in single layer in shallow pan.
Drizzle half melted butter or juices over chicken.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: quick cheesy trout fillet
directions: Place fillets in a single layer in a well-greased baking dish. Combine salad dressing and tartar sauce.
Spread sauce liberally over the fillets.
Sprinkle salt and any other seasonings you may wish over this.
Crush the potato chips and spread over the fish. Sprinkle the shredded cheese over the chips, and it is ready to bake.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Melt shortening in a large saucepan.
Add sugar and blend well.
Cool 10 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla; mix well.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread evenly into a well-greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Mix with chili.
Spread in oblong baking dish.
Spread with the sour cream.
Lay cheese slices over all of this.
Crush Doritos and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve with taco sauce.
Good with salad and garlic bread.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle a few dried onion chips and a little Tony Chachere seasoning on bottom crust.
Pour the mixture in crust.
Cover with 2nd crust.
Bake at 425° until golden brown (about 40 to 45 minutes).

title: oven fried chicken
directions: In a Ziploc bag, mix flour, Bisquick, crackers, onion salt, paprika and sugar.
Beat egg and water.
Dip chicken in egg, then in mix in bag.
Fry until brown.
Then place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: party mix(microwave)
directions: Place butter or margarine in 2-cup glass bowl.
Cover and microwave on High 45 seconds or until melted.

Stir in soup mix. Combine remaining ingredients in a 4-quart microwave-safe bowl. Pour butter mixture over cracker mixture and toss well to coat. Microwave, uncovered, on High for 5 minutes, stirring twice during heating.
Cool.
Store mixture in airtight container.
Makes about 10 cups.

title: refried bean dip
directions: Spread beans in bottom of dish or pan.
Then spread on sour cream.
Add cut up tomatoes, green onions and olives.
Grate cheese; sprinkle on top.

title: hershey fudgy brownies
directions: Beat together oleo, sugar and eggs until mixed.
Combine with the Hershey's syrup.
Add the flour.
Bake on greased and floured cookie sheet in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
These are very moist brownies.

title: brown bread
directions: Boil the raisins in the water for 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Use 6 round cans (No. 2 cans) or 8 smaller round cans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Melt margarine in soup kettle.
Cook cabbage and onions in the margarine for 15 minutes.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Gradually add water while stirring and heat to boiling.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer over low heat for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding and milk.
Add sour cream and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Place a layer of vanilla wafers and bananas in bowl.
Pour pudding mix over these.
Make as many layers as you wish.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Add
to mixture.
Spread over graham crackers and cover with another layer of crackers.

title: pepperoni 'n cheese crescents
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Stretch each slightly.
Place 3 slices pepperoni on center of triangle. Top each with a tablespoon of cheese.
Roll up, starting at shortest side to opposite point.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and spices together.
Stir in pumpkin. Add Milnot, eggs and nuts; beat.
Place in shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in small amount of oil.
In large pan, add beans, tomato paste, chili powder, meat and onion.
Bring to boil.
Mash mixture (especially beans) with potato masher and reduce heat to simmer.
Cook 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed except decrease water to 1 cup. Stir in zucchini.
Bake in 9 x 13 inch baking pan or 2
(8 or 9 inch) round pans in 350° preheated oven for 37 to 39 minutes. Frost with your favorite icing.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix chicken with cream of chicken soup and Stokes green chili sauce; add chopped onion.
Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with Doritos.
Pour sauce over chips.
Sprinkle cheese over sauce. Repeat 1 more layer.
Cover top of casserole with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jello and fruit
directions: Layer prepared Jell-O (prepare according to directions on box), alternating with fresh fruit in individual dishes.
Top with Dream Whip.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together (flour and sugar mixed first). Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then 300° for 25 minutes.
Makes large pie.

title: fat-free cherry crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, oats and sugar and Butter Buds.
Save 1 cup for topping.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread pie filling in the middle and top with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Mix salt, celery seed, mustard, oil and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cabbage and onions.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: homemade pizza crust
directions: Combine water, shortening and salt in a large mixing bowl. Stir until shortening is
melted.
Let cool to lukewarm (105° to 115°).
Sprinkle yeast over mixture.
Stir until dissolved. Gradually add flour, mixing well after each addition.
Turn dough out on a lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes).
Shape into a ball.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for about 1 hour.
Punch down and divide in half.
Lightly grease hands and put dough evenly into 2 (12-inch) pizza pans.
Makes 2 pizza crusts.

title: orange ambrosia
directions: Mix jello and sugar in boiling water.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch container.
Set in refrigerator for a little while (syrup consistency, not gelled).
Add remaining ingredients, then refrigerate.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Beat eggs, milk and sugar together.
Stir in pineapple, bread cubes and butter.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve warm or cold.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and dice enough potatoes to make 4 cups.
Cover with water; add salt and cook just until tender.
Drain; let cool. Place in a large mixing bowl.
Peel and dice eggs.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Toss potatoes, egg and dressing gently. Place in airtight container; refrigerate until ready to use.

title: squash relish
directions: Heat and put into jars.
Process for 15 minutes.

title: scallop corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Turn into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Put cheese on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Good.

title: iced strawberry soup
directions: Combine strawberry yogurt, milk, cinnamon and salt.
Blend gently.
Fold in strawberries.
Chill.
When ready to serve, top each bowl with a dollop of plain yogurt and a dash of nutmeg. Float a slice of lemon on top of each bowl of soup.

title: sand crescents
directions: Cream butter in large mixing bowl.
Gradually add 1/4 cup plus 1 tablespoon sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla, blending well.
Gradually add flour and chopped pecans mixing just until blended.
Shape dough into small crescents. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Roll in additional powdered sugar.
Store in airtight containers.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: barbie's shrimp scampi
directions: Boil noodles.
Add in large skillet, butter, garlic, cheese, crab meat and shrimp.
Cover for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and mushrooms.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Pour over noodles.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Beat sugar and butter until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, and flour and milk alternately.
Add nuts.
Bake at 325° in tube pan for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Test with toothpick after first hour and 15 minutes, but the cake is large and will probably take the entire time.
Eat and enjoy!

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat undrained pineapple and jello to boiling point.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Set aside until cool.
Mix Cool Whip and buttermilk thoroughly.
Then add cooled jello mixture and pecans, if desired.
Let set until congealed.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Pour cranberries in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish and mash out evenly with spoon.
Pour pineapple (not juice) on top and stir. Mix jello according to package and pour over mixture.
Stir.
Lay pecans on top and chill.

title: sugar-free boiled chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in saucepan and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until peanut butter is melted.
Add vanilla and stir.
Slowly add oats, stirring until well mixed.
Roll out foil on table.
Drop cookies by tablespoonfuls onto the foil.
Eat when cooled.

title: fruit pudding dessert
directions: Drain pineapple and fruit cocktail, reserving juice.
Measure juice and add water to make 1 1/2 cups of liquid.
Pour into pudding mix.
Beat until thickened.
Add coconut, marshmallows and bananas.
Fold gently.
Place in serving bowl and chill.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine zucchini, oil, basil and parsley in microwave casserole dish.
Microwave 3 minutes on High, stirring once.
Cook sausage and onion in skillet; add garlic to taste.
Put beans in dish with Parmesan cheese on top.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Make cake mix as directed on cake box.
While cake is still warm, poke holes into top of cake.
(Suggestion:
Use a wooden spoon handle.)
Pour coconut cream into each hole slowly.
Add Eagle Brand milk to each hole also.
Let cake cool.
Then add Cool Whip over top of cake.
Sprinkle some coconut and pecans over top of cake.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Cook beef and drain. Set aside.
Cook bacon. Crumble. Set aside. Saute onion in bacon grease. Mix all ingredients together. Bake in casserole dish at 300° for 1 hour.

title: hot chicken nut salad
directions: Mix ingredients; add salt and pepper to taste.
Put in casserole and top with potato chips and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: loaf cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add milk and flour alternately, having sifted flour and baking powder together.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add extract.
Put in loaf tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: divinity(microwave)
directions: Mix together sugar, syrup, water and salt in a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Cook at Full power for 20 to 22 minutes or until hard ball stage is reached.
Stir 1 to 2 times.
While syrup cooks, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Gradually pour hot syrup over egg whites while beating at high speed until mixture is thick and candy starts to lose its gloss, about 12 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts and drop on waxed paper by the teaspoon.
Makes about 70 pieces.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Make a bottom crust using 1 cup graham cracker or vanilla wafer crumbs mixed with 1/4 cup of white sugar and melted oleo.

title: avocado-bean dip
directions: Layer on plate:
bean dip; avocados and lemon juice; sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning (mixed together); olives; tomatoes and cheese.

title: golden delight pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Cover and blend at high speed for 1 minute, stopping to stir down once.
Bake on greased griddle, using 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.
Makes 20 (4-inch) pancakes.
This is also excellent for waffles.
Bake extra waffles and freeze.
Reheat in toaster and they are as delicious as freshly made.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Open the bun and lay on a cookie sheet.
Put hot pepper Jack cheese on the bun and spread out evenly.
Add the pepperoni. Layer it evenly.
Add roast beef.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix together in a large bowl with all other ingredients.
Store, covered, in refrigerator overnight. Spoon batter into well-greased muffin tins. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: pie crust shell
directions: Combine flour, shortening and salt until corn meal like, then add water.
Blend together, shape in a ball and flatten.
Roll from the center out.
Roll thin and larger than pie plate using. No grease is needed in the pan.
Set oven at 350°.
Bake until golden brown.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll in coconut. Drop by teaspoon, separating by 1 inch each.
Press with thumb a spot in middle of dough.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips over top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: broiled crab meltaways
directions: Cut up 1 package of English muffins into eighths.
Place on large cookie sheet.

title: holiday ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve red gelatin completely in 1 cup boiling water in medium bowl, stirring for 2 minutes.
Stir in 3/4 cup cold water. Pour into 5-cup ring mold.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until set, but not firm.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Prepare as directed.
Bake on greased pizza pan for 20 minutes or until done.
The longer it bakes the harder the crust.
Let cool.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add bananas.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 2 layer pans or a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Good served warm with whipped cream.

title: chicken or pork adobo(guam)
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan and cook until meat is done. We serve this over rice.

title: peppered chicken and rice
directions: Combine chicken breasts, salt, black pepper, bell peppers, onion and oleo in a large boiler in enough water to provide an adequate amount of broth.
Boil until chicken breasts are very tender.
Cook over medium heat about 45 minutes.
Add uncooked rice (do not use instant).
Reduce heat to low and cook, covered, until all broth is absorbed into rice.
Stir occasionally but keep covered as much as possible.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and beat; stir milk in.
Sift dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mix.
Divide in half.
Chill 1 hour.
Lightly flour a pastry board surface. Roll to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet for 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.

title: quick rolls
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and egg.
Mix by hand until blended well.
Add water and yeast.
Mix well.
Add flour all at once and mix.
Do not allow this mixture to rise.
Put quickly into greased muffin tins.

title: ginger chicken teriyaki
directions: Marinate chicken wings overnight in mixture of soy sauce and grated ginger.
Heat oil and fry wings until well done, dark brown.
Cut up bell pepper, onions and tomatoes; add to chicken. Simmer until done.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple.
Add water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Bring to a boil and pour over gelatin; blend in cream cheese.
Let cool.
Add cherries, pineapple, nuts and Coke.
Chill until thickened.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chicken casserole with stove top stuffing
directions: Boil
chicken
and
cut in pieces.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add butter, raisins and buttermilk.
Mix to blend.
Turn onto floured surface and knead from 3 to 5 minutes or until firm.
Split in half and shape into 2 round loaves.
Place on buttered and floured cookie sheet.
Brush with milk and dust with flour.
Make an X on top of loaf with knife.
Bake until golden (about 1 hour).
Cool on rack.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare muffin tin with paper liners. In medium bowl, cream sugar and margarine on low speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Add milk, egg, 2/3 cup flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, vanilla and salt and mix just until thoroughly blended.
Gently mix in remaining 2/3 cup flour (batter should still be lumpy).
Fold in the blueberries.
Fill muffin tin liners 3/4 full (muffins will rise 1-inch above pan).
Bake until golden brown, 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt 1 cup margarine in 1 cup milk and pour over potatoes.
Refrigerate overnight covered with foil.
Uncover, sprinkle 1 cup cornflakes or Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 45 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add cake mix.
Beat and add apricot nectar; mix well.
Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Glaze with confectioners sugar and lemon juice.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix apple slices, white sugar and cinnamon; put in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; pat on top of apples.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In heavy saucepan over medium heat, melt chips and margarine with sweetened condensed milk, water and vanilla.
Cook and stir constantly until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Serve warm over ice cream.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: rice drop dumplings
directions: Mix flour, beaten egg, milk and melted butter.
Stir in rice and parsley.
Beat until smooth.
Drop from spoon into hot chicken stock.
Cover.
Cook 15 minutes; leave covered during time dumplings are cooking.
Do not boil.

title: apricot filled oatmeal bars
directions: Set oven at 375°.
Stir together flour, oats, brown sugar and soda.
Cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Press 2/3 of crumbs in the bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread with preserves.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 30 bars.

title: "one bowl brownies"
directions: Microwave chocolate and butter in a large bowl for 2 minutes or until butter is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in sugar.
Mix in eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
(Do not overbake.)

title: raisin crisscross pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, water, raisins, grated peel and fruit juice.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add nuts.
Pour into 9-inch lined pie pan.
Make lattice top cust; flute edge. Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then in moderate oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Roll gumdrops and nuts with 1/2 cup flour.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Alternately add dry ingredients and milk. Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed on mixer.
Fold in gumdrops and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, then increase heat to 350° and bake another 30 minutes or until done.
Frost with a thin icing. Makes 12 to 16 servings.
Beautiful at Christmas using red and green gumdrops.

title: raquet's pralines
directions: Melt 1 cup sugar in an iron skillet over medium heat.
At the same time, cook the sugar and milk.
Test "white" candy in cup of water.
When it makes a firm ball, pour melted sugar, a little at a time, stirring constantly.
Add some butter and 1 1/2 cups nuts. Drop on waxed paper.
When melted sugar is poured onto white candy do so slowly because it will bubble up.
Stir fast to keep from sticking or boiling over.

title: perfect pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to
Remove pie crust shell from freezer.

title: coconut pie
directions: Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: purple passion salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add cherries, pineapple tidbits and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip and cherry juice.
Chill and serve.

title: spanish bagel
directions: Cut one bagel in half.
Smear with desired amount of cream cheese.
Cut Spanish olives into small pieces and place on cream cheesed bagel.
(Bagel can be toasted, if desired.)

title: all in one chicken delight(a fast, easy falcone family favorite)
directions: Prepare stuffing according to directions.
Set aside.
In baking dish, put 4 hard-packed mounds of stuffing.
Place chicken over stuffing.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour in chicken broth.

title: chocolate bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix together all except chips. When mixed well, fold in chips gently.
Pour into greased bundt pan and bake 30-45 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a pot, cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk, stirring constantly; cook slowly until thick.
Add cheese; cook until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add chicken broth and hot water.
Blend in broccoli; cook until heated.
Garnish with red pepper flakes.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into finger-size strips.
Set aside. Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a small bowl, mixing well.
Add milk, eggs and 1 teaspoon vegetable oil, stirring until smooth.
Dip eggplant strips into batter.
