Fry in hot 375° oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: salmon in mineral water sauce
directions: Grease dish liberally with Bertolli light olive oil.
Cover the bottom with shallots and rinsed, dried and chopped mushrooms. Place the salmon steaks on top in a single layer.
Surround the salmon steaks with rinsed dried mushrooms.
Season with salt and freshly ground white pepper.
Add the mineral water.
Cook in an oven preheated to 375° for 15 minutes or until the fish is just cooked.
Carefully remove the skin from the salmon steaks and transfer to a serving plate.
Surround with the mushrooms.
Cover and keep warm.
Strain the cooking liquid into a saucepan.
Boil, uncovered, until reduced by two-thirds.
Reduce the heat to very low.
Beat in the remaining olive oil; add the skim milk and continue stirring one to two minutes.
The sauce should have a thickened consistency and look very smooth.
Pour the sauce over the salmon and mushrooms and serve.

title: grandma's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients
well.
Drop
by tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Place 2
inches apart.
Bake at 375° for about 11 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: cheese cake (jewish)
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter; mix well. Firmly press mixture into the bottom of a greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill thoroughly.
In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese with mixer until light and fluffy; gradually add sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well each time.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes at 350°.
Turn oven off.
Allow cheese cake to cool 4 hours.
Do not open oven door for the 4 hours.
Remove from oven; refrigerate 12 hours.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
Much trouble, but really worth it.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cook until thick; add 1 cup chopped nuts and spread on cake.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, butter and 1 egg together.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the mixture.
Press the remaining mixture into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
This forms the crust.
Mix together the pie mix, eggs and milk.
Pour over the crust.
Mix the reserved mixture with the sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Spoon over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix meat together. Toss in all spices. Add eggs and onion. Soak bread in milk for a few seconds (one slice at a time). Squeeze out excess milk and add bread to meat mixture. Mix everything until spices are blended evenly throughout meat.

Make into balls (any size you want). Place on broiler pan and bake in oven at 350° for approximately 30 minutes. This way the excess grease runs into bottom of broiler pan. You may have to do this several times until you run out of meat mixture. Place meatballs in your sauce; cook over medium-low heat for several hours. Don't let sauce burn on bottom of pot. Great for family gatherings.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot. Cover and cook on low for 12 to 24 hours. (High 4 to 6 hours.)

title: decorator's frosting
directions: In mixing bowl, cream the shortening for 5 minutes.
Add eggs whites.
Cream well.
Add vanilla.
By hand, gradually stir in confectioners sugar.
Makes 3 cups.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon, together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Cut bacon in strips and place on top of beans. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: homemade soup
directions: Combine soup bone, stew meat and onion in large pot.
Add 2-quarts water; let boil for 2 or 3 hours or until tender.
Add all ingredients to pot.
Bring to a boil, then simmer about 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: frosty's ice cream
directions: Put Cool Whip in refrigerator overnight to soften.
Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk together.
After well blended, add milk and mix well.
Pour into ice cream freezer and follow manufacture directions.
The secret to mixing the Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip together is to let it set in the refrigerator overnight.
It is soft all the way through and easy to mix.
I have used Hershey's chocolate milk.
It also works fine.
Whatever chocolate milk you use just make sure it is chocolate milk not chocolate drink.
You can make different kinds of ice cream with this recipe.
We have made this with Eagle Brand chocolate milk (very hard to find) and with Cool Whip Chocolate.
We have made it with Strawberry Quick and blended 2 packages of frozen strawberries and added them to the mix.
You have to blend your berries or the whole berries will end up in the bottom of your ice cream.
If you can find vanilla milk (usually at Kroger) you can make vanilla. You can also blend other kinds of fruit and add them to the vanilla for fruit ice cream.
Enjoy!

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Press 1 can of rolls into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend cream cheese, vanilla, sugar and egg yolk until smooth.
Spread over pressed rolls.
Press second can of rolls to go over cream cheese. Seal all around the sides.
Beat egg white until foamy and brush over top.
Sprinkle sugar and pecans over egg white.
Bake for about 30 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Mix all ingredients with rice.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mushroom stuffed french bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and half the flour; beat well.
Add more flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover and let rest 15 minutes.
Turn out onto floured board.
Knead 10 minutes.
Place into greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, saute mushrooms and onion in butter until soft.
Cool to room temperature.
Turn dough out onto oiled board.
Divide into 2 parts.
Pat each part out to make a 12-inch square.
Spread with mushroom mixture, dividing equally.
Roll each part up tightly. Place on cornmeal covered baking sheet.
Let rise 1 hour until doubled.
Brush with water.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour cherry pie filling into a 9 x 11-inch baking dish. Sprinkle dry cake mix over the top, then pour melted margarine evenly over the cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Very rich; can be served with Cool Whip.

title: avocado salad
directions: Chop first 3 ingredients and add the last 4 ingredients and mix well.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all of this together.
Pour in bread pan and cook at 325° or 350° until done.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and oil; add the eggs.
In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend into the oil mixture alternately with the bananas and pineapple.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes.
Nuts are optional and may be blended in after mixing the rest of the ingredients.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and egg.
Add fruit cocktail.
Sift flour, salt and soda; add to mixture.
Top with brown sugar and chopped walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Bake in greased square baking pan.

title: hasty cake icing
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients and add boiling water and cook, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire and add flavoring. Coloring may also be added.

title: pizza appetizers
directions: Brown beef and sausage.
Drain.
Melt cheese.
Mix all together. Add spices.
Spread on party rye bread.
Place on cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: nanny's holiday pomanders
directions: Melt semi-sweet chocolate bits over hot (not boiling) water. Remove from water.
Stir in sugar and corn syrup.
Blend in water.

title: canned okra to fry
directions: Mix ingredients by shaking.
Cover okra with water.
Add vinegar and salt mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Put okra in jars.
Fill with water mixture and seal.
Put in hot water bath for 10 minutes.
Have lids in boiling water.

title: dieting soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer 1 to 2 hours.

title: oreo cookies and pudding
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and sugar.
In another bowl mix both boxes of pudding with milk.
Place pudding mixture in refrigerator to set (1 hour).
Fold set pudding into Cool Whip.
Fold cream cheese into pudding mixture.
Crumble 3/4 bag of Oreo cookies into bottom of large pan.
Spread mixture over cookies.
Crumble the rest of the cookies over the top.
Place in refrigerator to settle.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together with hands and shape into balls.
Cook the wax, chocolate chips and butter all together. Drop the balls into this and put on wax paper.

title: layered salad
directions: In a large bowl layer in order given.
Cover and chill 24 hours.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Stir oats in boiling water; let stand 20 minutes.
Cream shortening, brown sugar and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and oatmeal mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in oblong pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Brown onion and sausage in a large skillet, stirring to crumble sausage. Drain well. Add soup mix to uncooked rice, water and almonds.
Mix well and simmer for 7 minutes.
Spoon into buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: oven baked stew
directions: Mix together.
Bake in covered Dutch oven or roaster at 250° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: garden pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place crescent roll dough on cookie sheet, making a crust, shaped like a pizza crust.
Bake dough in oven at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: no-bake oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, cocoa, and milk.
Stir together with whisk over medium heat.
Heat to boiling and boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until melted. Add vanilla and oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper; let cool.
Store in airtight container.
We store in refrigerator.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Boil the potatoes until tender; peel and mash.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 2 loaf pans (8 x 4 x 2-inch).
Beat the eggs lightly, then blend in the oil and water.
Add and stir in the mashed potatoes.
In another bowl, mix flour, sugar, salt, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Then stir the dry ingredients into the potato mixture with a wire whisk.
Pour into the loaf pans and bake 55 to 60 minutes or until bread tests done in the center.
Remove from pans when cool.

title: creamy herbed pork chops
directions: Trim fat; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a large skillet, cook chops in margarine or butter over medium heat for 5 minutes. Turn chops and add carrot.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes more, until no pink remains.
Remove chops; reserve drippings and carrot.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Chop artichoke hearts.
Put in bowl and combine all remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Fat-free products can be used.

title: quick western soup
directions: Saute meat and onion with salt and pepper.
Do not drain liquid from vegetables or beans.
Add sauce and water.
Add macaroni.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Cover potatoes with cold water in kettle.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain and let cool enough to peel.
Dice potatoes into 1/2-inch pieces and chill, covered. Cook onion in 3 tablespoons butter over moderate heat for 2 minutes.
Stir in flour and cook the roux over moderately low heat, stirring, for 3 minutes.
Remove pan from heat; add milk, scalded, in a stream, stirring, and cook for 2 minutes.
Stir in cream, salt and pepper to taste.
Butter 10-inch round ovenproof dish. Alternately layer sauce and potatoes in dish.
Combine bread crumbs and butter (2 tablespoons, melted) together and sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chewy spice bars
directions: Combine and spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil rice, salt, 1/2 cup sugar and milk in double boiler until rice is tender.
Add egg yolks and boil 5 minutes more.
Put in casserole and add beaten egg whites sweetened with 6 tablespoons of sugar on top.
Brown in oven.

title: cheese cake
directions: At slow speed, in mixer, add cream cheese, Ricotta cheese and sugar.
Blend well, then add 4 eggs (one at a time).
Mix well. Add vanilla, lemon juice, cornstarch, flour and butter.
At end, fold in pint of sour cream.

title: breakfast hit(for those who don't like breakfast)
directions: Brown ground meat and onion in bacon drippings.
Beat together eggs, salt, pepper and chopped pimiento.
Add egg mixture to beef mixture.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until eggs are firm. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: apple logs
directions: Scald milk, stir in sugar, salt and oleo.
Cool to lukewarm. Measure water into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast, stir until dissolved.
Stir in lukewarm milk mixture, beaten eggs and 1 cup flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add more flour to make a soft dough. Turn dough on floured board.
Knead till smooth and elastic. Grease top and bowl.
Cover:
let rise in warm place till double in bulk.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each half of dough into 16x15 inch rectangle.
Brush each with oleo.
Blend apples, pecans, sugar and cinnamon.
Spread evenly over dough to 1/2 inch of edge.
Roll tightly.
Seal edges.
Place each roll on a greased baking sheet.
Let rise till doubled, about 1/2 hour. Bake at 375 degrees for 20 minutes or until done.
While warm frost with lots of oleo, powdered sugar, cream and vanilla.
Remember:
makes 2 large rolls.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Can be served over ice or can be frozen for a slushy.
To freeze, put in gallon plastic jugs and store in freezer.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in foil at 400° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool and cut into large cubes.

title: key lime pie(low calorie)
directions: In large heat resistant bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in yogurt with wire whisk.
Fold in whipped topping with wooden spoon.
Spread in crust.
Refrigerate overnight, or at least 2 hours.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 8 Servings, 3 Points.

title: tater-tot casserole
directions: Brown burger.
Put in bottom of a casserole dish.
Mix soups together (without water).
Spread soups on top of burger.
Place Tater Tots on top of soups.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 20 minutes. Kids love this casserole.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cut carrots in circles & cook in salted water 12 minutes on low heat after starting to boil. Drain well & let cool. Mix tomato soup, worchestershire sauce, mustard & sugar. Add vinegar & oil & bring to a boil. Let cool. After carrots & soup mixture is completely cool, cut onions & peppers into bite size pieces. Make a layer of onions & peppers in casserole bowl, add a layer of carrots until you have three layers of each. Pour soup mixture over carrots & refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients. To use, add 2 Tbsp. mix to 3/4 c. hot milk.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat oleo, sugar and eggs in a large bowl with electric mixer for 3 minutes or until fluffy and light.
Stir in bananas.
Sift flour, soda and salt together and add gradually to oleo mixture; stir until well mixed.
Add sour cream; stir until smooth.
Add nuts last.
Pour batter into a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours, or until it tests done with toothpick.
Cool 10 minutes in pan on wire rack.
Remove from pan and cool.
Makes a very moist loaf.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add taco seasoning if preferred.
Combine onion, salt, pepper, lettuce, tomatoes, beans and cheese.
Mix in salad dressing.
Add ground beef to it all.
Before serving, crumble taco chips and mix in salad.

title: pasta e fagioli
directions: In a saucepan brown garlic in oil.
Add tomato sauce and water and let cook 10 minutes.
Add beans; stir gently, continue to cook on simmer.
Cook macaroni al dente, drain and add to bean mixture, stir gently.
If it gets too thick, add more liquid.
Add parsley. Serve immediately as pasta will absorb all liquid if left to sit. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
If any leftovers, add a little water and warm it up.

title: spaghetti squash salad
directions: Cook until thick:
eggs, lemon juice and powdered sugar.
Cool. Mix with spaghetti squash, apples, pineapple and coconut.
Add Cool Whip.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: If baking conventionally, preheat the conventional oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine the applesauce, cottage cheese, egg, oil and honey.

title: pecan patties
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Fry in small patties.
Mix soup with milk.
Pour over patties.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tucker's spinach dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Set aside.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Crush chips into crumbs and add onion and garlic powders, along with Parmesan cheese.
Melt margarine and add Worcestershire sauce.
Dip chicken into margarine and then coat with potato chip crumbs. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Cut Crisco into flour and salt until size of peas.
Blend egg and milk; add to flour mixture and stir until in soft ball.
Turn out on floured board and roll out to desired thickness.
I roll thin like pie crust.
Cut into squares.
Drop into boiling broth. Cover, but stir occasionally so they don't stick.

title: classic bean casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in beans and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onion and bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.
Can be doubled.
Bake the same.

title: chili-cheese fries
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add beans, chili mix and bay leaf.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Remove bay leaf.
Fry French fries. Spoon chili over fries and top with shredded cheese.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: the all american dessert
directions: Stir 2 cups boiling water into each flavor of gelatin in separate bowls until dissolved.
Stir 1 cup cold water into each bowl.
Pour into separate 13 x 9-inch pans.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours or until firm.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Layer gelatin cubes, whipped topping, cake and strawberries in 3-quart serving bowl.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping and Jell-O star jigglers.

title: ham and bean soup
directions: Rinse beans. Place beans in water. Cover and let soak in a cool place for 6 to 8 hours. Drain and rinse beans.

title: buffalo chili con carne
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, brown meat in oil; drain. Add onion and green pepper; saute for 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until the meat is tender.
Yields 6 servings (1 1/2 quarts).

title: apple nut cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil, vanilla, lemon juice and salt.
Gradually add flour, baking soda and cinnamon. Mix thoroughly, adding milk until it looks like cake batter.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Beat eggs and sugar until creamy; add oil and vanilla and beat until smooth. Add sifted flour mixture and mix to form stiff dough.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Lightly brown chicken in margarine.

Place chicken in baking dish. Add white pepper and nutmeg to chicken and cover with slices of Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Remove from oven and add half and half and sprinkle on Parmesan cheese. Broil for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: no cholesterol honey bran muffin(low-fat)
directions: Spray 12 (2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch) muffin cups with cooking spray. In large bowl, sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add bran cereal and raisins.
In small bowl, stir egg whites, milk, corn oil and honey until well blended.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in butter.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Set aside.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Steam broccoli until stems are almost tender (10 to 12 minutes); drain.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Heat oven to 400°.
Beat soup and milk until smooth.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix baking mix and butter until crumbly; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake until crumbs are light brown, about 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hawaiian rice
directions: In medium saucepan, bring 1 1/2 cups broth to a boil over high heat.
Add rice; cover and reduce heat to low setting so rice bubbles gently.
Cook for 50 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
When rice is almost done, saute green pepper and celery in 2 tablespoons broth in small skillet for 5 to 7 minutes or until softened, over medium-high heat.
Add sauteed green pepper and celery, drained pineapple, honey, vinegar and white pepper to rice and mix well.
Heat 2 to 3 minutes over medium-high heat.
Remove and stir in green onions.
Serve.

title: mocha brownie torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round cake pans. Blend brownie mix, water and eggs.
Stir in pecans.
Spread in pans and bake 20 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
In chilled bowl, beat cream until it begins to thicken.
Gradually add sugar and coffee and continue beating until stiff.
Frost cake and sprinkle with chocolate.
Chill.

title: sherry's peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together the graham crackers, sugar and butter.
Press on bottom and sides of pan.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Cool crust.

title: filled cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk. Keep dough soft; roll out and mix with flour.
Use cutter and lift with egg turner after cutting circles.
Put on cookie sheet and put 1 heaping teaspoon of filling in center; top with cut out circle.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Cook pineapple or fruit cocktail with Jell-O until bubbles (not hard boil).
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Let congeal.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
To batter add 1 teaspoon coconut flavoring and most of coconut.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan which has been greased on the bottom.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
While still hot, punch holes in cake with a straw.
Pour the following liquid into holes:
combine cream, powdered sugar and 1 teaspoon coconut flavoring.
Add enough water to make 1 cup of liquid.
Mix well and pour over cake.
Cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip.
Cover with coconut. Refrigerate.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together for dough. Pat into a greased 13 x 9 inch pan.

title: hot chili
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package (about 5 minutes).
Rinse, drain and return to pot.
Fry ground meat until no longer red.
Drain fat and add meat to macaroni; turn heat to medium-low and stir in tomato paste.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 1 hour.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: angel pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add 1 cup sugar a little at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Continue beating until a mixture holds soft peaks.
Mix cracker crumbs and 1 cup pecans.
Fold into meringue mixture.
Pour into pie plate to form shell.
Pull up mixture into peaks around edges of plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.

title: savory saucy stir-fry
directions: Marinate beef or chicken overnight in fajita seasoning mix (follow directions on package).
In hot frypan or wok, put a small amount of olive oil.
Add onion and pepper; cook for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add beef or chicken marinade; stir-fry for approximately 5 minutes.
Add the picante sauce and any remaining marinade mixture; mix until thoroughly heated.
Serve over cooked rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: ralston pineapple muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Sift together dry ingredients; blend in Ralston and sugar.
Beat egg; add oil and pineapple.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir only enough to moisten flour.
Bake until tester comes out clean.

title: molasses cake
directions: Put molasses, water, salt, spices and raisins in saucepan. Bring to boil; cook 3 minutes.
Add shortening; let cool.
Add baking soda dissolved in warm water.
Add flour, baking powder and nuts.
Stir to mix well.
Pour into greased square or loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
No egg, no sugar and little shortening.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over very low heat in pan large enough to hold all ingredients.
Add ingredients in order listed, dry ingredients, eggs, vanilla and nuts, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into well buttered 10-inch pie dish.
Bake 350° for 25 minutes.
Allow to cool before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: citrus-nut-honey slaw
directions: In a large bowl, mix well honey, lemon juice, mustard and salt.
Beat in oil until well mixed.
Add cabbage and nuts; toss to mix well.
Just before serving, stir in oranges and grapefruit. Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple upside down cake(microwave)
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar and water and cook in microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes or until mixture boils 1 minute.
Spread mixture in two 8 or 9 inch round pans (microwave safe).
Arrange pineapple and cherries.
Prepare cake mix according to directions, using reserved pineapple juice as part of the water.
Pour batter into each pan.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour, baking powder, 2 tablespoons of sugar and vinegar and stir until dough is formed.
Pat dough into a 9-inch pie plate.
Arrange apples in the shell and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Beat eggs well and pour over the top. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until golden.

title: frozen salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add juice to water to make 4 cups of boiling liquid.
Stir in jello and vanilla.
Chill until almost firm; fold in whipped topping, pineapple and walnuts into jello.
Set until firm.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Crunch up half the bag of chips.
Mix with tuna fish and onion.
In separate bowl, mix soup and milk.
Pour soup mixture over tuna mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: stir up hearty chicken stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in 3-quart Dutch oven; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer 1 hour or until thick, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot.

title: san francisco stir-fry(ready in 20 minutes)
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat in oil.
Season meat to taste. Combine jelly, cornstarch and mustard.
Add to meat.
Add vegetables.
Cover.
Simmer 5 to 7 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring frequently.
Serve over hot rice, if desired.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, stir well.
Cover and chill.
Add mayonnaise, grapes, oranges and almonds to chicken mixture; toss well.
Serve on lettuce.
Garnish with additional orange slices and grape clusters.
Yields 6 servings.

title: buttermilk yeast pancakes
directions: Place all ingredients into a medium-size bowl and stir.
Do not use a mixer.
Make batter the night before and store in refrigerator for use the next morning or even a week later.
Allow for slight rising in your bowl.
Stir gently before pouring on grill.
Very light!

title: salmon ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped nuts and parsley.
This make 2 good size balls and freezes well. Delicious!

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with powdered sugar, peanut butter and cracker crumbs.
Press into cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Spread on top.

title: one hour buttermilk rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter three 6-cup muffin pans.

title: steamed brown bread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into 2 cans (such as peach or bean cans).
Steam for 3 hours in covered kettle with water 2/3 up cans.
If cooked in smaller cans, steam for 2 to 2 1/2 hours. Serve with beans.

title: veal piccata
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder; set aside. Remove and discard any excess fat from veal and dredge in flour mixture.

title: asparagus-water chestnut casserole
directions: Drain water chestnuts; drain and slice mushrooms.
Drain and chop pimentos.
Drain asparagus; arrange spears in greased casserole dish.
Mix water chestnuts, mushrooms, pimentos and eggs with mushroom soup; pour over asparagus.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Top with onion rings.
Bake for 10 minutes longer.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: First cook rice and milk in double boiler for 45 minutes or until rice is done.
Mix all other ingredients together.
When rice is done, mix together.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes in hot water.

title: make ahead egg casserole
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons melted butter and flour, blending until smooth.
Cook over low heat until bubbly.
Gradually stir in milk; cook until smooth and thickened, stirring constantly.
Add salt, pepper and cheese; heat until cheese melts, stirring constantly. Set aside.
Saute bacon and onion in 3 tablespoons of butter until onion is tender.
Add eggs; cook until set, stirring occasionally to scramble.
Fold in mushrooms and cheese sauce.
Spoon egg mixture into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashion cheesecake
directions: Chill cream overnight in refrigerator.
Mix Jell-O and water. Cool.
Pour cream into a large bowl; beat until it is like whipped cream, then add mixture of cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla.
Add Jell-O, which should be slightly jelled.
Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: caramel popcorn(microwave)
directions: Microwave on high (10) for 12 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes.
Pour over 3 cups of popped popcorn and 1 cup peanuts; toss to coat.
Spread on foil to cool or make into balls.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix ingredients well; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Mix sugar, flour and soda in a large bowl.
Cook margarine, water and cocoa until melted and add to flour mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: maui bread
directions: Combine 1 cup lukewarm water, yeast and honey.
Set aside in a warm place until yeast is thoroughly dissolved.
Combine 3 cups lukewarm water, eggs, salt and 5 cups of flour; beat well.
Add the yeast mixture and beat in well.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 30 minutes.
Then add rest of ingredients but just enough of the flour to handle dough (dough should be slightly sticky).
Knead for 15 minutes.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double its size.
Punch down and shape into loaves.
Place into greased bread pans and let rise in warm place until double in size.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes; lower to 350° and bake 30 minutes or until bread draws away from pan.
When done, remove from pan immediately and brush tops with oil (optional).
Cool thoroughly before storing away in refrigerator or freezer in plastic bags.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: snickers
directions: Mix all ingredients except cereal.
Spread in an 8 x 8-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle cereal over top.
Freeze.
When hard, cut into squares.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease pan with 1/4 cup oil.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add egg and milk until thick batter.
Add remaining oil.
Mix well.
Pour into pan and bake until golden brown.

title: orange chiffon cake
directions: Slice cake into 3 layers.
Mix well the eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, butter and orange juice.
Then add coconut, pecans and pineapple.

title: all occasion punch
directions: Mix all juices.
Just before serving, add the chilled ginger ale.
Use an ice cream scoop to spoon balls of sherbet into punch. You may make a colored or clear ring of ice to help keep it cool.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic in hot oil until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and all seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with 2 teaspoons water and use to thicken sauce.
Add shrimp last and simmer, covered, until shrimp is cooked (about 5 minutes).
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 5 to 6 persons.

title: mandarin orange and pineapple salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Sprinkle jello over mixture and stir well.
Spoon mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Combine nuts and coconut.
Sprinkle over salad.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.
Yields 15 servings.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Line a pie pan with crust.
In a cup, put syrup and soda and pour boiling water over this.
Stir well and put in the crust.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter.
Blend in sugar and egg with a fork.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and remaining spices. Mix with apples and nuts. Turn into a greased and floured 8-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tuna salad sandwiches
directions: Drain;	then rinse tuna.
Shred one apple then mix with other ingredients.
Use enough Miracle Whip to make spreadable for sandwiches.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Mix all together and use enough milk to get consistency.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk until smooth.
Place in refrigerator until set, very short time, then mix in peanut butter.
When that is done, add Cool Whip, then spoon the mixture into pie crust and cool in refrigerator.
This is a quick and tasty dessert.

title: honey apple salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the fruit.
Stir gently and chill.

title: squash dressing
directions: Variation:
Use 1 cup buttermilk in place of soup.
Season as for chicken dressing with sage.

title: herman
directions: Mix and pour over the dough. Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: zeta's favorite dog treats
directions: In a large bowl pour boiling water over oatmeal and margarine. Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in milk, egg, sugar, bouillon and cornmeal.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Knead in the final 1/2 cup or more of flour to make a stiff dough.
Continue kneading 3 to 4 more minutes.
Pat or roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into bone shapes with dog biscuit cutter and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: best rum cake ever
directions: Before you start, sample the rum to check for quality.
Good, isn't it?
Now go ahead.
Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc.
Check the rum again.
It must be just right.
To be sure the rum is of the highest quality, pour one level cup of rum into a glass and drink it as fast as you can.
Repeat.
With an electric mixer, beat 1 cup of butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 seaspoon of sugar and beat again.
Meanwhile, make sure the rum is of the highest quality.
Try another cup.
Open second quart if necessary. Add 2 arge leggs, 2 cups fried druit and beat till high.
If druit gets stuck in beaters, just pry it loose with a drewscriver. Sample the rum again, checking for tonscisticity.
Next sift 3 cups of pepper or salt (it really doesn't matter).
Sample the rum again.
Sift 1/2 pint of lemon juice.
Fold in chopped butter and strained nuts.
Add 1 babblespoon of brown thugar, or whatever color you can find.
Wix mell.
Grease oven and turn cake into pan 350 gredees.
Now pour the whole mess into the coven and ake. Check the rum again and bo to ged.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Mix all in bowl.
Add to skillet with a little oil; cook about 30 minutes on medium heat, turning chicken a couple of times. Serve on cooked rice bed.

title: bourbon cake
directions: Place all ingredients in a mixing bowl and beat 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased Bundt pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
While cake is baking, prepare sauce.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into pie shells.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 425°.
Knife should come out clean when inserted into middle of pie.

title: beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon into an 8-inch pie plate or a 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until edges are bubbly.
Can be doubled.
Also good served cold on toast.

title: spicy texas corn cake
directions: Roast the chile on broiler pan about 4-inches from heat. Place in a paper bag until cool enough to handle.
Peel chile by rubbing in paper toweling.
Scrap out seeds and remove veins. Finely mince.

title: cherry salad delight
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges and mix together.
Pour in Eagle Brand milk and let sit for five minutes, then mix cherry pie filling in.
Fold Cool Whip into it.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine first 6 ingredients.
Cook until thickened.
Add evaporated milk; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add vanilla.
Pour into the cylinder of an ice cream freezer; add enough milk to fill cylinder 3/4 full.
Freeze according to manufacturer's directions.
Yields about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in the boiling water. Stir in the cranberry sauce, drained pineapple and nuts.
Pour into dish and refrigerate until firm.

title: cherry salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients well and chill. This is good made ahead.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in large pan of water until well done.
Reserve 1 cup of broth.
Remove chicken from bones and cut into small pieces.
Mix sour cream, soup, taco seasoning and cooled chicken broth.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan 1/2 of chips, 1/2 of chicken, 1/2 of sauce and 1 cup of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with salsa.
Serves 8.

title: dill dressing
directions: Mix together and let stand at least 4 hours.
Refreshing as salad dressing for pasta or greens.
Also good as dressing for cold chicken or fish.

title: braciola
directions: Spread meat with garlic, basil and parsley.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Roll up like a jelly roll and tie with butcher's string. Brown in a little oil and water on top of the stove along with the short rib.
Lower the heat and continue cooking until done.
Slice and serve or can be put whole in your meat sauce along with the meats for extra flavor.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Put chopped apples in bottom.
Mix
flour,
sugar
and
baking
powder.
Add slightly beaten egg
and
pour over apples.
Pour melted butter over the top and add cinnamon.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: oysters casino
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

Place two drained oysters on the deep half of one shell. Arrange filled oyster shells on a layer of rock salt in one large baking pan or six individual shallow casseroles. Fry bacon until crisp, remove from pan.
Drain and crumble.
To bacon fat, add onion, green pepper and celery.
Cook until almost tender.
Season with lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco.
Spoon mixture on the oysters in the shells and top with crumbled bacon.
Yields 6 servings.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add other ingredients.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Boil until it tests brittle when dropped in cold water.
Pour onto buttered platter.
Break into pieces when cool. (Can also drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.)

title: mexican casserole(microwave)
directions: Place frozen tortillas between paper towels.
Microwave at High 30 to 60 seconds.
Separate.
Crumble ground beef into a 2-quart casserole.
Add green pepper and onions.
Microwave at High 3 to 5 minutes or until meat loses its pink color and vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir and drain.
Mix in taco seasoning, tomato sauce and paste, water and chili powder. Microwave on Medium 10 to 15 minutes or until thickened.
Blend sour cream, eggs and pepper together in a small bowl.
Place 2 tortillas on bottom of 12 x 8-inch dish.
Top with half the meat mixture followed by half the sour cream mixture.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle with corn chips and cheese. Microwave on medium 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
In a large pot, put tomato juice, corn, peas, potatoes and ground beef.
Cook for 1 hour.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes, peppers and onions until tender.
Cool and run through blender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 hour.
Put in jars and seal.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in skillet until golden brown. Boil chicken until done. Cook spaghetti noodles in chicken broth. Remove bones and skin from chicken. Mix all ingredients together. Add cheese last and let melt.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Make several layers of cukes, onions, salt and ice.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Drain well.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil and remove from heat.
Add cucumbers and onions to syrup and return to heat until scalding hot, but not boiling.
Seal in hot jars and process in hot water bath 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hominy potatoes - onion saute
directions: Heat drippings in heavy skillet.
Cook onion slowly until transparent, not brown.
Add potatoes and hominy.
Season with salt.
Cook over moderate heat until vegetables are slightly brown and crusty.

title: baked spaghetti for the microwave
directions: Cook spaghetti for 5 minutes, drain.
Brown beef, drain off fat, add spices, puree and tomato sauce; mix well.
In a 9 x 13-inch non-metallic pan spray cooking oil.
Add mixture, then sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on half powder for 45 minutes then 15 minutes at 100% power.
Serve.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix and cook 1 hour in Bundt pan at 325°.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Add sugar to
pears,
mix
and	let
stand overnight in refrigerator.
Sift
dry
ingredients
together and add Wesson oil, eggs (beaten
well)
and vanilla.
Mix all together well. Add chopped nuts and
raisins.	Preheat
oven to 350°.	Bake 1 hour in greased and floured tube pan.

title: hot chicken salad and stuffing
directions: Bring broth and butter to boil.
Add cornbread mix and mayonnaise; blend well.
Spread 1/2 of the mixture in bottom of a large casserole.
Add chicken, onion, celery, salt and pepper. Add remaining 1/2 mixture.
Beat eggs well and add to milk.
Pour over casserole and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Pour mushroom soup over all and let set 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: low-fat chili
directions: In skillet, crumble hamburger; add onion, celery and green pepper.
Cook until meat is no longer red.
Pour into large stew pot and add chopped tomatoes, 2 cans beans, salt, pepper and hot sauce to taste.
If desired, can add 2 cups of cooked brown rice when ready to eat.

title: self filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake using package directions.
Fill paper bake cups in muffin tin 2/3 full.
Blend cream cheese with sugar; beat egg and salt.
Stir in nuts and chocolate pieces.
Drop 1 rounded teaspoonful cheese mixture into each cupcake.
Bake as directed on box for cupcakes.
May be frosted.
Serves 30.

title: mincemeat custard pie
directions: Spread mincemeat on bottom of pie shell. Bake at 425° until crust is golden, about 15 minutes. Cool thoroughly.

title: baked stuffed haddock
directions: Melt the butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble the crackers in the butter.
Place haddock on this.
Repeat layers and sprinkle on seafood seasoning.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: no bake pumpkin pie
directions: In small bowl blend milk, eggs, spices and salt.
Set aside. In medium saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over water, let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatin completely dissolved, about 2 minutes.
Blend in milk mixture.
Continue stirring over low heat until mixture is slightly thickened, about 5 minutes. Blend in pumpkin.
Turn into pie crust.
Chill until firm.
Garnish as desired.
Suggest making the day before serving for best results.

title: stuffed jalapenos
directions: Mix cream cheese with shredded, cheese, garlic powder, chopped mushrooms, and seasoned salt. Stuff each pepper shell with 1-2 tbsp cheese mixture. Roll each pepper in bread crumbs. Bake uncovered, 30-45 minutes, at 300°. Serve with sour cream or ranch dressing.This is very spicy, you can substitute sweet green peppers for tasty but mild alternative.

title: corn casserole
directions: Add all ingredients and simmer.
Top with cheese and serve hot.

title: onion and pepper relish
directions: Chop all ingredients.
Cook until thick, about 1 1/2 hours. When thick, seal in sterilized jars.

title: mustard glazed ham and cabbage
directions: Combine oil, onion and pepper in shallow 2-quart microwave proof casserole.
Cover and microwave on High 2 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in cabbage; microwave covered 3 minutes more.
Combine mustard, honey and vinegar in a cup.
Place ham steak over cabbage; spread with the mixture.
Cover and microwave on Medium for 7 minutes or until ham is heated through.
Sprinkle with parsley. Makes 4 servings.
